66 /* (!LSHIFTABLE(d, n) ? 0 : (n)) is same as n but suppress a warning, C4293, by Visual Studio. */
67 #define LSHIFTABLE(d, n) ((n) < sizeof(d) * CHAR_BIT)
68 #define LSHIFTX(d, n) (!LSHIFTABLE(d, n) ? 0 : ((d) << (!LSHIFTABLE(d, n) ? 0 : (n))))
69 #define CLEAR_LOWBITS(d, numbits) ((d) & LSHIFTX(~((d)*0), (numbits)))

75 #define BIGRAD ((BDIGIT_DBL)1 << BITSPERDIG)
76 #define BIGRAD_HALF ((BDIGIT)(BIGRAD >> 1))

176 /* The following script, maxpow.rb, generates the tables follows.
177 
178 def big(n, bits)
179  ns = []
180  ((bits+31)/32).times {
181  ns << sprintf("0x%08x", n & 0xffff_ffff)
182  n >>= 32
183  }
184  "U#{bits}(" + ns.reverse.join(",") + ")"
185 end
186 def values(ary, width, indent)
187  lines = [""]
188  ary.each {|e|
189  lines << "" if !ary.last.empty? && width < (lines.last + e + ", ").length
190  lines.last << e + ", "
191  }
192  lines.map {|line| " " * indent + line.chomp(" ") + "\n" }.join
193 end
194 [16,32,64,128].each {|bits|
195  max = 2**bits-1
196  exps = []
197  nums = []
198  2.upto(36) {|base|
199  exp = 0
200  n = 1
201  while n * base <= max
202  exp += 1
203  n *= base
204  end
205  exps << exp.to_s
206  nums << big(n, bits)
207  }
208  puts "#ifdef HAVE_UINT#{bits}_T"
209  puts "static const int maxpow#{bits}_exp[35] = {"
210  print values(exps, 70, 4)
211  puts "};"
212  puts "static const uint#{bits}_t maxpow#{bits}_num[35] = {"
213  print values(nums, 70, 4)
214  puts "};"
215  puts "#endif"
216 }
217 
218  */

323 static BDIGIT_DBL
324 maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(int base, int *exp_ret)
325 {
326  BDIGIT_DBL maxpow;
327  int exponent;
328 
329  assert(2 <= base && base <= 36);
330 
331  {
332 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT_DBL == 2
333  maxpow = maxpow16_num[base-2];
334  exponent = maxpow16_exp[base-2];
335 #elif SIZEOF_BDIGIT_DBL == 4
336  maxpow = maxpow32_num[base-2];
337  exponent = maxpow32_exp[base-2];
338 #elif SIZEOF_BDIGIT_DBL == 8 && defined HAVE_UINT64_T
339  maxpow = maxpow64_num[base-2];
340  exponent = maxpow64_exp[base-2];
341 #elif SIZEOF_BDIGIT_DBL == 16 && defined HAVE_UINT128_T
342  maxpow = maxpow128_num[base-2];
343  exponent = maxpow128_exp[base-2];
344 #else
345  maxpow = base;
346  exponent = 1;
347  while (maxpow <= BDIGIT_DBL_MAX / base) {
348  maxpow *= base;
349  exponent++;
350  }
351 #endif
352  }
353 
354  *exp_ret = exponent;
355  return maxpow;
356 }
357 
358 static inline BDIGIT_DBL
359 bary2bdigitdbl(const BDIGIT *ds, size_t n)
360 {
361  assert(n <= 2);
362 
363  if (n == 2)
364  return ds[0] | BIGUP(ds[1]);
365  if (n == 1)
366  return ds[0];
367  return 0;
368 }
369 
370 static inline void
371 bdigitdbl2bary(BDIGIT *ds, size_t n, BDIGIT_DBL num)
372 {
373  assert(n == 2);
374 
375  ds[0] = BIGLO(num);
376  ds[1] = (BDIGIT)BIGDN(num);
377 }
378 
379 static int
380 bary_cmp(const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
381 {
382  BARY_TRUNC(xds, xn);
383  BARY_TRUNC(yds, yn);
384 
385  if (xn < yn)
386  return -1;
387  if (xn > yn)
388  return 1;
389 
390  while (xn-- && xds[xn] == yds[xn])
391  ;
392  if (xn == (size_t)-1)
393  return 0;
394  return xds[xn] < yds[xn] ? -1 : 1;
395 }
396 
397 static BDIGIT
398 bary_small_lshift(BDIGIT *zds, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t n, int shift)
399 {
400  size_t i;
401  BDIGIT_DBL num = 0;
402  assert(0 <= shift && shift < BITSPERDIG);
403 
404  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
405  num = num | (BDIGIT_DBL)*xds++ << shift;
406  *zds++ = BIGLO(num);
407  num = BIGDN(num);
408  }
409  return BIGLO(num);
410 }
411 
412 static void
413 bary_small_rshift(BDIGIT *zds, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t n, int shift, BDIGIT higher_bdigit)
414 {
415  BDIGIT_DBL num = 0;
416  BDIGIT x;
417 
418  assert(0 <= shift && shift < BITSPERDIG);
419 
420  num = BIGUP(higher_bdigit);
421  while (n--) {
422  num = (num | xds[n]) >> shift;
423  x = xds[n];
424  zds[n] = BIGLO(num);
425  num = BIGUP(x);
426  }
427 }
428 
429 static int
430 bary_zero_p(BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn)
431 {
432  if (xn == 0)
433  return 1;
434  do {
435  if (xds[--xn]) return 0;
436  } while (xn);
437  return 1;
438 }
439 
440 static void
441 bary_neg(BDIGIT *ds, size_t n)
442 {
443  while (n--)
444  ds[n] = BIGLO(~ds[n]);
445 }
446 
447 static int
448 bary_2comp(BDIGIT *ds, size_t n)
449 {
450  size_t i;
451  i = 0;
452  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
453  if (ds[i] != 0) {
454  goto non_zero;
455  }
456  }
457  return 1;
458 
459  non_zero:
460  ds[i] = BIGLO(~ds[i] + 1);
461  i++;
462  for (; i < n; i++) {
463  ds[i] = BIGLO(~ds[i]);
464  }
465  return 0;
466 }
467 
468 static void
469 bary_swap(BDIGIT *ds, size_t num_bdigits)
470 {
471  BDIGIT *p1 = ds;
472  BDIGIT *p2 = ds + num_bdigits - 1;
473  for (; p1 < p2; p1++, p2--) {
474  BDIGIT tmp = *p1;
475  *p1 = *p2;
476  *p2 = tmp;
477  }
478 }
479 
480 #define INTEGER_PACK_WORDORDER_MASK \
481  (INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST | \
482  INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST)
483 #define INTEGER_PACK_BYTEORDER_MASK \
484  (INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST | \
485  INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST | \
486  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER)
487 
488 static void
489 validate_integer_pack_format(size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int flags, int supported_flags)
490 {
491  int wordorder_bits = flags & INTEGER_PACK_WORDORDER_MASK;
492  int byteorder_bits = flags & INTEGER_PACK_BYTEORDER_MASK;
493 
494  if (flags & ~supported_flags) {
495  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "unsupported flags specified");
496  }
497  if (wordorder_bits == 0) {
498  if (1 < numwords)
499  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "word order not specified");
500  }
501  else if (wordorder_bits != INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST &&
502  wordorder_bits != INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST)
503  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "unexpected word order");
504  if (byteorder_bits == 0) {
505  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "byte order not specified");
506  }
507  else if (byteorder_bits != INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST &&
508  byteorder_bits != INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST &&
509  byteorder_bits != INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER)
510  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "unexpected byte order");
511  if (wordsize == 0)
512  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid wordsize: %"PRI_SIZE_PREFIX"u", wordsize);
513  if (SSIZE_MAX < wordsize)
514  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big wordsize: %"PRI_SIZE_PREFIX"u", wordsize);
515  if (wordsize <= nails / CHAR_BIT)
516  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big nails: %"PRI_SIZE_PREFIX"u", nails);
517  if (SIZE_MAX / wordsize < numwords)
518  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big numwords * wordsize: %"PRI_SIZE_PREFIX"u * %"PRI_SIZE_PREFIX"u", numwords, wordsize);
519 }
520 
521 static void
522 integer_pack_loop_setup(
523  size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int flags,
524  size_t *word_num_fullbytes_ret,
525  int *word_num_partialbits_ret,
526  size_t *word_start_ret,
527  ssize_t *word_step_ret,
528  size_t *word_last_ret,
529  size_t *byte_start_ret,
530  int *byte_step_ret)
531 {
532  int wordorder_bits = flags & INTEGER_PACK_WORDORDER_MASK;
533  int byteorder_bits = flags & INTEGER_PACK_BYTEORDER_MASK;
534  size_t word_num_fullbytes;
535  int word_num_partialbits;
536  size_t word_start;
537  ssize_t word_step;
538  size_t word_last;
539  size_t byte_start;
540  int byte_step;
541 
542  word_num_partialbits = CHAR_BIT - (int)(nails % CHAR_BIT);
543  if (word_num_partialbits == CHAR_BIT)
544  word_num_partialbits = 0;
545  word_num_fullbytes = wordsize - (nails / CHAR_BIT);
546  if (word_num_partialbits != 0) {
547  word_num_fullbytes--;
548  }
549 
550  if (wordorder_bits == INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST) {
551  word_start = wordsize*(numwords-1);
552  word_step = -(ssize_t)wordsize;
553  word_last = 0;
554  }
555  else {
556  word_start = 0;
557  word_step = wordsize;
558  word_last = wordsize*(numwords-1);
559  }
560 
561  if (byteorder_bits == INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER) {
562 #ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
563  byteorder_bits = INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST;
564 #else
565  byteorder_bits = INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST;
566 #endif
567  }
568  if (byteorder_bits == INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST) {
569  byte_start = wordsize-1;
570  byte_step = -1;
571  }
572  else {
573  byte_start = 0;
574  byte_step = 1;
575  }
576 
577  *word_num_partialbits_ret = word_num_partialbits;
578  *word_num_fullbytes_ret = word_num_fullbytes;
579  *word_start_ret = word_start;
580  *word_step_ret = word_step;
581  *word_last_ret = word_last;
582  *byte_start_ret = byte_start;
583  *byte_step_ret = byte_step;
584 }
585 
586 static inline void
587 integer_pack_fill_dd(BDIGIT **dpp, BDIGIT **dep, BDIGIT_DBL *ddp, int *numbits_in_dd_p)
588 {
589  if (*dpp < *dep && BITSPERDIG <= (int)sizeof(*ddp) * CHAR_BIT - *numbits_in_dd_p) {
590  *ddp |= (BDIGIT_DBL)(*(*dpp)++) << *numbits_in_dd_p;
591  *numbits_in_dd_p += BITSPERDIG;
592  }
593  else if (*dpp == *dep) {
594  /* higher bits are infinity zeros */
595  *numbits_in_dd_p = (int)sizeof(*ddp) * CHAR_BIT;
596  }
597 }
598 
599 static inline BDIGIT_DBL
600 integer_pack_take_lowbits(int n, BDIGIT_DBL *ddp, int *numbits_in_dd_p)
601 {
602  BDIGIT_DBL ret;
603  ret = (*ddp) & (((BDIGIT_DBL)1 << n) - 1);
604  *ddp >>= n;
605  *numbits_in_dd_p -= n;
606  return ret;
607 }
608 
609 #if !defined(WORDS_BIGENDIAN)
610 static int
611 bytes_2comp(unsigned char *buf, size_t len)
612 {
613  size_t i;
614  for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
615  buf[i] = ~buf[i];
616  for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
617  buf[i]++;
618  if (buf[i] != 0)
619  return 0;
620  }
621  return 1;
622 }
623 #endif
624 
625 static int
626 bary_pack(int sign, BDIGIT *ds, size_t num_bdigits, void *words, size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int flags)
627 {
628  BDIGIT *dp, *de;
629  unsigned char *buf, *bufend;
630 
631  dp = ds;
632  de = ds + num_bdigits;
633 
634  validate_integer_pack_format(numwords, wordsize, nails, flags,
635  INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST|
636  INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST|
637  INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST|
638  INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST|
639  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER|
640  INTEGER_PACK_2COMP|
641  INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_GENERIC_IMPLEMENTATION);
642 
643  while (dp < de && de[-1] == 0)
644  de--;
645  if (dp == de) {
646  sign = 0;
647  }
648 
649  if (!(flags & INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_GENERIC_IMPLEMENTATION)) {
650  if (sign == 0) {
651  MEMZERO(words, unsigned char, numwords * wordsize);
652  return 0;
653  }
654  if (nails == 0 && numwords == 1) {
655  int need_swap = wordsize != 1 &&
656  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_BYTEORDER_MASK) != INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER &&
657  ((flags & INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST) ? !HOST_BIGENDIAN_P : HOST_BIGENDIAN_P);
658  if (0 < sign || !(flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP)) {
659  BDIGIT d;
660  if (wordsize == 1) {
661  *((unsigned char *)words) = (unsigned char)(d = dp[0]);
662  return ((1 < de - dp || CLEAR_LOWBITS(d, 8) != 0) ? 2 : 1) * sign;
663  }
664 #if defined(HAVE_UINT16_T) && 2 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
665  if (wordsize == 2 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint16_t) == 0) {
666  uint16_t u = (uint16_t)(d = dp[0]);
667  if (need_swap) u = swap16(u);
668  *((uint16_t *)words) = u;
669  return ((1 < de - dp || CLEAR_LOWBITS(d, 16) != 0) ? 2 : 1) * sign;
670  }
671 #endif
672 #if defined(HAVE_UINT32_T) && 4 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
673  if (wordsize == 4 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint32_t) == 0) {
674  uint32_t u = (uint32_t)(d = dp[0]);
675  if (need_swap) u = swap32(u);
676  *((uint32_t *)words) = u;
677  return ((1 < de - dp || CLEAR_LOWBITS(d, 32) != 0) ? 2 : 1) * sign;
678  }
679 #endif
680 #if defined(HAVE_UINT64_T) && 8 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
681  if (wordsize == 8 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint64_t) == 0) {
682  uint64_t u = (uint64_t)(d = dp[0]);
683  if (need_swap) u = swap64(u);
684  *((uint64_t *)words) = u;
685  return ((1 < de - dp || CLEAR_LOWBITS(d, 64) != 0) ? 2 : 1) * sign;
686  }
687 #endif
688  }
689  else { /* sign < 0 && (flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP) */
690  BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED d;
691  if (wordsize == 1) {
692  *((unsigned char *)words) = (unsigned char)(d = -(BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)dp[0]);
693  return (1 < de - dp || FILL_LOWBITS(d, 8) != -1) ? -2 : -1;
694  }
695 #if defined(HAVE_UINT16_T) && 2 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
696  if (wordsize == 2 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint16_t) == 0) {
697  uint16_t u = (uint16_t)(d = -(BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)dp[0]);
698  if (need_swap) u = swap16(u);
699  *((uint16_t *)words) = u;
700  return (wordsize == SIZEOF_BDIGIT && de - dp == 2 && dp[1] == 1 && dp[0] == 0) ? -1 :
701  (1 < de - dp || FILL_LOWBITS(d, 16) != -1) ? -2 : -1;
702  }
703 #endif
704 #if defined(HAVE_UINT32_T) && 4 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
705  if (wordsize == 4 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint32_t) == 0) {
706  uint32_t u = (uint32_t)(d = -(BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)dp[0]);
707  if (need_swap) u = swap32(u);
708  *((uint32_t *)words) = u;
709  return (wordsize == SIZEOF_BDIGIT && de - dp == 2 && dp[1] == 1 && dp[0] == 0) ? -1 :
710  (1 < de - dp || FILL_LOWBITS(d, 32) != -1) ? -2 : -1;
711  }
712 #endif
713 #if defined(HAVE_UINT64_T) && 8 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
714  if (wordsize == 8 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint64_t) == 0) {
715  uint64_t u = (uint64_t)(d = -(BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)dp[0]);
716  if (need_swap) u = swap64(u);
717  *((uint64_t *)words) = u;
718  return (wordsize == SIZEOF_BDIGIT && de - dp == 2 && dp[1] == 1 && dp[0] == 0) ? -1 :
719  (1 < de - dp || FILL_LOWBITS(d, 64) != -1) ? -2 : -1;
720  }
721 #endif
722  }
723  }
724 #if !defined(WORDS_BIGENDIAN)
725  if (nails == 0 && SIZEOF_BDIGIT == sizeof(BDIGIT) &&
726  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_WORDORDER_MASK) == INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST &&
727  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_BYTEORDER_MASK) != INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST) {
728  size_t src_size = (de - dp) * SIZEOF_BDIGIT;
729  size_t dst_size = numwords * wordsize;
730  int overflow = 0;
731  while (0 < src_size && ((unsigned char *)ds)[src_size-1] == 0)
732  src_size--;
733  if (src_size <= dst_size) {
734  MEMCPY(words, dp, char, src_size);
735  MEMZERO((char*)words + src_size, char, dst_size - src_size);
736  }
737  else {
738  MEMCPY(words, dp, char, dst_size);
739  overflow = 1;
740  }
741  if (sign < 0 && (flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP)) {
742  int zero_p = bytes_2comp(words, dst_size);
743  if (zero_p && overflow) {
744  unsigned char *p = (unsigned char *)dp;
745  if (dst_size == src_size-1 &&
746  p[dst_size] == 1) {
747  overflow = 0;
748  }
749  }
750  }
751  if (overflow)
752  sign *= 2;
753  return sign;
754  }
755 #endif
756  if (nails == 0 && SIZEOF_BDIGIT == sizeof(BDIGIT) &&
757  wordsize % SIZEOF_BDIGIT == 0 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(BDIGIT) == 0) {
758  size_t bdigits_per_word = wordsize / SIZEOF_BDIGIT;
759  size_t src_num_bdigits = de - dp;
760  size_t dst_num_bdigits = numwords * bdigits_per_word;
761  int overflow = 0;
762  int mswordfirst_p = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST) != 0;
763  int msbytefirst_p = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER) ? HOST_BIGENDIAN_P :
764  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST) != 0;
765  if (src_num_bdigits <= dst_num_bdigits) {
766  MEMCPY(words, dp, BDIGIT, src_num_bdigits);
767  BDIGITS_ZERO((BDIGIT*)words + src_num_bdigits, dst_num_bdigits - src_num_bdigits);
768  }
769  else {
770  MEMCPY(words, dp, BDIGIT, dst_num_bdigits);
771  overflow = 1;
772  }
773  if (sign < 0 && (flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP)) {
774  int zero_p = bary_2comp(words, dst_num_bdigits);
775  if (zero_p && overflow &&
776  dst_num_bdigits == src_num_bdigits-1 &&
777  dp[dst_num_bdigits] == 1)
778  overflow = 0;
779  }
780  if (msbytefirst_p != HOST_BIGENDIAN_P) {
781  size_t i;
782  for (i = 0; i < dst_num_bdigits; i++) {
783  BDIGIT d = ((BDIGIT*)words)[i];
784  ((BDIGIT*)words)[i] = swap_bdigit(d);
785  }
786  }
787  if (mswordfirst_p ? !msbytefirst_p : msbytefirst_p) {
788  size_t i;
789  BDIGIT *p = words;
790  for (i = 0; i < numwords; i++) {
791  bary_swap(p, bdigits_per_word);
792  p += bdigits_per_word;
793  }
794  }
795  if (mswordfirst_p) {
796  bary_swap(words, dst_num_bdigits);
797  }
798  if (overflow)
799  sign *= 2;
800  return sign;
801  }
802  }
803 
804  buf = words;
805  bufend = buf + numwords * wordsize;
806 
807  if (buf == bufend) {
808  /* overflow if non-zero*/
809  if (!(flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP) || 0 <= sign)
810  sign *= 2;
811  else {
812  if (de - dp == 1 && dp[0] == 1)
813  sign = -1; /* val == -1 == -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) */
814  else
815  sign = -2; /* val < -1 == -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) */
816  }
817  }
818  else if (dp == de) {
819  memset(buf, '\0', bufend - buf);
820  }
821  else if (dp < de && buf < bufend) {
822  int word_num_partialbits;
823  size_t word_num_fullbytes;
824 
825  ssize_t word_step;
826  size_t byte_start;
827  int byte_step;
828 
829  size_t word_start, word_last;
830  unsigned char *wordp, *last_wordp;
831  BDIGIT_DBL dd;
832  int numbits_in_dd;
833 
834  integer_pack_loop_setup(numwords, wordsize, nails, flags,
835  &word_num_fullbytes, &word_num_partialbits,
836  &word_start, &word_step, &word_last, &byte_start, &byte_step);
837 
838  wordp = buf + word_start;
839  last_wordp = buf + word_last;
840 
841  dd = 0;
842  numbits_in_dd = 0;
843 
844 #define FILL_DD \
845  integer_pack_fill_dd(&dp, &de, &dd, &numbits_in_dd)
846 #define TAKE_LOWBITS(n) \
847  integer_pack_take_lowbits(n, &dd, &numbits_in_dd)
848 
849  while (1) {
850  size_t index_in_word = 0;
851  unsigned char *bytep = wordp + byte_start;
852  while (index_in_word < word_num_fullbytes) {
853  FILL_DD;
854  *bytep = TAKE_LOWBITS(CHAR_BIT);
855  bytep += byte_step;
856  index_in_word++;
857  }
858  if (word_num_partialbits) {
859  FILL_DD;
860  *bytep = TAKE_LOWBITS(word_num_partialbits);
861  bytep += byte_step;
862  index_in_word++;
863  }
864  while (index_in_word < wordsize) {
865  *bytep = 0;
866  bytep += byte_step;
867  index_in_word++;
868  }
869 
870  if (wordp == last_wordp)
871  break;
872 
873  wordp += word_step;
874  }
875  FILL_DD;
876  /* overflow tests */
877  if (dp != de || 1 < dd) {
878  /* 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)+1) <= abs(val) */
879  sign *= 2;
880  }
881  else if (dd == 1) {
882  /* 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) <= abs(val) < 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)+1) */
883  if (!(flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP) || 0 <= sign)
884  sign *= 2;
885  else { /* overflow_2comp && sign == -1 */
886  /* test lower bits are all zero. */
887  dp = ds;
888  while (dp < de && *dp == 0)
889  dp++;
890  if (de - dp == 1 && /* only one non-zero word. */
891  POW2_P(*dp)) /* *dp contains only one bit set. */
892  sign = -1; /* val == -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) */
893  else
894  sign = -2; /* val < -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) */
895  }
896  }
897  }
898 
899  if ((flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP) && (sign < 0 && numwords != 0)) {
900  unsigned char *buf;
901 
902  int word_num_partialbits;
903  size_t word_num_fullbytes;
904 
905  ssize_t word_step;
906  size_t byte_start;
907  int byte_step;
908 
909  size_t word_start, word_last;
910  unsigned char *wordp, *last_wordp;
911 
912  unsigned int partialbits_mask;
913  int carry;
914 
915  integer_pack_loop_setup(numwords, wordsize, nails, flags,
916  &word_num_fullbytes, &word_num_partialbits,
917  &word_start, &word_step, &word_last, &byte_start, &byte_step);
918 
919  partialbits_mask = (1 << word_num_partialbits) - 1;
920 
921  buf = words;
922  wordp = buf + word_start;
923  last_wordp = buf + word_last;
924 
925  carry = 1;
926  while (1) {
927  size_t index_in_word = 0;
928  unsigned char *bytep = wordp + byte_start;
929  while (index_in_word < word_num_fullbytes) {
930  carry += (unsigned char)~*bytep;
931  *bytep = (unsigned char)carry;
932  carry >>= CHAR_BIT;
933  bytep += byte_step;
934  index_in_word++;
935  }
936  if (word_num_partialbits) {
937  carry += (*bytep & partialbits_mask) ^ partialbits_mask;
938  *bytep = carry & partialbits_mask;
939  carry >>= word_num_partialbits;
940  bytep += byte_step;
941  index_in_word++;
942  }
943 
944  if (wordp == last_wordp)
945  break;
946 
947  wordp += word_step;
948  }
949  }
950 
951  return sign;
952 #undef FILL_DD
953 #undef TAKE_LOWBITS
954 }
955 
956 static size_t
957 integer_unpack_num_bdigits_small(size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int *nlp_bits_ret)
958 {
959  /* nlp_bits stands for number of leading padding bits */
960  size_t num_bits = (wordsize * CHAR_BIT - nails) * numwords;
961  size_t num_bdigits = (num_bits + BITSPERDIG - 1) / BITSPERDIG;
962  *nlp_bits_ret = (int)(num_bdigits * BITSPERDIG - num_bits);
963  return num_bdigits;
964 }
965 
966 static size_t
967 integer_unpack_num_bdigits_generic(size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int *nlp_bits_ret)
968 {
969  /* BITSPERDIG = SIZEOF_BDIGIT * CHAR_BIT */
970  /* num_bits = (wordsize * CHAR_BIT - nails) * numwords */
971  /* num_bdigits = (num_bits + BITSPERDIG - 1) / BITSPERDIG */
972 
973  /* num_bits = CHAR_BIT * (wordsize * numwords) - nails * numwords = CHAR_BIT * num_bytes1 - nails * numwords */
974  size_t num_bytes1 = wordsize * numwords;
975 
976  /* q1 * CHAR_BIT + r1 = numwords */
977  size_t q1 = numwords / CHAR_BIT;
978  size_t r1 = numwords % CHAR_BIT;
979 
980  /* num_bits = CHAR_BIT * num_bytes1 - nails * (q1 * CHAR_BIT + r1) = CHAR_BIT * num_bytes2 - nails * r1 */
981  size_t num_bytes2 = num_bytes1 - nails * q1;
982 
983  /* q2 * CHAR_BIT + r2 = nails */
984  size_t q2 = nails / CHAR_BIT;
985  size_t r2 = nails % CHAR_BIT;
986 
987  /* num_bits = CHAR_BIT * num_bytes2 - (q2 * CHAR_BIT + r2) * r1 = CHAR_BIT * num_bytes3 - r1 * r2 */
988  size_t num_bytes3 = num_bytes2 - q2 * r1;
989 
990  /* q3 * BITSPERDIG + r3 = num_bytes3 */
991  size_t q3 = num_bytes3 / BITSPERDIG;
992  size_t r3 = num_bytes3 % BITSPERDIG;
993 
994  /* num_bits = CHAR_BIT * (q3 * BITSPERDIG + r3) - r1 * r2 = BITSPERDIG * num_digits1 + CHAR_BIT * r3 - r1 * r2 */
995  size_t num_digits1 = CHAR_BIT * q3;
996 
997  /*
998  * if CHAR_BIT * r3 >= r1 * r2
999  * CHAR_BIT * r3 - r1 * r2 = CHAR_BIT * BITSPERDIG - (CHAR_BIT * BITSPERDIG - (CHAR_BIT * r3 - r1 * r2))
1000  * q4 * BITSPERDIG + r4 = CHAR_BIT * BITSPERDIG - (CHAR_BIT * r3 - r1 * r2)
1001  * num_bits = BITSPERDIG * num_digits1 + CHAR_BIT * BITSPERDIG - (q4 * BITSPERDIG + r4) = BITSPERDIG * num_digits2 - r4
1002  * else
1003  * q4 * BITSPERDIG + r4 = -(CHAR_BIT * r3 - r1 * r2)
1004  * num_bits = BITSPERDIG * num_digits1 - (q4 * BITSPERDIG + r4) = BITSPERDIG * num_digits2 - r4
1005  * end
1006  */
1007 
1008  if (CHAR_BIT * r3 >= r1 * r2) {
1009  size_t tmp1 = CHAR_BIT * BITSPERDIG - (CHAR_BIT * r3 - r1 * r2);
1010  size_t q4 = tmp1 / BITSPERDIG;
1011  int r4 = (int)(tmp1 % BITSPERDIG);
1012  size_t num_digits2 = num_digits1 + CHAR_BIT - q4;
1013  *nlp_bits_ret = r4;
1014  return num_digits2;
1015  }
1016  else {
1017  size_t tmp1 = r1 * r2 - CHAR_BIT * r3;
1018  size_t q4 = tmp1 / BITSPERDIG;
1019  int r4 = (int)(tmp1 % BITSPERDIG);
1020  size_t num_digits2 = num_digits1 - q4;
1021  *nlp_bits_ret = r4;
1022  return num_digits2;
1023  }
1024 }
1025 
1026 static size_t
1027 integer_unpack_num_bdigits(size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int *nlp_bits_ret)
1028 {
1029  size_t num_bdigits;
1030 
1031  if (numwords <= (SIZE_MAX - (BITSPERDIG-1)) / CHAR_BIT / wordsize) {
1032  num_bdigits = integer_unpack_num_bdigits_small(numwords, wordsize, nails, nlp_bits_ret);
1033 #ifdef DEBUG_INTEGER_PACK
1034  {
1035  int nlp_bits1;
1036  size_t num_bdigits1 = integer_unpack_num_bdigits_generic(numwords, wordsize, nails, &nlp_bits1);
1037  assert(num_bdigits == num_bdigits1);
1038  assert(*nlp_bits_ret == nlp_bits1);
1039  }
1040 #endif
1041  }
1042  else {
1043  num_bdigits = integer_unpack_num_bdigits_generic(numwords, wordsize, nails, nlp_bits_ret);
1044  }
1045  return num_bdigits;
1046 }
1047 
1048 static inline void
1049 integer_unpack_push_bits(int data, int numbits, BDIGIT_DBL *ddp, int *numbits_in_dd_p, BDIGIT **dpp)
1050 {
1051  (*ddp) |= ((BDIGIT_DBL)data) << (*numbits_in_dd_p);
1052  *numbits_in_dd_p += numbits;
1053  while (BITSPERDIG <= *numbits_in_dd_p) {
1054  *(*dpp)++ = BIGLO(*ddp);
1055  *ddp = BIGDN(*ddp);
1056  *numbits_in_dd_p -= BITSPERDIG;
1057  }
1058 }
1059 
1060 static int
1061 integer_unpack_single_bdigit(BDIGIT u, size_t size, int flags, BDIGIT *dp)
1062 {
1063  int sign;
1064  if (flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP) {
1065  sign = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) ?
1066  ((size == SIZEOF_BDIGIT && u == 0) ? -2 : -1) :
1067  ((u >> (size * CHAR_BIT - 1)) ? -1 : 1);
1068  if (sign < 0) {
1069  u |= LSHIFTX(BDIGMAX, size * CHAR_BIT);
1070  u = BIGLO(1 + ~u);
1071  }
1072  }
1073  else
1074  sign = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) ? -1 : 1;
1075  *dp = u;
1076  return sign;
1077 }
1078 
1079 static int
1080 bary_unpack_internal(BDIGIT *bdigits, size_t num_bdigits, const void *words, size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int flags, int nlp_bits)
1081 {
1082  int sign;
1083  const unsigned char *buf = words;
1084  BDIGIT *dp;
1085  BDIGIT *de;
1086 
1087  dp = bdigits;
1088  de = dp + num_bdigits;
1089 
1090  if (!(flags & INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_GENERIC_IMPLEMENTATION)) {
1091  if (nails == 0 && numwords == 1) {
1092  int need_swap = wordsize != 1 &&
1093  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_BYTEORDER_MASK) != INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER &&
1094  ((flags & INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST) ? !HOST_BIGENDIAN_P : HOST_BIGENDIAN_P);
1095  if (wordsize == 1) {
1096  return integer_unpack_single_bdigit(*(uint8_t *)buf, sizeof(uint8_t), flags, dp);
1097  }
1098 #if defined(HAVE_UINT16_T) && 2 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
1099  if (wordsize == 2 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint16_t) == 0) {
1100  uint16_t u = *(uint16_t *)buf;
1101  return integer_unpack_single_bdigit(need_swap ? swap16(u) : u, sizeof(uint16_t), flags, dp);
1102  }
1103 #endif
1104 #if defined(HAVE_UINT32_T) && 4 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
1105  if (wordsize == 4 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint32_t) == 0) {
1106  uint32_t u = *(uint32_t *)buf;
1107  return integer_unpack_single_bdigit(need_swap ? swap32(u) : u, sizeof(uint32_t), flags, dp);
1108  }
1109 #endif
1110 #if defined(HAVE_UINT64_T) && 8 <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
1111  if (wordsize == 8 && (uintptr_t)words % ALIGNOF(uint64_t) == 0) {
1112  uint64_t u = *(uint64_t *)buf;
1113  return integer_unpack_single_bdigit(need_swap ? swap64(u) : u, sizeof(uint64_t), flags, dp);
1114  }
1115 #endif
1116  }
1117 #if !defined(WORDS_BIGENDIAN)
1118  if (nails == 0 && SIZEOF_BDIGIT == sizeof(BDIGIT) &&
1119  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_WORDORDER_MASK) == INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST &&
1120  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_BYTEORDER_MASK) != INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST) {
1121  size_t src_size = numwords * wordsize;
1122  size_t dst_size = num_bdigits * SIZEOF_BDIGIT;
1123  MEMCPY(dp, words, char, src_size);
1124  if (flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP) {
1125  if (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) {
1126  int zero_p;
1127  memset((char*)dp + src_size, 0xff, dst_size - src_size);
1128  zero_p = bary_2comp(dp, num_bdigits);
1129  sign = zero_p ? -2 : -1;
1130  }
1131  else if (buf[src_size-1] >> (CHAR_BIT-1)) {
1132  memset((char*)dp + src_size, 0xff, dst_size - src_size);
1133  bary_2comp(dp, num_bdigits);
1134  sign = -1;
1135  }
1136  else {
1137  MEMZERO((char*)dp + src_size, char, dst_size - src_size);
1138  sign = 1;
1139  }
1140  }
1141  else {
1142  MEMZERO((char*)dp + src_size, char, dst_size - src_size);
1143  sign = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) ? -1 : 1;
1144  }
1145  return sign;
1146  }
1147 #endif
1148  if (nails == 0 && SIZEOF_BDIGIT == sizeof(BDIGIT) &&
1149  wordsize % SIZEOF_BDIGIT == 0) {
1150  size_t bdigits_per_word = wordsize / SIZEOF_BDIGIT;
1151  int mswordfirst_p = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST) != 0;
1152  int msbytefirst_p = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER) ? HOST_BIGENDIAN_P :
1153  (flags & INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST) != 0;
1154  MEMCPY(dp, words, BDIGIT, numwords*bdigits_per_word);
1155  if (mswordfirst_p) {
1156  bary_swap(dp, num_bdigits);
1157  }
1158  if (mswordfirst_p ? !msbytefirst_p : msbytefirst_p) {
1159  size_t i;
1160  BDIGIT *p = dp;
1161  for (i = 0; i < numwords; i++) {
1162  bary_swap(p, bdigits_per_word);
1163  p += bdigits_per_word;
1164  }
1165  }
1166  if (msbytefirst_p != HOST_BIGENDIAN_P) {
1167  BDIGIT *p;
1168  for (p = dp; p < de; p++) {
1169  BDIGIT d = *p;
1170  *p = swap_bdigit(d);
1171  }
1172  }
1173  if (flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP) {
1174  if (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) {
1175  int zero_p = bary_2comp(dp, num_bdigits);
1176  sign = zero_p ? -2 : -1;
1177  }
1178  else if (BDIGIT_MSB(de[-1])) {
1179  bary_2comp(dp, num_bdigits);
1180  sign = -1;
1181  }
1182  else {
1183  sign = 1;
1184  }
1185  }
1186  else {
1187  sign = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) ? -1 : 1;
1188  }
1189  return sign;
1190  }
1191  }
1192 
1193  if (num_bdigits != 0) {
1194  int word_num_partialbits;
1195  size_t word_num_fullbytes;
1196 
1197  ssize_t word_step;
1198  size_t byte_start;
1199  int byte_step;
1200 
1201  size_t word_start, word_last;
1202  const unsigned char *wordp, *last_wordp;
1203  BDIGIT_DBL dd;
1204  int numbits_in_dd;
1205 
1206  integer_pack_loop_setup(numwords, wordsize, nails, flags,
1207  &word_num_fullbytes, &word_num_partialbits,
1208  &word_start, &word_step, &word_last, &byte_start, &byte_step);
1209 
1210  wordp = buf + word_start;
1211  last_wordp = buf + word_last;
1212 
1213  dd = 0;
1214  numbits_in_dd = 0;
1215 
1216 #define PUSH_BITS(data, numbits) \
1217  integer_unpack_push_bits(data, numbits, &dd, &numbits_in_dd, &dp)
1218 
1219  while (1) {
1220  size_t index_in_word = 0;
1221  const unsigned char *bytep = wordp + byte_start;
1222  while (index_in_word < word_num_fullbytes) {
1223  PUSH_BITS(*bytep, CHAR_BIT);
1224  bytep += byte_step;
1225  index_in_word++;
1226  }
1227  if (word_num_partialbits) {
1228  PUSH_BITS(*bytep & ((1 << word_num_partialbits) - 1), word_num_partialbits);
1229  bytep += byte_step;
1230  index_in_word++;
1231  }
1232 
1233  if (wordp == last_wordp)
1234  break;
1235 
1236  wordp += word_step;
1237  }
1238  if (dd)
1239  *dp++ = (BDIGIT)dd;
1240  assert(dp <= de);
1241  while (dp < de)
1242  *dp++ = 0;
1243 #undef PUSH_BITS
1244  }
1245 
1246  if (!(flags & INTEGER_PACK_2COMP)) {
1247  sign = (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) ? -1 : 1;
1248  }
1249  else {
1250  if (nlp_bits) {
1251  if ((flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) ||
1252  (bdigits[num_bdigits-1] >> (BITSPERDIG - nlp_bits - 1))) {
1253  bdigits[num_bdigits-1] |= BIGLO(BDIGMAX << (BITSPERDIG - nlp_bits));
1254  sign = -1;
1255  }
1256  else {
1257  sign = 1;
1258  }
1259  }
1260  else {
1261  if (flags & INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE) {
1262  sign = bary_zero_p(bdigits, num_bdigits) ? -2 : -1;
1263  }
1264  else {
1265  if (num_bdigits != 0 && BDIGIT_MSB(bdigits[num_bdigits-1]))
1266  sign = -1;
1267  else
1268  sign = 1;
1269  }
1270  }
1271  if (sign == -1 && num_bdigits != 0) {
1272  bary_2comp(bdigits, num_bdigits);
1273  }
1274  }
1275 
1276  return sign;
1277 }
1278 
1279 static void
1280 bary_unpack(BDIGIT *bdigits, size_t num_bdigits, const void *words, size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int flags)
1281 {
1282  size_t num_bdigits0;
1283  int nlp_bits;
1284  int sign;
1285 
1286  validate_integer_pack_format(numwords, wordsize, nails, flags,
1287  INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST|
1288  INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST|
1289  INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST|
1290  INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST|
1291  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER|
1292  INTEGER_PACK_2COMP|
1293  INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_BIGNUM|
1294  INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE|
1295  INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_GENERIC_IMPLEMENTATION);
1296 
1297  num_bdigits0 = integer_unpack_num_bdigits(numwords, wordsize, nails, &nlp_bits);
1298 
1299  assert(num_bdigits0 <= num_bdigits);
1300 
1301  sign = bary_unpack_internal(bdigits, num_bdigits0, words, numwords, wordsize, nails, flags, nlp_bits);
1302 
1303  if (num_bdigits0 < num_bdigits) {
1304  BDIGITS_ZERO(bdigits + num_bdigits0, num_bdigits - num_bdigits0);
1305  if (sign == -2) {
1306  bdigits[num_bdigits0] = 1;
1307  }
1308  }
1309 }
1310 
1311 static int
1312 bary_subb(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, int borrow)
1313 {
1314  BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED num;
1315  size_t i;
1316  size_t sn;
1317 
1318  assert(xn <= zn);
1319  assert(yn <= zn);
1320 
1321  sn = xn < yn ? xn : yn;
1322 
1323  num = borrow ? -1 : 0;
1324  for (i = 0; i < sn; i++) {
1325  num += (BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)xds[i] - yds[i];
1326  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
1327  num = BIGDN(num);
1328  }
1329  if (yn <= xn) {
1330  for (; i < xn; i++) {
1331  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero;
1332  num += xds[i];
1333  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
1334  num = BIGDN(num);
1335  }
1336  }
1337  else {
1338  for (; i < yn; i++) {
1339  num -= yds[i];
1340  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
1341  num = BIGDN(num);
1342  }
1343  }
1344  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero;
1345  for (; i < zn; i++) {
1346  zds[i] = BDIGMAX;
1347  }
1348  return 1;
1349 
1350  num_is_zero:
1351  if (xds == zds && xn == zn)
1352  return 0;
1353  for (; i < xn; i++) {
1354  zds[i] = xds[i];
1355  }
1356  for (; i < zn; i++) {
1357  zds[i] = 0;
1358  }
1359  return 0;
1360 }
1361 
1362 static int
1363 bary_sub(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
1364 {
1365  return bary_subb(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, 0);
1366 }
1367 
1368 static int
1369 bary_sub_one(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn)
1370 {
1371  return bary_subb(zds, zn, zds, zn, NULL, 0, 1);
1372 }
1373 
1374 static int
1375 bary_addc(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, int carry)
1376 {
1377  BDIGIT_DBL num;
1378  size_t i;
1379 
1380  assert(xn <= zn);
1381  assert(yn <= zn);
1382 
1383  if (xn > yn) {
1384  const BDIGIT *tds;
1385  tds = xds; xds = yds; yds = tds;
1386  i = xn; xn = yn; yn = i;
1387  }
1388 
1389  num = carry ? 1 : 0;
1390  for (i = 0; i < xn; i++) {
1391  num += (BDIGIT_DBL)xds[i] + yds[i];
1392  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
1393  num = BIGDN(num);
1394  }
1395  for (; i < yn; i++) {
1396  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero;
1397  num += yds[i];
1398  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
1399  num = BIGDN(num);
1400  }
1401  for (; i < zn; i++) {
1402  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero;
1403  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
1404  num = BIGDN(num);
1405  }
1406  return num != 0;
1407 
1408  num_is_zero:
1409  if (yds == zds && yn == zn)
1410  return 0;
1411  for (; i < yn; i++) {
1412  zds[i] = yds[i];
1413  }
1414  for (; i < zn; i++) {
1415  zds[i] = 0;
1416  }
1417  return 0;
1418 }
1419 
1420 static int
1421 bary_add(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
1422 {
1423  return bary_addc(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, 0);
1424 }
1425 
1426 static int
1427 bary_add_one(BDIGIT *ds, size_t n)
1428 {
1429  size_t i;
1430  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1431  ds[i] = BIGLO(ds[i]+1);
1432  if (ds[i] != 0)
1433  return 0;
1434  }
1435  return 1;
1436 }
1437 
1438 static void
1439 bary_mul_single(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, BDIGIT x, BDIGIT y)
1440 {
1441  BDIGIT_DBL n;
1442 
1443  assert(2 <= zn);
1444 
1445  n = (BDIGIT_DBL)x * y;
1446  bdigitdbl2bary(zds, 2, n);
1447  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds + 2, zn - 2);
1448 }
1449 
1450 static int
1451 bary_muladd_1xN(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, BDIGIT x, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
1452 {
1453  BDIGIT_DBL n;
1454  BDIGIT_DBL dd;
1455  size_t j;
1456 
1457  assert(zn > yn);
1458 
1459  if (x == 0)
1460  return 0;
1461  dd = x;
1462  n = 0;
1463  for (j = 0; j < yn; j++) {
1464  BDIGIT_DBL ee = n + dd * yds[j];
1465  if (ee) {
1466  n = zds[j] + ee;
1467  zds[j] = BIGLO(n);
1468  n = BIGDN(n);
1469  }
1470  else {
1471  n = 0;
1472  }
1473 
1474  }
1475  for (; j < zn; j++) {
1476  if (n == 0)
1477  break;
1478  n += zds[j];
1479  zds[j] = BIGLO(n);
1480  n = BIGDN(n);
1481  }
1482  return n != 0;
1483 }
1484 
1485 static BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED
1486 bigdivrem_mulsub(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, BDIGIT x, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
1487 {
1488  size_t i;
1489  BDIGIT_DBL t2;
1490  BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED num;
1491 
1492  assert(zn == yn + 1);
1493 
1494  num = 0;
1495  t2 = 0;
1496  i = 0;
1497 
1498  do {
1499  BDIGIT_DBL ee;
1500  t2 += (BDIGIT_DBL)yds[i] * x;
1501  ee = num - BIGLO(t2);
1502  num = (BDIGIT_DBL)zds[i] + ee;
1503  if (ee) zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
1504  num = BIGDN(num);
1505  t2 = BIGDN(t2);
1506  } while (++i < yn);
1507  num += zds[i] - t2; /* borrow from high digit; don't update */
1508  return num;
1509 }
1510 
1511 static int
1512 bary_mulsub_1xN(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, BDIGIT x, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
1513 {
1514  BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED num;
1515 
1516  assert(zn == yn + 1);
1517 
1518  num = bigdivrem_mulsub(zds, zn, x, yds, yn);
1519  zds[yn] = BIGLO(num);
1520  if (BIGDN(num))
1521  return 1;
1522  return 0;
1523 }
1524 
1525 static void
1526 bary_mul_normal(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
1527 {
1528  size_t i;
1529 
1530  assert(xn + yn <= zn);
1531 
1532  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds, zn);
1533  for (i = 0; i < xn; i++) {
1534  bary_muladd_1xN(zds+i, zn-i, xds[i], yds, yn);
1535  }
1536 }
1537 
1538 VALUE
1539 rb_big_mul_normal(VALUE x, VALUE y)
1540 {
1541  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y), zn = xn + yn;
1542  VALUE z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
1543  bary_mul_normal(BDIGITS(z), zn, BDIGITS(x), xn, BDIGITS(y), yn);
1544  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
1545  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
1546  return z;
1547 }
1548 
1549 /* efficient squaring (2 times faster than normal multiplication)
1550  * ref: Handbook of Applied Cryptography, Algorithm 14.16
1551  * http://www.cacr.math.uwaterloo.ca/hac/about/chap14.pdf
1552  */
1553 static void
1554 bary_sq_fast(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn)
1555 {
1556  size_t i, j;
1557  BDIGIT_DBL c, v, w;
1558  BDIGIT vl;
1559  int vh;
1560 
1561  assert(xn * 2 <= zn);
1562 
1563  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds, zn);
1564 
1565  if (xn == 0)
1566  return;
1567 
1568  for (i = 0; i < xn-1; i++) {
1569  v = (BDIGIT_DBL)xds[i];
1570  if (!v)
1571  continue;
1572  c = (BDIGIT_DBL)zds[i + i] + v * v;
1573  zds[i + i] = BIGLO(c);
1574  c = BIGDN(c);
1575  v *= 2;
1576  vl = BIGLO(v);
1577  vh = (int)BIGDN(v);
1578  for (j = i + 1; j < xn; j++) {
1579  w = (BDIGIT_DBL)xds[j];
1580  c += (BDIGIT_DBL)zds[i + j] + vl * w;
1581  zds[i + j] = BIGLO(c);
1582  c = BIGDN(c);
1583  if (vh)
1584  c += w;
1585  }
1586  if (c) {
1587  c += (BDIGIT_DBL)zds[i + xn];
1588  zds[i + xn] = BIGLO(c);
1589  c = BIGDN(c);
1590  if (c)
1591  zds[i + xn + 1] += (BDIGIT)c;
1592  }
1593  }
1594 
1595  /* i == xn-1 */
1596  v = (BDIGIT_DBL)xds[i];
1597  if (!v)
1598  return;
1599  c = (BDIGIT_DBL)zds[i + i] + v * v;
1600  zds[i + i] = BIGLO(c);
1601  c = BIGDN(c);
1602  if (c) {
1603  zds[i + xn] += BIGLO(c);
1604  }
1605 }
1606 
1607 VALUE
1608 rb_big_sq_fast(VALUE x)
1609 {
1610  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), zn = 2 * xn;
1611  VALUE z = bignew(zn, 1);
1612  bary_sq_fast(BDIGITS(z), zn, BDIGITS(x), xn);
1613  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
1614  return z;
1615 }
1616 
1617 /* balancing multiplication by slicing larger argument */
1618 static void
1619 bary_mul_balance_with_mulfunc(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, BDIGIT *wds, size_t wn, mulfunc_t *mulfunc)
1620 {
1621  VALUE work = 0;
1622  size_t yn0 = yn;
1623  size_t r, n;
1624 
1625  assert(xn + yn <= zn);
1626  assert(xn <= yn);
1627  assert(!KARATSUBA_BALANCED(xn, yn) || !TOOM3_BALANCED(xn, yn));
1628 
1629  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds, xn);
1630 
1631  n = 0;
1632  while (yn > 0) {
1633  BDIGIT *tds;
1634  size_t tn;
1635  r = xn > yn ? yn : xn;
1636  tn = xn + r;
1637  if (2 * (xn + r) <= zn - n) {
1638  tds = zds + n + xn + r;
1639  mulfunc(tds, tn, xds, xn, yds + n, r, wds, wn);
1640  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds + n + xn, r);
1641  bary_add(zds + n, tn,
1642  zds + n, tn,
1643  tds, tn);
1644  }
1645  else {
1646  if (wn < xn) {
1647  wn = xn;
1648  wds = ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, work, wn);
1649  }
1650  tds = zds + n;
1651  MEMCPY(wds, zds + n, BDIGIT, xn);
1652  mulfunc(tds, tn, xds, xn, yds + n, r, wds+xn, wn-xn);
1653  bary_add(zds + n, tn,
1654  zds + n, tn,
1655  wds, xn);
1656  }
1657  yn -= r;
1658  n += r;
1659  }
1660  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds+xn+yn0, zn - (xn+yn0));
1661 
1662  if (work)
1663  ALLOCV_END(work);
1664 }
1665 
1666 VALUE
1667 rb_big_mul_balance(VALUE x, VALUE y)
1668 {
1669  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y), zn = xn + yn;
1670  VALUE z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
1671  bary_mul_balance_with_mulfunc(BDIGITS(z), zn, BDIGITS(x), xn, BDIGITS(y), yn, NULL, 0, bary_mul_toom3_start);
1672  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
1673  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
1674  return z;
1675 }
1676 
1677 /* multiplication by karatsuba method */
1678 static void
1679 bary_mul_karatsuba(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, BDIGIT *wds, size_t wn)
1680 {
1681  VALUE work = 0;
1682 
1683  size_t n;
1684  int sub_p, borrow, carry1, carry2, carry3;
1685 
1686  int odd_y = 0;
1687  int odd_xy = 0;
1688  int sq;
1689 
1690  const BDIGIT *xds0, *xds1, *yds0, *yds1;
1691  BDIGIT *zds0, *zds1, *zds2, *zds3;
1692 
1693  assert(xn + yn <= zn);
1694  assert(xn <= yn);
1695  assert(yn < 2 * xn);
1696 
1697  sq = xds == yds && xn == yn;
1698 
1699  if (yn & 1) {
1700  odd_y = 1;
1701  yn--;
1702  if (yn < xn) {
1703  odd_xy = 1;
1704  xn--;
1705  }
1706  }
1707 
1708  n = yn / 2;
1709 
1710  assert(n < xn);
1711 
1712  if (wn < n) {
1713  /* This function itself needs only n BDIGITs for work area.
1714  * However this function calls bary_mul_karatsuba and
1715  * bary_mul_balance recursively.
1716  * 2n BDIGITs are enough to avoid allocations in
1717  * the recursively called functions.
1718  */
1719  wn = 2*n;
1720  wds = ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, work, wn);
1721  }
1722 
1723  /* Karatsuba algorithm:
1724  *
1725  * x = x0 + r*x1
1726  * y = y0 + r*y1
1727  * z = x*y
1728  * = (x0 + r*x1) * (y0 + r*y1)
1729  * = x0*y0 + r*(x1*y0 + x0*y1) + r*r*x1*y1
1730  * = x0*y0 + r*(x0*y0 + x1*y1 - (x1-x0)*(y1-y0)) + r*r*x1*y1
1731  * = x0*y0 + r*(x0*y0 + x1*y1 - (x0-x1)*(y0-y1)) + r*r*x1*y1
1732  */
1733 
1734  xds0 = xds;
1735  xds1 = xds + n;
1736  yds0 = yds;
1737  yds1 = yds + n;
1738  zds0 = zds;
1739  zds1 = zds + n;
1740  zds2 = zds + 2*n;
1741  zds3 = zds + 3*n;
1742 
1743  sub_p = 1;
1744 
1745  /* zds0:? zds1:? zds2:? zds3:? wds:? */
1746 
1747  if (bary_sub(zds0, n, xds, n, xds+n, xn-n)) {
1748  bary_2comp(zds0, n);
1749  sub_p = !sub_p;
1750  }
1751 
1752  /* zds0:|x1-x0| zds1:? zds2:? zds3:? wds:? */
1753 
1754  if (sq) {
1755  sub_p = 1;
1756  bary_mul_karatsuba_start(zds1, 2*n, zds0, n, zds0, n, wds, wn);
1757  }
1758  else {
1759  if (bary_sub(wds, n, yds, n, yds+n, n)) {
1760  bary_2comp(wds, n);
1761  sub_p = !sub_p;
1762  }
1763 
1764  /* zds0:|x1-x0| zds1:? zds2:? zds3:? wds:|y1-y0| */
1765 
1766  bary_mul_karatsuba_start(zds1, 2*n, zds0, n, wds, n, wds+n, wn-n);
1767  }
1768 
1769  /* zds0:|x1-x0| zds1,zds2:|x1-x0|*|y1-y0| zds3:? wds:|y1-y0| */
1770 
1771  borrow = 0;
1772  if (sub_p) {
1773  borrow = !bary_2comp(zds1, 2*n);
1774  }
1775  /* zds0:|x1-x0| zds1,zds2:-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0| zds3:? wds:|y1-y0| */
1776 
1777  MEMCPY(wds, zds1, BDIGIT, n);
1778 
1779  /* zds0:|x1-x0| zds1,zds2:-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0| zds3:? wds:lo(-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1780 
1781  bary_mul_karatsuba_start(zds0, 2*n, xds0, n, yds0, n, wds+n, wn-n);
1782 
1783  /* zds0,zds1:x0*y0 zds2:hi(-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) zds3:? wds:lo(-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1784 
1785  carry1 = bary_add(wds, n, wds, n, zds0, n);
1786  carry1 = bary_addc(zds2, n, zds2, n, zds1, n, carry1);
1787 
1788  /* zds0,zds1:x0*y0 zds2:hi(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) zds3:? wds:lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1789 
1790  carry2 = bary_add(zds1, n, zds1, n, wds, n);
1791 
1792  /* zds0:lo(x0*y0) zds1:hi(x0*y0)+lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) zds2:hi(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) zds3:? wds:lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1793 
1794  MEMCPY(wds, zds2, BDIGIT, n);
1795 
1796  /* zds0:lo(x0*y0) zds1:hi(x0*y0)+lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) zds2:_ zds3:? wds:hi(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1797 
1798  bary_mul_karatsuba_start(zds2, zn-2*n, xds1, xn-n, yds1, n, wds+n, wn-n);
1799 
1800  /* zds0:lo(x0*y0) zds1:hi(x0*y0)+lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) zds2,zds3:x1*y1 wds:hi(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1801 
1802  carry3 = bary_add(zds1, n, zds1, n, zds2, n);
1803 
1804  /* zds0:lo(x0*y0) zds1:hi(x0*y0)+lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|)+lo(x1*y1) zds2,zds3:x1*y1 wds:hi(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1805 
1806  carry3 = bary_addc(zds2, n, zds2, n, zds3, (4*n < zn ? n : zn-3*n), carry3);
1807 
1808  /* zds0:lo(x0*y0) zds1:hi(x0*y0)+lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|)+lo(x1*y1) zds2,zds3:x1*y1+hi(x1*y1) wds:hi(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) */
1809 
1810  bary_add(zds2, zn-2*n, zds2, zn-2*n, wds, n);
1811 
1812  /* zds0:lo(x0*y0) zds1:hi(x0*y0)+lo(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|)+lo(x1*y1) zds2,zds3:x1*y1+hi(x1*y1)+hi(x0*y0-?|x1-x0|*|y1-y0|) wds:_ */
1813 
1814  if (carry2)
1815  bary_add_one(zds2, zn-2*n);
1816 
1817  if (carry1 + carry3 - borrow < 0)
1818  bary_sub_one(zds3, zn-3*n);
1819  else if (carry1 + carry3 - borrow > 0) {
1820  BDIGIT c = carry1 + carry3 - borrow;
1821  bary_add(zds3, zn-3*n, zds3, zn-3*n, &c, 1);
1822  }
1823 
1824  /*
1825  if (SIZEOF_BDIGIT * zn <= 16) {
1826  uint128_t z, x, y;
1827  ssize_t i;
1828  for (x = 0, i = xn-1; 0 <= i; i--) { x <<= SIZEOF_BDIGIT*CHAR_BIT; x |= xds[i]; }
1829  for (y = 0, i = yn-1; 0 <= i; i--) { y <<= SIZEOF_BDIGIT*CHAR_BIT; y |= yds[i]; }
1830  for (z = 0, i = zn-1; 0 <= i; i--) { z <<= SIZEOF_BDIGIT*CHAR_BIT; z |= zds[i]; }
1831  assert(z == x * y);
1832  }
1833  */
1834 
1835  if (odd_xy) {
1836  bary_muladd_1xN(zds+yn, zn-yn, yds[yn], xds, xn);
1837  bary_muladd_1xN(zds+xn, zn-xn, xds[xn], yds, yn+1);
1838  }
1839  else if (odd_y) {
1840  bary_muladd_1xN(zds+yn, zn-yn, yds[yn], xds, xn);
1841  }
1842 
1843  if (work)
1844  ALLOCV_END(work);
1845 }
1846 
1847 VALUE
1848 rb_big_mul_karatsuba(VALUE x, VALUE y)
1849 {
1850  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y), zn = xn + yn;
1851  VALUE z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
1852  if (!((xn <= yn && yn < 2) || KARATSUBA_BALANCED(xn, yn)))
1853  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "unexpected bignum length for karatsuba");
1854  bary_mul_karatsuba(BDIGITS(z), zn, BDIGITS(x), xn, BDIGITS(y), yn, NULL, 0);
1855  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
1856  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
1857  return z;
1858 }
1859 
1860 static void
1861 bary_mul_toom3(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, BDIGIT *wds, size_t wn)
1862 {
1863  size_t n;
1864  size_t wnc;
1865  VALUE work = 0;
1866 
1867  /* "p" stands for "positive". Actually it means "non-negative", though. */
1868  size_t x0n; const BDIGIT *x0ds;
1869  size_t x1n; const BDIGIT *x1ds;
1870  size_t x2n; const BDIGIT *x2ds;
1871  size_t y0n; const BDIGIT *y0ds;
1872  size_t y1n; const BDIGIT *y1ds;
1873  size_t y2n; const BDIGIT *y2ds;
1874 
1875  size_t u1n; BDIGIT *u1ds; int u1p;
1876  size_t u2n; BDIGIT *u2ds; int u2p;
1877  size_t u3n; BDIGIT *u3ds; int u3p;
1878 
1879  size_t v1n; BDIGIT *v1ds; int v1p;
1880  size_t v2n; BDIGIT *v2ds; int v2p;
1881  size_t v3n; BDIGIT *v3ds; int v3p;
1882 
1883  size_t t0n; BDIGIT *t0ds; int t0p;
1884  size_t t1n; BDIGIT *t1ds; int t1p;
1885  size_t t2n; BDIGIT *t2ds; int t2p;
1886  size_t t3n; BDIGIT *t3ds; int t3p;
1887  size_t t4n; BDIGIT *t4ds; int t4p;
1888 
1889  size_t z0n; BDIGIT *z0ds;
1890  size_t z1n; BDIGIT *z1ds; int z1p;
1891  size_t z2n; BDIGIT *z2ds; int z2p;
1892  size_t z3n; BDIGIT *z3ds; int z3p;
1893  size_t z4n; BDIGIT *z4ds;
1894 
1895  size_t zzn; BDIGIT *zzds;
1896 
1897  int sq = xds == yds && xn == yn;
1898 
1899  assert(xn <= yn); /* assume y >= x */
1900  assert(xn + yn <= zn);
1901 
1902  n = (yn + 2) / 3;
1903  assert(2*n < xn);
1904 
1905  wnc = 0;
1906 
1907  wnc += (u1n = n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*n+2 bits */
1908  wnc += (u2n = n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*n+1 bits */
1909  wnc += (u3n = n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*n+3 bits */
1910  wnc += (v1n = n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*n+2 bits */
1911  wnc += (v2n = n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*n+1 bits */
1912  wnc += (v3n = n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*n+3 bits */
1913 
1914  wnc += (t0n = 2*n); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n bits */
1915  wnc += (t1n = 2*n+2); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n+4 bits but bary_mul needs u1n+v1n */
1916  wnc += (t2n = 2*n+2); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n+2 bits but bary_mul needs u2n+v2n */
1917  wnc += (t3n = 2*n+2); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n+6 bits but bary_mul needs u3n+v3n */
1918  wnc += (t4n = 2*n); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n bits */
1919 
1920  wnc += (z1n = 2*n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n+5 bits */
1921  wnc += (z2n = 2*n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n+6 bits */
1922  wnc += (z3n = 2*n+1); /* BITSPERDIG*2*n+8 bits */
1923 
1924  if (wn < wnc) {
1925  wn = wnc * 3 / 2; /* Allocate working memory for whole recursion at once. */
1926  wds = ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, work, wn);
1927  }
1928 
1929  u1ds = wds; wds += u1n;
1930  u2ds = wds; wds += u2n;
1931  u3ds = wds; wds += u3n;
1932 
1933  v1ds = wds; wds += v1n;
1934  v2ds = wds; wds += v2n;
1935  v3ds = wds; wds += v3n;
1936 
1937  t0ds = wds; wds += t0n;
1938  t1ds = wds; wds += t1n;
1939  t2ds = wds; wds += t2n;
1940  t3ds = wds; wds += t3n;
1941  t4ds = wds; wds += t4n;
1942 
1943  z1ds = wds; wds += z1n;
1944  z2ds = wds; wds += z2n;
1945  z3ds = wds; wds += z3n;
1946 
1947  wn -= wnc;
1948 
1949  zzds = u1ds;
1950  zzn = 6*n+1;
1951 
1952  x0n = n;
1953  x1n = n;
1954  x2n = xn - 2*n;
1955  x0ds = xds;
1956  x1ds = xds + n;
1957  x2ds = xds + 2*n;
1958 
1959  if (sq) {
1960  y0n = x0n;
1961  y1n = x1n;
1962  y2n = x2n;
1963  y0ds = x0ds;
1964  y1ds = x1ds;
1965  y2ds = x2ds;
1966  }
1967  else {
1968  y0n = n;
1969  y1n = n;
1970  y2n = yn - 2*n;
1971  y0ds = yds;
1972  y1ds = yds + n;
1973  y2ds = yds + 2*n;
1974  }
1975 
1976  /*
1977  * ref. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toom%E2%80%93Cook_multiplication
1978  *
1979  * x(b) = x0 * b^0 + x1 * b^1 + x2 * b^2
1980  * y(b) = y0 * b^0 + y1 * b^1 + y2 * b^2
1981  *
1982  * z(b) = x(b) * y(b)
1983  * z(b) = z0 * b^0 + z1 * b^1 + z2 * b^2 + z3 * b^3 + z4 * b^4
1984  * where:
1985  * z0 = x0 * y0
1986  * z1 = x0 * y1 + x1 * y0
1987  * z2 = x0 * y2 + x1 * y1 + x2 * y0
1988  * z3 = x1 * y2 + x2 * y1
1989  * z4 = x2 * y2
1990  *
1991  * Toom3 method (a.k.a. Toom-Cook method):
1992  * (Step1) calculating 5 points z(b0), z(b1), z(b2), z(b3), z(b4),
1993  * where:
1994  * b0 = 0, b1 = 1, b2 = -1, b3 = -2, b4 = inf,
1995  * z(0) = x(0) * y(0) = x0 * y0
1996  * z(1) = x(1) * y(1) = (x0 + x1 + x2) * (y0 + y1 + y2)
1997  * z(-1) = x(-1) * y(-1) = (x0 - x1 + x2) * (y0 - y1 + y2)
1998  * z(-2) = x(-2) * y(-2) = (x0 - 2 * (x1 - 2 * x2)) * (y0 - 2 * (y1 - 2 * y2))
1999  * z(inf) = x(inf) * y(inf) = x2 * y2
2000  *
2001  * (Step2) interpolating z0, z1, z2, z3 and z4.
2002  *
2003  * (Step3) Substituting base value into b of the polynomial z(b),
2004  */
2005 
2006  /*
2007  * [Step1] calculating 5 points z(b0), z(b1), z(b2), z(b3), z(b4)
2008  */
2009 
2010  /* u1 <- x0 + x2 */
2011  bary_add(u1ds, u1n, x0ds, x0n, x2ds, x2n);
2012  u1p = 1;
2013 
2014  /* x(-1) : u2 <- u1 - x1 = x0 - x1 + x2 */
2015  if (bary_sub(u2ds, u2n, u1ds, u1n, x1ds, x1n)) {
2016  bary_2comp(u2ds, u2n);
2017  u2p = 0;
2018  }
2019  else {
2020  u2p = 1;
2021  }
2022 
2023  /* x(1) : u1 <- u1 + x1 = x0 + x1 + x2 */
2024  bary_add(u1ds, u1n, u1ds, u1n, x1ds, x1n);
2025 
2026  /* x(-2) : u3 <- 2 * (u2 + x2) - x0 = x0 - 2 * (x1 - 2 * x2) */
2027  u3p = 1;
2028  if (u2p) {
2029  bary_add(u3ds, u3n, u2ds, u2n, x2ds, x2n);
2030  }
2031  else if (bary_sub(u3ds, u3n, x2ds, x2n, u2ds, u2n)) {
2032  bary_2comp(u3ds, u3n);
2033  u3p = 0;
2034  }
2035  bary_small_lshift(u3ds, u3ds, u3n, 1);
2036  if (!u3p) {
2037  bary_add(u3ds, u3n, u3ds, u3n, x0ds, x0n);
2038  }
2039  else if (bary_sub(u3ds, u3n, u3ds, u3n, x0ds, x0n)) {
2040  bary_2comp(u3ds, u3n);
2041  u3p = 0;
2042  }
2043 
2044  if (sq) {
2045  v1n = u1n; v1ds = u1ds; v1p = u1p;
2046  v2n = u2n; v2ds = u2ds; v2p = u2p;
2047  v3n = u3n; v3ds = u3ds; v3p = u3p;
2048  }
2049  else {
2050  /* v1 <- y0 + y2 */
2051  bary_add(v1ds, v1n, y0ds, y0n, y2ds, y2n);
2052  v1p = 1;
2053 
2054  /* y(-1) : v2 <- v1 - y1 = y0 - y1 + y2 */
2055  v2p = 1;
2056  if (bary_sub(v2ds, v2n, v1ds, v1n, y1ds, y1n)) {
2057  bary_2comp(v2ds, v2n);
2058  v2p = 0;
2059  }
2060 
2061  /* y(1) : v1 <- v1 + y1 = y0 + y1 + y2 */
2062  bary_add(v1ds, v1n, v1ds, v1n, y1ds, y1n);
2063 
2064  /* y(-2) : v3 <- 2 * (v2 + y2) - y0 = y0 - 2 * (y1 - 2 * y2) */
2065  v3p = 1;
2066  if (v2p) {
2067  bary_add(v3ds, v3n, v2ds, v2n, y2ds, y2n);
2068  }
2069  else if (bary_sub(v3ds, v3n, y2ds, y2n, v2ds, v2n)) {
2070  bary_2comp(v3ds, v3n);
2071  v3p = 0;
2072  }
2073  bary_small_lshift(v3ds, v3ds, v3n, 1);
2074  if (!v3p) {
2075  bary_add(v3ds, v3n, v3ds, v3n, y0ds, y0n);
2076  }
2077  else if (bary_sub(v3ds, v3n, v3ds, v3n, y0ds, y0n)) {
2078  bary_2comp(v3ds, v3n);
2079  v3p = 0;
2080  }
2081  }
2082 
2083  /* z(0) : t0 <- x0 * y0 */
2084  bary_mul_toom3_start(t0ds, t0n, x0ds, x0n, y0ds, y0n, wds, wn);
2085  t0p = 1;
2086 
2087  /* z(1) : t1 <- u1 * v1 */
2088  bary_mul_toom3_start(t1ds, t1n, u1ds, u1n, v1ds, v1n, wds, wn);
2089  t1p = u1p == v1p;
2090  assert(t1ds[t1n-1] == 0);
2091  t1n--;
2092 
2093  /* z(-1) : t2 <- u2 * v2 */
2094  bary_mul_toom3_start(t2ds, t2n, u2ds, u2n, v2ds, v2n, wds, wn);
2095  t2p = u2p == v2p;
2096  assert(t2ds[t2n-1] == 0);
2097  t2n--;
2098 
2099  /* z(-2) : t3 <- u3 * v3 */
2100  bary_mul_toom3_start(t3ds, t3n, u3ds, u3n, v3ds, v3n, wds, wn);
2101  t3p = u3p == v3p;
2102  assert(t3ds[t3n-1] == 0);
2103  t3n--;
2104 
2105  /* z(inf) : t4 <- x2 * y2 */
2106  bary_mul_toom3_start(t4ds, t4n, x2ds, x2n, y2ds, y2n, wds, wn);
2107  t4p = 1;
2108 
2109  /*
2110  * [Step2] interpolating z0, z1, z2, z3 and z4.
2111  */
2112 
2113  /* z0 <- z(0) == t0 */
2114  z0n = t0n; z0ds = t0ds;
2115 
2116  /* z4 <- z(inf) == t4 */
2117  z4n = t4n; z4ds = t4ds;
2118 
2119  /* z3 <- (z(-2) - z(1)) / 3 == (t3 - t1) / 3 */
2120  if (t3p == t1p) {
2121  z3p = t3p;
2122  if (bary_sub(z3ds, z3n, t3ds, t3n, t1ds, t1n)) {
2123  bary_2comp(z3ds, z3n);
2124  z3p = !z3p;
2125  }
2126  }
2127  else {
2128  z3p = t3p;
2129  bary_add(z3ds, z3n, t3ds, t3n, t1ds, t1n);
2130  }
2131  bigdivrem_single(z3ds, z3ds, z3n, 3);
2132 
2133  /* z1 <- (z(1) - z(-1)) / 2 == (t1 - t2) / 2 */
2134  if (t1p == t2p) {
2135  z1p = t1p;
2136  if (bary_sub(z1ds, z1n, t1ds, t1n, t2ds, t2n)) {
2137  bary_2comp(z1ds, z1n);
2138  z1p = !z1p;
2139  }
2140  }
2141  else {
2142  z1p = t1p;
2143  bary_add(z1ds, z1n, t1ds, t1n, t2ds, t2n);
2144  }
2145  bary_small_rshift(z1ds, z1ds, z1n, 1, 0);
2146 
2147  /* z2 <- z(-1) - z(0) == t2 - t0 */
2148  if (t2p == t0p) {
2149  z2p = t2p;
2150  if (bary_sub(z2ds, z2n, t2ds, t2n, t0ds, t0n)) {
2151  bary_2comp(z2ds, z2n);
2152  z2p = !z2p;
2153  }
2154  }
2155  else {
2156  z2p = t2p;
2157  bary_add(z2ds, z2n, t2ds, t2n, t0ds, t0n);
2158  }
2159 
2160  /* z3 <- (z2 - z3) / 2 + 2 * z(inf) == (z2 - z3) / 2 + 2 * t4 */
2161  if (z2p == z3p) {
2162  z3p = z2p;
2163  if (bary_sub(z3ds, z3n, z2ds, z2n, z3ds, z3n)) {
2164  bary_2comp(z3ds, z3n);
2165  z3p = !z3p;
2166  }
2167  }
2168  else {
2169  z3p = z2p;
2170  bary_add(z3ds, z3n, z2ds, z2n, z3ds, z3n);
2171  }
2172  bary_small_rshift(z3ds, z3ds, z3n, 1, 0);
2173  if (z3p == t4p) {
2174  bary_muladd_1xN(z3ds, z3n, 2, t4ds, t4n);
2175  }
2176  else {
2177  if (bary_mulsub_1xN(z3ds, z3n, 2, t4ds, t4n)) {
2178  bary_2comp(z3ds, z3n);
2179  z3p = !z3p;
2180  }
2181  }
2182 
2183  /* z2 <- z2 + z1 - z(inf) == z2 + z1 - t4 */
2184  if (z2p == z1p) {
2185  bary_add(z2ds, z2n, z2ds, z2n, z1ds, z1n);
2186  }
2187  else {
2188  if (bary_sub(z2ds, z2n, z2ds, z2n, z1ds, z1n)) {
2189  bary_2comp(z2ds, z2n);
2190  z2p = !z2p;
2191  }
2192  }
2193 
2194  if (z2p == t4p) {
2195  if (bary_sub(z2ds, z2n, z2ds, z2n, t4ds, t4n)) {
2196  bary_2comp(z2ds, z2n);
2197  z2p = !z2p;
2198  }
2199  }
2200  else {
2201  bary_add(z2ds, z2n, z2ds, z2n, t4ds, t4n);
2202  }
2203 
2204  /* z1 <- z1 - z3 */
2205  if (z1p == z3p) {
2206  if (bary_sub(z1ds, z1n, z1ds, z1n, z3ds, z3n)) {
2207  bary_2comp(z1ds, z1n);
2208  z1p = !z1p;
2209  }
2210  }
2211  else {
2212  bary_add(z1ds, z1n, z1ds, z1n, z3ds, z3n);
2213  }
2214 
2215  /*
2216  * [Step3] Substituting base value into b of the polynomial z(b),
2217  */
2218 
2219  MEMCPY(zzds, z0ds, BDIGIT, z0n);
2220  BDIGITS_ZERO(zzds + z0n, 4*n - z0n);
2221  MEMCPY(zzds + 4*n, z4ds, BDIGIT, z4n);
2222  BDIGITS_ZERO(zzds + 4*n + z4n, zzn - (4*n + z4n));
2223  if (z1p)
2224  bary_add(zzds + n, zzn - n, zzds + n, zzn - n, z1ds, z1n);
2225  else
2226  bary_sub(zzds + n, zzn - n, zzds + n, zzn - n, z1ds, z1n);
2227  if (z2p)
2228  bary_add(zzds + 2*n, zzn - 2*n, zzds + 2*n, zzn - 2*n, z2ds, z2n);
2229  else
2230  bary_sub(zzds + 2*n, zzn - 2*n, zzds + 2*n, zzn - 2*n, z2ds, z2n);
2231  if (z3p)
2232  bary_add(zzds + 3*n, zzn - 3*n, zzds + 3*n, zzn - 3*n, z3ds, z3n);
2233  else
2234  bary_sub(zzds + 3*n, zzn - 3*n, zzds + 3*n, zzn - 3*n, z3ds, z3n);
2235 
2236  BARY_TRUNC(zzds, zzn);
2237  MEMCPY(zds, zzds, BDIGIT, zzn);
2238  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds + zzn, zn - zzn);
2239 
2240  if (work)
2241  ALLOCV_END(work);
2242 }
2243 
2244 VALUE
2245 rb_big_mul_toom3(VALUE x, VALUE y)
2246 {
2247  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y), zn = xn + yn;
2248  VALUE z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
2249  if (xn > yn || yn < 3 || !TOOM3_BALANCED(xn,yn))
2250  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "unexpected bignum length for toom3");
2251  bary_mul_toom3(BDIGITS(z), zn, BDIGITS(x), xn, BDIGITS(y), yn, NULL, 0);
2252  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
2253  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
2254  return z;
2255 }
2256 
2257 #ifdef USE_GMP
2258 static void
2259 bary_mul_gmp(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2260 {
2261  const size_t nails = (sizeof(BDIGIT)-SIZEOF_BDIGIT)*CHAR_BIT;
2262  mpz_t x, y, z;
2263  size_t count;
2264 
2265  assert(xn + yn <= zn);
2266 
2267  mpz_init(x);
2268  mpz_init(y);
2269  mpz_init(z);
2270  mpz_import(x, xn, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, xds);
2271  if (xds == yds && xn == yn) {
2272  mpz_mul(z, x, x);
2273  }
2274  else {
2275  mpz_import(y, yn, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, yds);
2276  mpz_mul(z, x, y);
2277  }
2278  mpz_export(zds, &count, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, z);
2279  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds+count, zn-count);
2280  mpz_clear(x);
2281  mpz_clear(y);
2282  mpz_clear(z);
2283 }
2284 
2285 VALUE
2286 rb_big_mul_gmp(VALUE x, VALUE y)
2287 {
2288  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y), zn = xn + yn;
2289  VALUE z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
2290  bary_mul_gmp(BDIGITS(z), zn, BDIGITS(x), xn, BDIGITS(y), yn);
2291  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
2292  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
2293  return z;
2294 }
2295 #endif
2296 
2297 static void
2298 bary_short_mul(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2299 {
2300  assert(xn + yn <= zn);
2301 
2302  if (xn == 1 && yn == 1) {
2303  bary_mul_single(zds, zn, xds[0], yds[0]);
2304  }
2305  else {
2306  bary_mul_normal(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2307  rb_thread_check_ints();
2308  }
2309 }
2310 
2311 /* determine whether a bignum is sparse or not by random sampling */
2312 static inline int
2313 bary_sparse_p(const BDIGIT *ds, size_t n)
2314 {
2315  long c = 0;
2316 
2317  if ( ds[rb_genrand_ulong_limited(n / 2) + n / 4]) c++;
2318  if (c <= 1 && ds[rb_genrand_ulong_limited(n / 2) + n / 4]) c++;
2319  if (c <= 1 && ds[rb_genrand_ulong_limited(n / 2) + n / 4]) c++;
2320 
2321  return (c <= 1) ? 1 : 0;
2322 }
2323 
2324 static int
2325 bary_mul_precheck(BDIGIT **zdsp, size_t *znp, const BDIGIT **xdsp, size_t *xnp, const BDIGIT **ydsp, size_t *ynp)
2326 {
2327  size_t nlsz; /* number of least significant zero BDIGITs */
2328 
2329  BDIGIT *zds = *zdsp;
2330  size_t zn = *znp;
2331  const BDIGIT *xds = *xdsp;
2332  size_t xn = *xnp;
2333  const BDIGIT *yds = *ydsp;
2334  size_t yn = *ynp;
2335 
2336  assert(xn + yn <= zn);
2337 
2338  nlsz = 0;
2339 
2340  while (0 < xn) {
2341  if (xds[xn-1] == 0) {
2342  xn--;
2343  }
2344  else {
2345  do {
2346  if (xds[0] != 0)
2347  break;
2348  xds++;
2349  xn--;
2350  nlsz++;
2351  } while (0 < xn);
2352  break;
2353  }
2354  }
2355 
2356  while (0 < yn) {
2357  if (yds[yn-1] == 0) {
2358  yn--;
2359  }
2360  else {
2361  do {
2362  if (yds[0] != 0)
2363  break;
2364  yds++;
2365  yn--;
2366  nlsz++;
2367  } while (0 < yn);
2368  break;
2369  }
2370  }
2371 
2372  if (nlsz) {
2373  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds, nlsz);
2374  zds += nlsz;
2375  zn -= nlsz;
2376  }
2377 
2378  /* make sure that y is longer than x */
2379  if (xn > yn) {
2380  const BDIGIT *tds;
2381  size_t tn;
2382  tds = xds; xds = yds; yds = tds;
2383  tn = xn; xn = yn; yn = tn;
2384  }
2385  assert(xn <= yn);
2386 
2387  if (xn <= 1) {
2388  if (xn == 0) {
2389  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds, zn);
2390  return 1;
2391  }
2392 
2393  if (xds[0] == 1) {
2394  MEMCPY(zds, yds, BDIGIT, yn);
2395  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds+yn, zn-yn);
2396  return 1;
2397  }
2398  if (POW2_P(xds[0])) {
2399  zds[yn] = bary_small_lshift(zds, yds, yn, bit_length(xds[0])-1);
2400  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds+yn+1, zn-yn-1);
2401  return 1;
2402  }
2403  if (yn == 1 && yds[0] == 1) {
2404  zds[0] = xds[0];
2405  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds+1, zn-1);
2406  return 1;
2407  }
2408  bary_mul_normal(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2409  return 1;
2410  }
2411 
2412  *zdsp = zds;
2413  *znp = zn;
2414  *xdsp = xds;
2415  *xnp = xn;
2416  *ydsp = yds;
2417  *ynp = yn;
2418 
2419  return 0;
2420 }
2421 
2422 static void
2423 bary_mul_karatsuba_branch(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, BDIGIT *wds, size_t wn)
2424 {
2425  /* normal multiplication when x is small */
2426  if (xn < KARATSUBA_MUL_DIGITS) {
2427  normal:
2428  if (xds == yds && xn == yn)
2429  bary_sq_fast(zds, zn, xds, xn);
2430  else
2431  bary_short_mul(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2432  return;
2433  }
2434 
2435  /* normal multiplication when x or y is a sparse bignum */
2436  if (bary_sparse_p(xds, xn)) goto normal;
2437  if (bary_sparse_p(yds, yn)) {
2438  bary_short_mul(zds, zn, yds, yn, xds, xn);
2439  return;
2440  }
2441 
2442  /* balance multiplication by slicing y when x is much smaller than y */
2443  if (!KARATSUBA_BALANCED(xn, yn)) {
2444  bary_mul_balance_with_mulfunc(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, wds, wn, bary_mul_karatsuba_start);
2445  return;
2446  }
2447 
2448  /* multiplication by karatsuba method */
2449  bary_mul_karatsuba(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, wds, wn);
2450 }
2451 
2452 static void
2453 bary_mul_karatsuba_start(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, BDIGIT *wds, size_t wn)
2454 {
2455  if (bary_mul_precheck(&zds, &zn, &xds, &xn, &yds, &yn))
2456  return;
2457 
2458  bary_mul_karatsuba_branch(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, wds, wn);
2459 }
2460 
2461 static void
2462 bary_mul_toom3_branch(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, BDIGIT *wds, size_t wn)
2463 {
2464  if (xn < TOOM3_MUL_DIGITS) {
2465  bary_mul_karatsuba_branch(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, wds, wn);
2466  return;
2467  }
2468 
2469  if (!TOOM3_BALANCED(xn, yn)) {
2470  bary_mul_balance_with_mulfunc(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, wds, wn, bary_mul_toom3_start);
2471  return;
2472  }
2473 
2474  bary_mul_toom3(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, wds, wn);
2475 }
2476 
2477 static void
2478 bary_mul_toom3_start(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn, BDIGIT *wds, size_t wn)
2479 {
2480  if (bary_mul_precheck(&zds, &zn, &xds, &xn, &yds, &yn))
2481  return;
2482 
2483  bary_mul_toom3_branch(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, wds, wn);
2484 }
2485 
2486 static void
2487 bary_mul(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2488 {
2489 #ifdef USE_GMP
2490  const size_t naive_threshold = GMP_MUL_DIGITS;
2491 #else
2492  const size_t naive_threshold = KARATSUBA_MUL_DIGITS;
2493 #endif
2494  if (xn <= yn) {
2495  if (xn < naive_threshold) {
2496  if (xds == yds && xn == yn)
2497  bary_sq_fast(zds, zn, xds, xn);
2498  else
2499  bary_short_mul(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2500  return;
2501  }
2502  }
2503  else {
2504  if (yn < naive_threshold) {
2505  bary_short_mul(zds, zn, yds, yn, xds, xn);
2506  return;
2507  }
2508  }
2509 
2510 #ifdef USE_GMP
2511  bary_mul_gmp(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2512 #else
2513  bary_mul_toom3_start(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn, NULL, 0);
2514 #endif
2515 }
2516 
2517 struct big_div_struct {
2518  size_t yn, zn;
2519  BDIGIT *yds, *zds;
2520  volatile VALUE stop;
2521 };
2522 
2523 static void *
2524 bigdivrem1(void *ptr)
2525 {
2526  struct big_div_struct *bds = (struct big_div_struct*)ptr;
2527  size_t yn = bds->yn;
2528  size_t zn = bds->zn;
2529  BDIGIT *yds = bds->yds, *zds = bds->zds;
2530  BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED num;
2531  BDIGIT q;
2532 
2533  do {
2534  if (bds->stop) {
2535  bds->zn = zn;
2536  return 0;
2537  }
2538  if (zds[zn-1] == yds[yn-1]) q = BDIGMAX;
2539  else q = (BDIGIT)((BIGUP(zds[zn-1]) + zds[zn-2])/yds[yn-1]);
2540  if (q) {
2541  num = bigdivrem_mulsub(zds+zn-(yn+1), yn+1,
2542  q,
2543  yds, yn);
2544  while (num) { /* "add back" required */
2545  q--;
2546  num = bary_add(zds+zn-(yn+1), yn,
2547  zds+zn-(yn+1), yn,
2548  yds, yn);
2549  num--;
2550  }
2551  }
2552  zn--;
2553  zds[zn] = q;
2554  } while (zn > yn);
2555  return 0;
2556 }
2557 
2558 static void
2559 rb_big_stop(void *ptr)
2560 {
2561  struct big_div_struct *bds = ptr;
2562  bds->stop = Qtrue;
2563 }
2564 
2565 static BDIGIT
2566 bigdivrem_single1(BDIGIT *qds, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, BDIGIT x_higher_bdigit, BDIGIT y)
2567 {
2568  assert(0 < xn);
2569  assert(x_higher_bdigit < y);
2570  if (POW2_P(y)) {
2571  BDIGIT r;
2572  r = xds[0] & (y-1);
2573  bary_small_rshift(qds, xds, xn, bit_length(y)-1, x_higher_bdigit);
2574  return r;
2575  }
2576  else {
2577  size_t i;
2578  BDIGIT_DBL t2;
2579  t2 = x_higher_bdigit;
2580  i = xn;
2581  while (i--) {
2582  t2 = BIGUP(t2) + xds[i];
2583  qds[i] = (BDIGIT)(t2 / y);
2584  t2 %= y;
2585  }
2586  return (BDIGIT)t2;
2587  }
2588 }
2589 
2590 static BDIGIT
2591 bigdivrem_single(BDIGIT *qds, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, BDIGIT y)
2592 {
2593  return bigdivrem_single1(qds, xds, xn, 0, y);
2594 }
2595 
2596 static void
2597 bigdivrem_restoring(BDIGIT *zds, size_t zn, BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2598 {
2599  struct big_div_struct bds;
2600  size_t ynzero;
2601 
2602  assert(yn < zn);
2603  assert(BDIGIT_MSB(yds[yn-1]));
2604  assert(zds[zn-1] < yds[yn-1]);
2605 
2606  for (ynzero = 0; !yds[ynzero]; ynzero++);
2607 
2608  if (ynzero+1 == yn) {
2609  BDIGIT r;
2610  r = bigdivrem_single1(zds+yn, zds+ynzero, zn-yn, zds[zn-1], yds[ynzero]);
2611  zds[ynzero] = r;
2612  return;
2613  }
2614 
2615  bds.yn = yn - ynzero;
2616  bds.zds = zds + ynzero;
2617  bds.yds = yds + ynzero;
2618  bds.stop = Qfalse;
2619  bds.zn = zn - ynzero;
2620  if (bds.zn > 10000 || bds.yn > 10000) {
2621  retry:
2622  bds.stop = Qfalse;
2623  rb_thread_call_without_gvl(bigdivrem1, &bds, rb_big_stop, &bds);
2624 
2625  if (bds.stop == Qtrue) {
2626  /* execute trap handler, but exception was not raised. */
2627  goto retry;
2628  }
2629  }
2630  else {
2631  bigdivrem1(&bds);
2632  }
2633 }
2634 
2635 static void
2636 bary_divmod_normal(BDIGIT *qds, size_t qn, BDIGIT *rds, size_t rn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2637 {
2638  int shift;
2639  BDIGIT *zds, *yyds;
2640  size_t zn;
2641  VALUE tmpyz = 0;
2642 
2643  assert(yn < xn || (xn == yn && yds[yn - 1] <= xds[xn - 1]));
2644  assert(qds ? (xn - yn + 1) <= qn : 1);
2645  assert(rds ? yn <= rn : 1);
2646 
2647  zn = xn + BIGDIVREM_EXTRA_WORDS;
2648 
2649  shift = nlz(yds[yn-1]);
2650  if (shift) {
2651  int alloc_y = !rds;
2652  int alloc_z = !qds || qn < zn;
2653  if (alloc_y && alloc_z) {
2654  yyds = ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, tmpyz, yn+zn);
2655  zds = yyds + yn;
2656  }
2657  else {
2658  yyds = alloc_y ? ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, tmpyz, yn) : rds;
2659  zds = alloc_z ? ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, tmpyz, zn) : qds;
2660  }
2661  zds[xn] = bary_small_lshift(zds, xds, xn, shift);
2662  bary_small_lshift(yyds, yds, yn, shift);
2663  }
2664  else {
2665  if (qds && zn <= qn)
2666  zds = qds;
2667  else
2668  zds = ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, tmpyz, zn);
2669  MEMCPY(zds, xds, BDIGIT, xn);
2670  zds[xn] = 0;
2671  /* bigdivrem_restoring will not modify y.
2672  * So use yds directly. */
2673  yyds = (BDIGIT *)yds;
2674  }
2675 
2676  bigdivrem_restoring(zds, zn, yyds, yn);
2677 
2678  if (rds) {
2679  if (shift)
2680  bary_small_rshift(rds, zds, yn, shift, 0);
2681  else
2682  MEMCPY(rds, zds, BDIGIT, yn);
2683  BDIGITS_ZERO(rds+yn, rn-yn);
2684  }
2685 
2686  if (qds) {
2687  size_t j = zn - yn;
2688  MEMMOVE(qds, zds+yn, BDIGIT, j);
2689  BDIGITS_ZERO(qds+j, qn-j);
2690  }
2691 
2692  if (tmpyz)
2693  ALLOCV_END(tmpyz);
2694 }
2695 
2696 VALUE
2697 rb_big_divrem_normal(VALUE x, VALUE y)
2698 {
2699  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y), qn, rn;
2700  BDIGIT *xds = BDIGITS(x), *yds = BDIGITS(y), *qds, *rds;
2701  VALUE q, r;
2702 
2703  BARY_TRUNC(yds, yn);
2704  if (yn == 0)
2705  rb_num_zerodiv();
2706  BARY_TRUNC(xds, xn);
2707 
2708  if (xn < yn || (xn == yn && xds[xn - 1] < yds[yn - 1]))
2709  return rb_assoc_new(LONG2FIX(0), x);
2710 
2711  qn = xn + BIGDIVREM_EXTRA_WORDS;
2712  q = bignew(qn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
2713  qds = BDIGITS(q);
2714 
2715  rn = yn;
2716  r = bignew(rn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
2717  rds = BDIGITS(r);
2718 
2719  bary_divmod_normal(qds, qn, rds, rn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2720 
2721  bigtrunc(q);
2722  bigtrunc(r);
2723 
2724  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
2725  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
2726 
2727  return rb_assoc_new(q, r);
2728 }

2730 #ifdef USE_GMP
2731 static void
2732 bary_divmod_gmp(BDIGIT *qds, size_t qn, BDIGIT *rds, size_t rn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2733 {
2734  const size_t nails = (sizeof(BDIGIT)-SIZEOF_BDIGIT)*CHAR_BIT;
2735  mpz_t x, y, q, r;
2736  size_t count;
2737 
2738  assert(yn < xn || (xn == yn && yds[yn - 1] <= xds[xn - 1]));
2739  assert(qds ? (xn - yn + 1) <= qn : 1);
2740  assert(rds ? yn <= rn : 1);
2741  assert(qds || rds);
2742 
2743  mpz_init(x);
2744  mpz_init(y);
2745  if (qds) mpz_init(q);
2746  if (rds) mpz_init(r);
2747 
2748  mpz_import(x, xn, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, xds);
2749  mpz_import(y, yn, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, yds);
2750 
2751  if (!rds) {
2752  mpz_fdiv_q(q, x, y);
2753  }
2754  else if (!qds) {
2755  mpz_fdiv_r(r, x, y);
2756  }
2757  else {
2758  mpz_fdiv_qr(q, r, x, y);
2759  }
2760 
2761  mpz_clear(x);
2762  mpz_clear(y);
2763 
2764  if (qds) {
2765  mpz_export(qds, &count, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, q);
2766  BDIGITS_ZERO(qds+count, qn-count);
2767  mpz_clear(q);
2768  }
2769 
2770  if (rds) {
2771  mpz_export(rds, &count, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, r);
2772  BDIGITS_ZERO(rds+count, rn-count);
2773  mpz_clear(r);
2774  }
2775 }

2781  BDIGIT *xds = BDIGITS(x), *yds = BDIGITS(y), *qds, *rds;
2782  VALUE q, r;
2783

2788

2790  return rb_assoc_new(LONG2FIX(0), x);
2791 
2792  qn = xn - yn + 1;

2794  qds = BDIGITS(q);

2812 static void
2813 bary_divmod_branch(BDIGIT *qds, size_t qn, BDIGIT *rds, size_t rn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2814 {
2815 #ifdef USE_GMP
2816  if (GMP_DIV_DIGITS < xn) {
2817  bary_divmod_gmp(qds, qn, rds, rn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2818  return;
2819  }
2820 #endif
2821  bary_divmod_normal(qds, qn, rds, rn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2822 }
2823 
2824 static void
2825 bary_divmod(BDIGIT *qds, size_t qn, BDIGIT *rds, size_t rn, const BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, const BDIGIT *yds, size_t yn)
2826 {
2827  assert(xn <= qn);
2828  assert(yn <= rn);
2829 
2830  BARY_TRUNC(yds, yn);
2831  if (yn == 0)
2832  rb_num_zerodiv();
2833 
2834  BARY_TRUNC(xds, xn);
2835  if (xn == 0) {
2836  BDIGITS_ZERO(qds, qn);
2837  BDIGITS_ZERO(rds, rn);
2838  return;
2839  }
2840 
2841  if (xn < yn || (xn == yn && xds[xn - 1] < yds[yn - 1])) {
2842  MEMCPY(rds, xds, BDIGIT, xn);
2843  BDIGITS_ZERO(rds+xn, rn-xn);
2844  BDIGITS_ZERO(qds, qn);
2845  }
2846  else if (yn == 1) {
2847  MEMCPY(qds, xds, BDIGIT, xn);
2848  BDIGITS_ZERO(qds+xn, qn-xn);
2849  rds[0] = bigdivrem_single(qds, xds, xn, yds[0]);
2850  BDIGITS_ZERO(rds+1, rn-1);
2851  }
2852  else if (xn == 2 && yn == 2) {
2853  BDIGIT_DBL x = bary2bdigitdbl(xds, 2);
2854  BDIGIT_DBL y = bary2bdigitdbl(yds, 2);
2855  BDIGIT_DBL q = x / y;
2856  BDIGIT_DBL r = x % y;
2857  qds[0] = BIGLO(q);
2858  qds[1] = BIGLO(BIGDN(q));
2859  BDIGITS_ZERO(qds+2, qn-2);
2860  rds[0] = BIGLO(r);
2861  rds[1] = BIGLO(BIGDN(r));
2862  BDIGITS_ZERO(rds+2, rn-2);
2863  }
2864  else {
2865  bary_divmod_branch(qds, qn, rds, rn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
2866  }
2867 }

2907 int
2908 rb_cmpint(VALUE val, VALUE a, VALUE b)
2909 {
2910  if (NIL_P(val)) {
2911  rb_cmperr(a, b);
2912  }
2913  if (FIXNUM_P(val)) {
2914  long l = FIX2LONG(val);
2915  if (l > 0) return 1;
2916  if (l < 0) return -1;
2917  return 0;
2918  }
2919  if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(val)) {
2920  if (BIGZEROP(val)) return 0;
2921  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(val)) return 1;
2922  return -1;
2923  }
2924  if (RTEST(rb_funcall(val, '>', 1, INT2FIX(0)))) return 1;
2925  if (RTEST(rb_funcall(val, '<', 1, INT2FIX(0)))) return -1;
2926  return 0;
2927 }

2929 #define BIGNUM_SET_LEN(b,l) \
2930  ((RBASIC(b)->flags & BIGNUM_EMBED_FLAG) ? \
2931  (void)(RBASIC(b)->flags = \
2932  (RBASIC(b)->flags & ~BIGNUM_EMBED_LEN_MASK) | \
2933  ((l) << BIGNUM_EMBED_LEN_SHIFT)) : \
2934  (void)(RBIGNUM(b)->as.heap.len = (l)))

2936 static void
2937 rb_big_realloc(VALUE big, size_t len)
2938 {
2939  BDIGIT *ds;
2940  if (RBASIC(big)->flags & BIGNUM_EMBED_FLAG) {
2941  if (BIGNUM_EMBED_LEN_MAX < len) {
2942  ds = ALLOC_N(BDIGIT, len);
2943  MEMCPY(ds, RBIGNUM(big)->as.ary, BDIGIT, BIGNUM_EMBED_LEN_MAX);
2944  RBIGNUM(big)->as.heap.len = BIGNUM_LEN(big);
2945  RBIGNUM(big)->as.heap.digits = ds;
2946  RBASIC(big)->flags &= ~BIGNUM_EMBED_FLAG;
2947  }
2948  }
2949  else {
2950  if (len <= BIGNUM_EMBED_LEN_MAX) {
2951  ds = RBIGNUM(big)->as.heap.digits;
2952  RBASIC(big)->flags |= BIGNUM_EMBED_FLAG;
2953  BIGNUM_SET_LEN(big, len);
2954  (void)VALGRIND_MAKE_MEM_UNDEFINED((void*)RBIGNUM(big)->as.ary, sizeof(RBIGNUM(big)->as.ary));
2955  if (ds) {
2956  MEMCPY(RBIGNUM(big)->as.ary, ds, BDIGIT, len);
2957  xfree(ds);
2958  }
2959  }
2960  else {
2961  if (BIGNUM_LEN(big) == 0) {
2962  RBIGNUM(big)->as.heap.digits = ALLOC_N(BDIGIT, len);
2963  }
2964  else {
2965  REALLOC_N(RBIGNUM(big)->as.heap.digits, BDIGIT, len);
2966  }
2967  }
2968  }
2969 }
2970 
2971 void
2972 rb_big_resize(VALUE big, size_t len)
2973 {
2974  rb_big_realloc(big, len);
2975  BIGNUM_SET_LEN(big, len);
2976 }

2978 static VALUE
2979 bignew_1(VALUE klass, size_t len, int sign)
2980 {
2981  NEWOBJ_OF(big, struct RBignum, klass, T_BIGNUM | (RGENGC_WB_PROTECTED_BIGNUM ? FL_WB_PROTECTED : 0));
2982  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(big, sign?1:0);
2983  if (len <= BIGNUM_EMBED_LEN_MAX) {
2984  RBASIC(big)->flags |= BIGNUM_EMBED_FLAG;
2985  BIGNUM_SET_LEN(big, len);
2986  (void)VALGRIND_MAKE_MEM_UNDEFINED((void*)RBIGNUM(big)->as.ary, sizeof(RBIGNUM(big)->as.ary));
2987  }
2988  else {
2989  RBIGNUM(big)->as.heap.digits = ALLOC_N(BDIGIT, len);
2990  RBIGNUM(big)->as.heap.len = len;
2991  }
2992  OBJ_FREEZE(big);
2993  return (VALUE)big;
2994 }

3067 static inline VALUE
3068 bigtrunc(VALUE x)
3069 {

3071  BDIGIT *ds = BDIGITS(x);
3072 
3073  if (len == 0) return x;
3074  while (--len && !ds[len]);
3075  if (BIGNUM_LEN(x) > len+1) {
3076  rb_big_resize(x, len+1);
3077  }
3078  return x;

3081 static inline VALUE
3082 bigfixize(VALUE x)
3083 {
3084  size_t n = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
3085  BDIGIT *ds = BDIGITS(x);
3086 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
3087  unsigned long u;
3088 #else
3089  BDIGIT u;
3090 #endif
3091 
3092  BARY_TRUNC(ds, n);
3093 
3094  if (n == 0) return INT2FIX(0);
3095 
3096 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
3097  if (sizeof(long)/SIZEOF_BDIGIT < n)
3098  goto return_big;
3099  else {
3100  int i = (int)n;
3101  u = 0;
3102  while (i--) {
3103  u = (unsigned long)(BIGUP(u) + ds[i]);
3104  }
3105  }
3106 #else /* SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG */
3107  if (1 < n)
3108  goto return_big;
3109  else
3110  u = ds[0];
3111 #endif
3112 
3113  if (BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(x)) {
3114  if (POSFIXABLE(u)) return LONG2FIX((long)u);
3115  }
3116  else {
3117  if (u <= -FIXNUM_MIN) return LONG2FIX(-(long)u);
3118  }
3119 
3120  return_big:
3121  rb_big_resize(x, n);
3122  return x;
3123 }

3126 bignorm(VALUE x)
3127 {
3128  if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(x)) {
3129  x = bigfixize(x);
3130  }
3131  return x;
3132 }

3140 VALUE
3141 rb_uint2big(VALUE n)
3142 {
3143  long i;
3144  VALUE big = bignew(bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_VALUE), 1);
3145  BDIGIT *digits = BDIGITS(big);
3146 
3147 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_VALUE
3148  digits[0] = n;
3149 #else
3150  for (i = 0; i < bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_VALUE); i++) {
3151  digits[i] = BIGLO(n);
3152  n = BIGDN(n);
3153  }
3154 #endif
3155 
3156  i = bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_VALUE);
3157  while (--i && !digits[i]) ;
3158  BIGNUM_SET_LEN(big, i+1);
3159  return big;
3160 }

3162 VALUE
3163 rb_int2big(SIGNED_VALUE n)
3164 {
3165  long neg = 0;
3166  VALUE u;
3167  VALUE big;
3168 
3169  if (n < 0) {
3170  u = 1 + (VALUE)(-(n + 1)); /* u = -n avoiding overflow */
3171  neg = 1;
3172  }
3173  else {
3174  u = n;
3175  }
3176  big = rb_uint2big(u);
3177  if (neg) {
3178  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(big, 0);
3179  }
3180  return big;
3181 }
