3213 /*
3214  * Calculate the number of bytes to be required to represent
3215  * the absolute value of the integer given as _val_.
3216  *
3217  * [val] an integer.
3218  * [nlz_bits_ret] number of leading zero bits in the most significant byte is returned if not NULL.
3219  *
3220  * This function returns ((val_numbits * CHAR_BIT + CHAR_BIT - 1) / CHAR_BIT)
3221  * where val_numbits is the number of bits of abs(val).
3222  * This function should not overflow.
3223  *
3224  * If nlz_bits_ret is not NULL,
3225  * (return_value * CHAR_BIT - val_numbits) is stored in *nlz_bits_ret.
3226  * In this case, 0 <= *nlz_bits_ret < CHAR_BIT.
3227  *
3228  */
3229 size_t
3230 rb_absint_size(VALUE val, int *nlz_bits_ret)
3231 {
3232  BDIGIT *dp;
3233  BDIGIT *de;
3234  BDIGIT fixbuf[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(long))];
3235 
3236  int num_leading_zeros;
3237 
3238  val = rb_to_int(val);
3239 
3240  if (FIXNUM_P(val)) {
3241  long v = FIX2LONG(val);
3242  if (v < 0) {
3243  v = -v;
3244  }
3245 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
3246  fixbuf[0] = v;
3247 #else
3248  {
3249  int i;
3250  for (i = 0; i < numberof(fixbuf); i++) {
3251  fixbuf[i] = BIGLO(v);
3252  v = BIGDN(v);
3253  }
3254  }
3255 #endif
3256  dp = fixbuf;
3257  de = fixbuf + numberof(fixbuf);
3258  }
3259  else {
3260  dp = BDIGITS(val);
3261  de = dp + BIGNUM_LEN(val);
3262  }
3263  while (dp < de && de[-1] == 0)
3264  de--;
3265  if (dp == de) {
3266  if (nlz_bits_ret)
3267  *nlz_bits_ret = 0;
3268  return 0;
3269  }
3270  num_leading_zeros = nlz(de[-1]);
3271  if (nlz_bits_ret)
3272  *nlz_bits_ret = num_leading_zeros % CHAR_BIT;
3273  return (de - dp) * SIZEOF_BDIGIT - num_leading_zeros / CHAR_BIT;
3274 }
3275 
3276 static size_t
3277 absint_numwords_small(size_t numbytes, int nlz_bits_in_msbyte, size_t word_numbits, size_t *nlz_bits_ret)
3278 {
3279  size_t val_numbits = numbytes * CHAR_BIT - nlz_bits_in_msbyte;
3280  size_t div = val_numbits / word_numbits;
3281  size_t mod = val_numbits % word_numbits;
3282  size_t numwords;
3283  size_t nlz_bits;
3284  numwords = mod == 0 ? div : div + 1;
3285  nlz_bits = mod == 0 ? 0 : word_numbits - mod;
3286  *nlz_bits_ret = nlz_bits;
3287  return numwords;
3288 }
3289 
3290 static size_t
3291 absint_numwords_generic(size_t numbytes, int nlz_bits_in_msbyte, size_t word_numbits, size_t *nlz_bits_ret)
3292 {
3293  static const BDIGIT char_bit[1] = { CHAR_BIT };
3294  BDIGIT numbytes_bary[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(numbytes))];
3295  BDIGIT val_numbits_bary[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(numbytes) + 1)];
3296  BDIGIT nlz_bits_in_msbyte_bary[1];
3297  BDIGIT word_numbits_bary[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(word_numbits))];
3298  BDIGIT div_bary[numberof(val_numbits_bary) + BIGDIVREM_EXTRA_WORDS];
3299  BDIGIT mod_bary[numberof(word_numbits_bary)];
3300  BDIGIT one[1] = { 1 };
3301  size_t nlz_bits;
3302  size_t mod;
3303  int sign;
3304  size_t numwords;
3305 
3306  nlz_bits_in_msbyte_bary[0] = nlz_bits_in_msbyte;
3307 
3308  /*
3309  * val_numbits = numbytes * CHAR_BIT - nlz_bits_in_msbyte
3310  * div, mod = val_numbits.divmod(word_numbits)
3311  * numwords = mod == 0 ? div : div + 1
3312  * nlz_bits = mod == 0 ? 0 : word_numbits - mod
3313  */
3314 
3315  bary_unpack(BARY_ARGS(numbytes_bary), &numbytes, 1, sizeof(numbytes), 0,
3316  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER);
3317  BARY_SHORT_MUL(val_numbits_bary, numbytes_bary, char_bit);
3318  if (nlz_bits_in_msbyte)
3319  BARY_SUB(val_numbits_bary, val_numbits_bary, nlz_bits_in_msbyte_bary);
3320  bary_unpack(BARY_ARGS(word_numbits_bary), &word_numbits, 1, sizeof(word_numbits), 0,
3321  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER);
3322  BARY_DIVMOD(div_bary, mod_bary, val_numbits_bary, word_numbits_bary);
3323  if (BARY_ZERO_P(mod_bary)) {
3324  nlz_bits = 0;
3325  }
3326  else {
3327  BARY_ADD(div_bary, div_bary, one);
3328  bary_pack(+1, BARY_ARGS(mod_bary), &mod, 1, sizeof(mod), 0,
3329  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER);
3330  nlz_bits = word_numbits - mod;
3331  }
3332  sign = bary_pack(+1, BARY_ARGS(div_bary), &numwords, 1, sizeof(numwords), 0,
3333  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER);
3334 
3335  if (sign == 2) {
3336 #if defined __GNUC__ && (__GNUC__ == 4 && __GNUC_MINOR__ == 4)
3337  *nlz_bits_ret = 0;
3338 #endif
3339  return (size_t)-1;
3340  }
3341  *nlz_bits_ret = nlz_bits;
3342  return numwords;
3343 }
3344 
3345 /*
3346  * Calculate the number of words to be required to represent
3347  * the absolute value of the integer given as _val_.
3348  *
3349  * [val] an integer.
3350  * [word_numbits] number of bits in a word.
3351  * [nlz_bits_ret] number of leading zero bits in the most significant word is returned if not NULL.
3352  *
3353  * This function returns ((val_numbits * CHAR_BIT + word_numbits - 1) / word_numbits)
3354  * where val_numbits is the number of bits of abs(val).
3355  *
3356  * This function can overflow.
3357  * When overflow occur, (size_t)-1 is returned.
3358  *
3359  * If nlz_bits_ret is not NULL and overflow is not occur,
3360  * (return_value * word_numbits - val_numbits) is stored in *nlz_bits_ret.
3361  * In this case, 0 <= *nlz_bits_ret < word_numbits.
3362  *
3363  */
3364 size_t
3365 rb_absint_numwords(VALUE val, size_t word_numbits, size_t *nlz_bits_ret)
3366 {
3367  size_t numbytes;
3368  int nlz_bits_in_msbyte;
3369  size_t numwords;
3370  size_t nlz_bits;
3371 
3372  if (word_numbits == 0)
3373  return (size_t)-1;
3374 
3375  numbytes = rb_absint_size(val, &nlz_bits_in_msbyte);
3376 
3377  if (numbytes <= SIZE_MAX / CHAR_BIT) {
3378  numwords = absint_numwords_small(numbytes, nlz_bits_in_msbyte, word_numbits, &nlz_bits);
3379 #ifdef DEBUG_INTEGER_PACK
3380  {
3381  size_t numwords0, nlz_bits0;
3382  numwords0 = absint_numwords_generic(numbytes, nlz_bits_in_msbyte, word_numbits, &nlz_bits0);
3383  assert(numwords0 == numwords);
3384  assert(nlz_bits0 == nlz_bits);
3385  }
3386 #endif
3387  }
3388  else {
3389  numwords = absint_numwords_generic(numbytes, nlz_bits_in_msbyte, word_numbits, &nlz_bits);
3390  }
3391  if (numwords == (size_t)-1)
3392  return numwords;
3393 
3394  if (nlz_bits_ret)
3395  *nlz_bits_ret = nlz_bits;
3396 
3397  return numwords;
3398 }
3399 
3400 /* Test abs(val) consists only a bit or not.
3401  *
3402  * Returns 1 if abs(val) == 1 << n for some n >= 0.
3403  * Returns 0 otherwise.
3404  *
3405  * rb_absint_singlebit_p can be used to determine required buffer size
3406  * for rb_integer_pack used with INTEGER_PACK_2COMP (two's complement).
3407  *
3408  * Following example calculates number of bits required to
3409  * represent val in two's complement number, without sign bit.
3410  *
3411  * size_t size;
3412  * int neg = FIXNUM_P(val) ? FIX2LONG(val) < 0 : BIGNUM_NEGATIVE_P(val);
3413  * size = rb_absint_numwords(val, 1, NULL)
3414  * if (size == (size_t)-1) ...overflow...
3415  * if (neg && rb_absint_singlebit_p(val))
3416  * size--;
3417  *
3418  * Following example calculates number of bytes required to
3419  * represent val in two's complement number, with sign bit.
3420  *
3421  * size_t size;
3422  * int neg = FIXNUM_P(val) ? FIX2LONG(val) < 0 : BIGNUM_NEGATIVE_P(val);
3423  * int nlz_bits;
3424  * size = rb_absint_size(val, &nlz_bits);
3425  * if (nlz_bits == 0 && !(neg && rb_absint_singlebit_p(val)))
3426  * size++;
3427  */
3428 int
3429 rb_absint_singlebit_p(VALUE val)
3430 {
3431  BDIGIT *dp;
3432  BDIGIT *de;
3433  BDIGIT fixbuf[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(long))];
3434  BDIGIT d;
3435 
3436  val = rb_to_int(val);
3437 
3438  if (FIXNUM_P(val)) {
3439  long v = FIX2LONG(val);
3440  if (v < 0) {
3441  v = -v;
3442  }
3443 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
3444  fixbuf[0] = v;
3445 #else
3446  {
3447  int i;
3448  for (i = 0; i < numberof(fixbuf); i++) {
3449  fixbuf[i] = BIGLO(v);
3450  v = BIGDN(v);
3451  }
3452  }
3453 #endif
3454  dp = fixbuf;
3455  de = fixbuf + numberof(fixbuf);
3456  }
3457  else {
3458  dp = BDIGITS(val);
3459  de = dp + BIGNUM_LEN(val);
3460  }
3461  while (dp < de && de[-1] == 0)
3462  de--;
3463  while (dp < de && dp[0] == 0)
3464  dp++;
3465  if (dp == de) /* no bit set. */
3466  return 0;
3467  if (dp != de-1) /* two non-zero words. two bits set, at least. */
3468  return 0;
3469  d = *dp;
3470  return POW2_P(d);
3471 }
3472 
3473 
3474 /*
3475  * Export an integer into a buffer.
3476  *
3477  * This function fills the buffer specified by _words_ and _numwords_ as
3478  * val in the format specified by _wordsize_, _nails_ and _flags_.
3479  *
3480  * [val] Fixnum, Bignum or another integer like object which has to_int method.
3481  * [words] buffer to export abs(val).
3482  * [numwords] the size of given buffer as number of words.
3483  * [wordsize] the size of word as number of bytes.
3484  * [nails] number of padding bits in a word.
3485  * Most significant nails bits of each word are filled by zero.
3486  * [flags] bitwise or of constants which name starts "INTEGER_PACK_".
3487  *
3488  * flags:
3489  * [INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST] Store the most significant word as the first word.
3490  * [INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST] Store the least significant word as the first word.
3491  * [INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST] Store the most significant byte in a word as the first byte in the word.
3492  * [INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST] Store the least significant byte in a word as the first byte in the word.
3493  * [INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER] INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST or INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST corresponding to the host's endian.
3494  * [INTEGER_PACK_2COMP] Use 2's complement representation.
3495  * [INTEGER_PACK_LITTLE_ENDIAN] Same as INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST|INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST
3496  * [INTEGER_PACK_BIG_ENDIAN] Same as INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST|INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST
3497  * [INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_GENERIC_IMPLEMENTATION] Use generic implementation (for test and debug).
3498  *
3499  * This function fills the buffer specified by _words_
3500  * as abs(val) if INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is not specified in _flags_.
3501  * If INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is specified, 2's complement representation of val is
3502  * filled in the buffer.
3503  *
3504  * This function returns the signedness and overflow condition.
3505  * The overflow condition depends on INTEGER_PACK_2COMP.
3506  *
3507  * INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is not specified:
3508  * -2 : negative overflow. val <= -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails))
3509  * -1 : negative without overflow. -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) < val < 0
3510  * 0 : zero. val == 0
3511  * 1 : positive without overflow. 0 < val < 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails))
3512  * 2 : positive overflow. 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) <= val
3513  *
3514  * INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is specified:
3515  * -2 : negative overflow. val < -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails))
3516  * -1 : negative without overflow. -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) <= val < 0
3517  * 0 : zero. val == 0
3518  * 1 : positive without overflow. 0 < val < 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails))
3519  * 2 : positive overflow. 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) <= val
3520  *
3521  * The value, -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)), is representable
3522  * in 2's complement representation but not representable in absolute value.
3523  * So -1 is returned for the value if INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is specified
3524  * but returns -2 if INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is not specified.
3525  *
3526  * The least significant words are filled in the buffer when overflow occur.
3527  */
3528 
3529 int
3530 rb_integer_pack(VALUE val, void *words, size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int flags)
3531 {
3532  int sign;
3533  BDIGIT *ds;
3534  size_t num_bdigits;
3535  BDIGIT fixbuf[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(long))];
3536 
3537  RB_GC_GUARD(val) = rb_to_int(val);
3538 
3539  if (FIXNUM_P(val)) {
3540  long v = FIX2LONG(val);
3541  if (v < 0) {
3542  sign = -1;
3543  v = -v;
3544  }
3545  else {
3546  sign = 1;
3547  }
3548 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
3549  fixbuf[0] = v;
3550 #else
3551  {
3552  int i;
3553  for (i = 0; i < numberof(fixbuf); i++) {
3554  fixbuf[i] = BIGLO(v);
3555  v = BIGDN(v);
3556  }
3557  }
3558 #endif
3559  ds = fixbuf;
3560  num_bdigits = numberof(fixbuf);
3561  }
3562  else {
3563  sign = BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(val) ? 1 : -1;
3564  ds = BDIGITS(val);
3565  num_bdigits = BIGNUM_LEN(val);
3566  }
3567 
3568  return bary_pack(sign, ds, num_bdigits, words, numwords, wordsize, nails, flags);
3569 }
3570 
3571 /*
3572  * Import an integer into a buffer.
3573  *
3574  * [words] buffer to import.
3575  * [numwords] the size of given buffer as number of words.
3576  * [wordsize] the size of word as number of bytes.
3577  * [nails] number of padding bits in a word.
3578  * Most significant nails bits of each word are ignored.
3579  * [flags] bitwise or of constants which name starts "INTEGER_PACK_".
3580  *
3581  * flags:
3582  * [INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST] Interpret the first word as the most significant word.
3583  * [INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST] Interpret the first word as the least significant word.
3584  * [INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST] Interpret the first byte in a word as the most significant byte in the word.
3585  * [INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST] Interpret the first byte in a word as the least significant byte in the word.
3586  * [INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER] INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST or INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST corresponding to the host's endian.
3587  * [INTEGER_PACK_2COMP] Use 2's complement representation.
3588  * [INTEGER_PACK_LITTLE_ENDIAN] Same as INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST|INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST
3589  * [INTEGER_PACK_BIG_ENDIAN] Same as INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST|INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST
3590  * [INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_BIGNUM] the result will be a Bignum
3591  * even if it is representable as a Fixnum.
3592  * [INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE] Returns non-positive value.
3593  * (Returns non-negative value if not specified.)
3594  * [INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_GENERIC_IMPLEMENTATION] Use generic implementation (for test and debug).
3595  *
3596  * This function returns the imported integer as Fixnum or Bignum.
3597  *
3598  * The range of the result value depends on INTEGER_PACK_2COMP and INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE.
3599  *
3600  * INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is not set:
3601  * 0 <= val < 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) if !INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE
3602  * -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) < val <= 0 if INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE
3603  *
3604  * INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is set:
3605  * -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)-1) <= val <= 2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)-1)-1 if !INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE
3606  * -2**(numwords*(wordsize*CHAR_BIT-nails)) <= val <= -1 if INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE
3607  *
3608  * INTEGER_PACK_2COMP without INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE means sign extension.
3609  * INTEGER_PACK_2COMP with INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE mean assuming the higher bits are 1.
3610  *
3611  * Note that this function returns 0 when numwords is zero and
3612  * INTEGER_PACK_2COMP is set but INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE is not set.
3613  */
3614 
3615 VALUE
3616 rb_integer_unpack(const void *words, size_t numwords, size_t wordsize, size_t nails, int flags)
3617 {
3618  VALUE val;
3619  size_t num_bdigits;
3620  int sign;
3621  int nlp_bits;
3622  BDIGIT *ds;
3623  BDIGIT fixbuf[2] = { 0, 0 };
3624 
3625  validate_integer_pack_format(numwords, wordsize, nails, flags,
3626  INTEGER_PACK_MSWORD_FIRST|
3627  INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST|
3628  INTEGER_PACK_MSBYTE_FIRST|
3629  INTEGER_PACK_LSBYTE_FIRST|
3630  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER|
3631  INTEGER_PACK_2COMP|
3632  INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_BIGNUM|
3633  INTEGER_PACK_NEGATIVE|
3634  INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_GENERIC_IMPLEMENTATION);
3635 
3636  num_bdigits = integer_unpack_num_bdigits(numwords, wordsize, nails, &nlp_bits);
3637 
3638  if (LONG_MAX-1 < num_bdigits)
3639  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big to unpack as an integer");
3640  if (num_bdigits <= numberof(fixbuf) && !(flags & INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_BIGNUM)) {
3641  val = Qfalse;
3642  ds = fixbuf;
3643  }
3644  else {
3645  val = bignew((long)num_bdigits, 0);
3646  ds = BDIGITS(val);
3647  }
3648  sign = bary_unpack_internal(ds, num_bdigits, words, numwords, wordsize, nails, flags, nlp_bits);
3649 
3650  if (sign == -2) {
3651  if (val) {
3652  big_extend_carry(val);
3653  }
3654  else if (num_bdigits == numberof(fixbuf)) {
3655  val = bignew((long)num_bdigits+1, 0);
3656  MEMCPY(BDIGITS(val), fixbuf, BDIGIT, num_bdigits);
3657  BDIGITS(val)[num_bdigits++] = 1;
3658  }
3659  else {
3660  ds[num_bdigits++] = 1;
3661  }
3662  }
3663 
3664  if (!val) {
3665  BDIGIT_DBL u = fixbuf[0] + BIGUP(fixbuf[1]);
3666  if (u == 0)
3667  return LONG2FIX(0);
3668  if (0 < sign && POSFIXABLE(u))
3669  return LONG2FIX(u);
3670  if (sign < 0 && BDIGIT_MSB(fixbuf[1]) == 0 &&
3671  NEGFIXABLE(-(BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)u))
3672  return LONG2FIX(-(BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)u);
3673  val = bignew((long)num_bdigits, 0 <= sign);
3674  MEMCPY(BDIGITS(val), fixbuf, BDIGIT, num_bdigits);
3675  }
3676 
3677  if ((flags & INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_BIGNUM) && sign != 0 &&
3678  bary_zero_p(BDIGITS(val), BIGNUM_LEN(val)))
3679  sign = 0;
3680  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(val, 0 <= sign);
3681 
3682  if (flags & INTEGER_PACK_FORCE_BIGNUM)
3683  return bigtrunc(val);
3684  return bignorm(val);
3685 }
3686 
3687 #define conv_digit(c) (ruby_digit36_to_number_table[(unsigned char)(c)])
3688 
3689 static void
3690 str2big_scan_digits(const char *s, const char *str, int base, int badcheck, size_t *num_digits_p, size_t *len_p)
3691 {
3692  char nondigit = 0;
3693  size_t num_digits = 0;
3694  const char *digits_start = str;
3695  const char *digits_end = str;
3696 
3697  int c;
3698 
3699  if (badcheck && *str == '_') goto bad;
3700 
3701  while ((c = *str++) != 0) {
3702  if (c == '_') {
3703  if (nondigit) {
3704  if (badcheck) goto bad;
3705  break;
3706  }
3707  nondigit = (char) c;
3708  continue;
3709  }
3710  else if ((c = conv_digit(c)) < 0) {
3711  break;
3712  }
3713  if (c >= base) break;
3714  nondigit = 0;
3715  num_digits++;
3716  digits_end = str;
3717  }
3718  if (badcheck) {
3719  str--;
3720  if (s+1 < str && str[-1] == '_') goto bad;
3721  while (*str && ISSPACE(*str)) str++;
3722  if (*str) {
3723  bad:
3724  rb_invalid_str(s, "Integer()");
3725  }
3726  }
3727  *num_digits_p = num_digits;
3728  *len_p = digits_end - digits_start;
3729 }
3730 
3731 static VALUE
3732 str2big_poweroftwo(
3733  int sign,
3734  const char *digits_start,
3735  const char *digits_end,
3736  size_t num_digits,
3737  int bits_per_digit)
3738 {
3739  BDIGIT *dp;
3740  BDIGIT_DBL dd;
3741  int numbits;
3742 
3743  size_t num_bdigits;
3744  const char *p;
3745  int c;
3746  VALUE z;
3747 
3748  num_bdigits = (num_digits / BITSPERDIG) * bits_per_digit + roomof((num_digits % BITSPERDIG) * bits_per_digit, BITSPERDIG);
3749  z = bignew(num_bdigits, sign);
3750  dp = BDIGITS(z);
3751  dd = 0;
3752  numbits = 0;
3753  for (p = digits_end; digits_start < p; p--) {
3754  if ((c = conv_digit(p[-1])) < 0)
3755  continue;
3756  dd |= (BDIGIT_DBL)c << numbits;
3757  numbits += bits_per_digit;
3758  if (BITSPERDIG <= numbits) {
3759  *dp++ = BIGLO(dd);
3760  dd = BIGDN(dd);
3761  numbits -= BITSPERDIG;
3762  }
3763  }
3764  if (numbits) {
3765  *dp++ = BIGLO(dd);
3766  }
3767  assert((size_t)(dp - BDIGITS(z)) == num_bdigits);
3768 
3769  return z;
3770 }
3771 
3772 static VALUE
3773 str2big_normal(
3774  int sign,
3775  const char *digits_start,
3776  const char *digits_end,
3777  size_t num_bdigits,
3778  int base)
3779 {
3780  size_t blen = 1;
3781  BDIGIT *zds;
3782  BDIGIT_DBL num;
3783 
3784  size_t i;
3785  const char *p;
3786  int c;
3787  VALUE z;
3788 
3789  z = bignew(num_bdigits, sign);
3790  zds = BDIGITS(z);
3791  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds, num_bdigits);
3792 
3793  for (p = digits_start; p < digits_end; p++) {
3794  if ((c = conv_digit(*p)) < 0)
3795  continue;
3796  num = c;
3797  i = 0;
3798  for (;;) {
3799  while (i<blen) {
3800  num += (BDIGIT_DBL)zds[i]*base;
3801  zds[i++] = BIGLO(num);
3802  num = BIGDN(num);
3803  }
3804  if (num) {
3805  blen++;
3806  continue;
3807  }
3808  break;
3809  }
3810  assert(blen <= num_bdigits);
3811  }
3812 
3813  return z;
3814 }
3815 
3816 static VALUE
3817 str2big_karatsuba(
3818  int sign,
3819  const char *digits_start,
3820  const char *digits_end,
3821  size_t num_digits,
3822  size_t num_bdigits,
3823  int digits_per_bdigits_dbl,
3824  int base)
3825 {
3826  VALUE powerv;
3827  size_t unit;
3828  VALUE tmpuv = 0;
3829  BDIGIT *uds, *vds, *tds;
3830  BDIGIT_DBL dd;
3831  BDIGIT_DBL current_base;
3832  int m;
3833  int power_level = 0;
3834 
3835  size_t i;
3836  const char *p;
3837  int c;
3838  VALUE z;
3839 
3840  uds = ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, tmpuv, 2*num_bdigits);
3841  vds = uds + num_bdigits;
3842 
3843  powerv = power_cache_get_power(base, power_level, NULL);
3844 
3845  i = 0;
3846  dd = 0;
3847  current_base = 1;
3848  m = digits_per_bdigits_dbl;
3849  if (num_digits < (size_t)m)
3850  m = (int)num_digits;
3851  for (p = digits_end; digits_start < p; p--) {
3852  if ((c = conv_digit(p[-1])) < 0)
3853  continue;
3854  dd = dd + c * current_base;
3855  current_base *= base;
3856  num_digits--;
3857  m--;
3858  if (m == 0) {
3859  uds[i++] = BIGLO(dd);
3860  uds[i++] = (BDIGIT)BIGDN(dd);
3861  dd = 0;
3862  m = digits_per_bdigits_dbl;
3863  if (num_digits < (size_t)m)
3864  m = (int)num_digits;
3865  current_base = 1;
3866  }
3867  }
3868  assert(i == num_bdigits);
3869  for (unit = 2; unit < num_bdigits; unit *= 2) {
3870  for (i = 0; i < num_bdigits; i += unit*2) {
3871  if (2*unit <= num_bdigits - i) {
3872  bary_mul(vds+i, unit*2, BDIGITS(powerv), BIGNUM_LEN(powerv), uds+i+unit, unit);
3873  bary_add(vds+i, unit*2, vds+i, unit*2, uds+i, unit);
3874  }
3875  else if (unit <= num_bdigits - i) {
3876  bary_mul(vds+i, num_bdigits-i, BDIGITS(powerv), BIGNUM_LEN(powerv), uds+i+unit, num_bdigits-(i+unit));
3877  bary_add(vds+i, num_bdigits-i, vds+i, num_bdigits-i, uds+i, unit);
3878  }
3879  else {
3880  MEMCPY(vds+i, uds+i, BDIGIT, num_bdigits-i);
3881  }
3882  }
3883  power_level++;
3884  powerv = power_cache_get_power(base, power_level, NULL);
3885  tds = vds;
3886  vds = uds;
3887  uds = tds;
3888  }
3889  BARY_TRUNC(uds, num_bdigits);
3890  z = bignew(num_bdigits, sign);
3891  MEMCPY(BDIGITS(z), uds, BDIGIT, num_bdigits);
3892 
3893  if (tmpuv)
3894  ALLOCV_END(tmpuv);
3895 
3896  return z;
3897 }
3898 
3899 #ifdef USE_GMP
3900 static VALUE
3901 str2big_gmp(
3902  int sign,
3903  const char *digits_start,
3904  const char *digits_end,
3905  size_t num_digits,
3906  size_t num_bdigits,
3907  int base)
3908 {
3909  const size_t nails = (sizeof(BDIGIT)-SIZEOF_BDIGIT)*CHAR_BIT;
3910  char *buf, *p;
3911  const char *q;
3912  VALUE tmps;
3913  mpz_t mz;
3914  VALUE z;
3915  BDIGIT *zds;
3916  size_t zn, count;
3917 
3918  buf = ALLOCV_N(char, tmps, num_digits+1);
3919  p = buf;
3920  for (q = digits_start; q < digits_end; q++) {
3921  if (conv_digit(*q) < 0)
3922  continue;
3923  *p++ = *q;
3924  }
3925  *p = '\0';
3926 
3927  mpz_init(mz);
3928  mpz_set_str(mz, buf, base);
3929  zn = num_bdigits;
3930  z = bignew(zn, sign);
3931  zds = BDIGITS(z);
3932  mpz_export(BDIGITS(z), &count, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, mz);
3933  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds+count, zn-count);
3934  mpz_clear(mz);
3935 
3936  if (tmps)
3937  ALLOCV_END(tmps);
3938 
3939  return z;
3940 }
3941 #endif
3942 
3943 VALUE
3944 rb_cstr_to_inum(const char *str, int base, int badcheck)
3945 {
3946  const char *s = str;
3947  char sign = 1;
3948  int c;
3949  VALUE z;
3950 
3951  int bits_per_digit;
3952 
3953  const char *digits_start, *digits_end;
3954  size_t num_digits;
3955  size_t num_bdigits;
3956  size_t len;
3957 
3958  if (!str) {
3959  if (badcheck) {
3960  bad:
3961  rb_invalid_str(s, "Integer()");
3962  }
3963  return INT2FIX(0);
3964  }
3965  while (ISSPACE(*str)) str++;
3966 
3967  if (str[0] == '+') {
3968  str++;
3969  }
3970  else if (str[0] == '-') {
3971  str++;
3972  sign = 0;
3973  }
3974  if (str[0] == '+' || str[0] == '-') {
3975  if (badcheck) goto bad;
3976  return INT2FIX(0);
3977  }
3978  if (base <= 0) {
3979  if (str[0] == '0') {
3980  switch (str[1]) {
3981  case 'x': case 'X':
3982  base = 16;
3983  str += 2;
3984  break;
3985  case 'b': case 'B':
3986  base = 2;
3987  str += 2;
3988  break;
3989  case 'o': case 'O':
3990  base = 8;
3991  str += 2;
3992  break;
3993  case 'd': case 'D':
3994  base = 10;
3995  str += 2;
3996  break;
3997  default:
3998  base = 8;
3999  }
4000  }
4001  else if (base < -1) {
4002  base = -base;
4003  }
4004  else {
4005  base = 10;
4006  }
4007  }
4008  else if (base == 2) {
4009  if (str[0] == '0' && (str[1] == 'b'||str[1] == 'B')) {
4010  str += 2;
4011  }
4012  }
4013  else if (base == 8) {
4014  if (str[0] == '0' && (str[1] == 'o'||str[1] == 'O')) {
4015  str += 2;
4016  }
4017  }
4018  else if (base == 10) {
4019  if (str[0] == '0' && (str[1] == 'd'||str[1] == 'D')) {
4020  str += 2;
4021  }
4022  }
4023  else if (base == 16) {
4024  if (str[0] == '0' && (str[1] == 'x'||str[1] == 'X')) {
4025  str += 2;
4026  }
4027  }
4028  if (base < 2 || 36 < base) {
4029  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid radix %d", base);
4030  }
4031  if (*str == '0') { /* squeeze preceding 0s */
4032  int us = 0;
4033  while ((c = *++str) == '0' || c == '_') {
4034  if (c == '_') {
4035  if (++us >= 2)
4036  break;
4037  }
4038  else {
4039  us = 0;
4040  }
4041  }
4042  if (!(c = *str) || ISSPACE(c)) --str;
4043  }
4044  c = *str;
4045  c = conv_digit(c);
4046  if (c < 0 || c >= base) {
4047  if (badcheck) goto bad;
4048  return INT2FIX(0);
4049  }
4050 
4051  bits_per_digit = bit_length(base-1);
4052  if (bits_per_digit * strlen(str) <= sizeof(long) * CHAR_BIT) {
4053  char *end;
4054  unsigned long val = STRTOUL(str, &end, base);
4055 
4056  if (str < end && *end == '_') goto bigparse;
4057  if (badcheck) {
4058  if (end == str) goto bad; /* no number */
4059  while (*end && ISSPACE(*end)) end++;
4060  if (*end) goto bad; /* trailing garbage */
4061  }
4062 
4063  if (POSFIXABLE(val)) {
4064  if (sign) return LONG2FIX(val);
4065  else {
4066  long result = -(long)val;
4067  return LONG2FIX(result);
4068  }
4069  }
4070  else {
4071  VALUE big = rb_uint2big(val);
4072  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(big, sign);
4073  return bignorm(big);
4074  }
4075  }
4076 
4077  bigparse:
4078  digits_start = str;
4079  str2big_scan_digits(s, str, base, badcheck, &num_digits, &len);
4080  digits_end = digits_start + len;
4081 
4082  if (POW2_P(base)) {
4083  z = str2big_poweroftwo(sign, digits_start, digits_end, num_digits,
4084  bits_per_digit);
4085  }
4086  else {
4087  int digits_per_bdigits_dbl;
4088  maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base, &digits_per_bdigits_dbl);
4089  num_bdigits = roomof(num_digits, digits_per_bdigits_dbl)*2;
4090 
4091 #ifdef USE_GMP
4092  if (GMP_STR2BIG_DIGITS < num_bdigits) {
4093  z = str2big_gmp(sign, digits_start, digits_end, num_digits,
4094  num_bdigits, base);
4095  }
4096  else
4097 #endif
4098  if (num_bdigits < KARATSUBA_MUL_DIGITS) {
4099  z = str2big_normal(sign, digits_start, digits_end,
4100  num_bdigits, base);
4101  }
4102  else {
4103  z = str2big_karatsuba(sign, digits_start, digits_end, num_digits,
4104  num_bdigits, digits_per_bdigits_dbl, base);
4105  }
4106  }
4107 
4108  return bignorm(z);
4109 }
4110 
4111 VALUE
4112 rb_str_to_inum(VALUE str, int base, int badcheck)
4113 {
4114  char *s;
4115  long len;
4116  VALUE v = 0;
4117  VALUE ret;
4118 
4119  StringValue(str);
4120  rb_must_asciicompat(str);
4121  if (badcheck) {
4122  s = StringValueCStr(str);
4123  }
4124  else {
4125  s = RSTRING_PTR(str);
4126  }
4127  if (s) {
4128  len = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4129  if (s[len]) { /* no sentinel somehow */
4130  char *p = ALLOCV(v, len+1);
4131 
4132  MEMCPY(p, s, char, len);
4133  p[len] = '\0';
4134  s = p;
4135  }
4136  }
4137  ret = rb_cstr_to_inum(s, base, badcheck);
4138  if (v)
4139  ALLOCV_END(v);
4140  return ret;
4141 }

4296 static VALUE
4297 rb_ull2big(unsigned LONG_LONG n)
4298 {
4299  long i;
4300  VALUE big = bignew(bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG_LONG), 1);
4301  BDIGIT *digits = BDIGITS(big);
4302 
4303 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG_LONG
4304  digits[0] = n;
4305 #else
4306  for (i = 0; i < bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG_LONG); i++) {
4307  digits[i] = BIGLO(n);
4308  n = BIGDN(n);
4309  }
4310 #endif
4311 
4312  i = bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG_LONG);
4313  while (i-- && !digits[i]) ;
4314  BIGNUM_SET_LEN(big, i+1);
4315  return big;
4316 }

4318 static VALUE
4319 rb_ll2big(LONG_LONG n)
4320 {
4321  long neg = 0;
4322  unsigned LONG_LONG u;
4323  VALUE big;
4324 
4325  if (n < 0) {
4326  u = 1 + (unsigned LONG_LONG)(-(n + 1)); /* u = -n avoiding overflow */
4327  neg = 1;
4328  }
4329  else {
4330  u = n;
4331  }
4332  big = rb_ull2big(u);
4333  if (neg) {
4334  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(big, 0);
4335  }
4336  return big;
4337 }

4361 VALUE
4362 rb_str2inum(VALUE str, int base)
4363 {
4364  return rb_str_to_inum(str, base, base==0);
4365 }
4366 
4367 static VALUE
4368 big_shift3(VALUE x, int lshift_p, size_t shift_numdigits, int shift_numbits)
4369 {
4370  BDIGIT *xds, *zds;
4371  long s1;
4372  int s2;
4373  VALUE z;
4374  long xn;
4375 
4376  if (lshift_p) {
4377  if (LONG_MAX < shift_numdigits) {
4378  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big number");
4379  }
4380  s1 = shift_numdigits;
4381  s2 = shift_numbits;
4382  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
4383  z = bignew(xn+s1+1, BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
4384  zds = BDIGITS(z);
4385  BDIGITS_ZERO(zds, s1);
4386  xds = BDIGITS(x);
4387  zds[xn+s1] = bary_small_lshift(zds+s1, xds, xn, s2);
4388  }
4389  else {
4390  long zn;
4391  BDIGIT hibitsx;
4392  if (LONG_MAX < shift_numdigits || (size_t)BIGNUM_LEN(x) <= shift_numdigits) {
4393  if (BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(x) ||
4394  bary_zero_p(BDIGITS(x), BIGNUM_LEN(x)))
4395  return INT2FIX(0);
4396  else
4397  return INT2FIX(-1);
4398  }
4399  s1 = shift_numdigits;
4400  s2 = shift_numbits;
4401  hibitsx = abs2twocomp(&x, &xn);
4402  xds = BDIGITS(x);
4403  if (xn <= s1) {
4404  return hibitsx ? INT2FIX(-1) : INT2FIX(0);
4405  }
4406  zn = xn - s1;
4407  z = bignew(zn, 0);
4408  zds = BDIGITS(z);
4409  bary_small_rshift(zds, xds+s1, zn, s2, hibitsx != 0 ? BDIGMAX : 0);
4410  twocomp2abs_bang(z, hibitsx != 0);
4411  }
4412  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
4413  return z;
4414 }
4415 
4416 static VALUE
4417 big_shift2(VALUE x, int lshift_p, VALUE y)
4418 {
4419  int sign;
4420  size_t lens[2];
4421  size_t shift_numdigits;
4422  int shift_numbits;
4423 
4424  assert(POW2_P(CHAR_BIT));
4425  assert(POW2_P(BITSPERDIG));
4426 
4427  if (BIGZEROP(x))
4428  return INT2FIX(0);
4429  sign = rb_integer_pack(y, lens, numberof(lens), sizeof(size_t), 0,
4430  INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST|INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER);
4431  if (sign < 0) {
4432  lshift_p = !lshift_p;
4433  sign = -sign;
4434  }
4435  if (lshift_p) {
4436  if (1 < sign || CHAR_BIT <= lens[1])
4437  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "shift width too big");
4438  }
4439  else {
4440  if (1 < sign || CHAR_BIT <= lens[1])
4441  return BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(x) ? INT2FIX(0) : INT2FIX(-1);
4442  }
4443  shift_numbits = (int)(lens[0] & (BITSPERDIG-1));
4444  shift_numdigits = (lens[0] >> bit_length(BITSPERDIG-1)) |
4445  (lens[1] << (CHAR_BIT*SIZEOF_SIZE_T - bit_length(BITSPERDIG-1)));
4446  return big_shift3(x, lshift_p, shift_numdigits, shift_numbits);
4447 }
4448 
4449 static VALUE
4450 big_lshift(VALUE x, unsigned long shift)
4451 {
4452  long s1 = shift/BITSPERDIG;
4453  int s2 = (int)(shift%BITSPERDIG);
4454  return big_shift3(x, 1, s1, s2);
4455 }
4456 
4457 static VALUE
4458 big_rshift(VALUE x, unsigned long shift)
4459 {
4460  long s1 = shift/BITSPERDIG;
4461  int s2 = (int)(shift%BITSPERDIG);
4462  return big_shift3(x, 0, s1, s2);
4463 }
4464 
4465 #define MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES (SIZEOF_SIZE_T * CHAR_BIT + 1)
4466 
4467 static VALUE base36_power_cache[35][MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES];
4468 static size_t base36_numdigits_cache[35][MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES];
4469 
4470 static void
4471 power_cache_init(void)
4472 {
4473  int i, j;
4474  for (i = 0; i < 35; ++i) {
4475  for (j = 0; j < MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES; ++j) {
4476  base36_power_cache[i][j] = Qnil;
4477  }
4478  }
4479 }
4480 
4481 static inline VALUE
4482 power_cache_get_power(int base, int power_level, size_t *numdigits_ret)
4483 {
4484  /*
4485  * MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES is big enough to that
4486  * base36_power_cache[base][MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES-1] fills whole memory.
4487  * So MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES <= power_level is not possible to calculate.
4488  *
4489  * number-of-bytes =
4490  * log256(base36_power_cache[base][MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES-1]) =
4491  * log256(maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base)**(2**(MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES-1))) =
4492  * log256(maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base)**(2**(SIZEOF_SIZE_T*CHAR_BIT))) =
4493  * (2**(SIZEOF_SIZE_T*CHAR_BIT))*log256(maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base)) =
4494  * (256**SIZEOF_SIZE_T)*log256(maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base)) >
4495  * (256**SIZEOF_SIZE_T)*(sizeof(BDIGIT_DBL)-1) >
4496  * 256**SIZEOF_SIZE_T
4497  */
4498  if (MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES <= power_level)
4499  rb_bug("too big power number requested: maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(%d)**(2**%d)", base, power_level);
4500 
4501  if (NIL_P(base36_power_cache[base - 2][power_level])) {
4502  VALUE power;
4503  size_t numdigits;
4504  if (power_level == 0) {
4505  int numdigits0;
4506  BDIGIT_DBL dd = maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base, &numdigits0);
4507  power = bignew(2, 1);
4508  bdigitdbl2bary(BDIGITS(power), 2, dd);
4509  numdigits = numdigits0;
4510  }
4511  else {
4512  power = bigtrunc(bigsq(power_cache_get_power(base, power_level - 1, &numdigits)));
4513  numdigits *= 2;
4514  }
4515  rb_obj_hide(power);
4516  base36_power_cache[base - 2][power_level] = power;
4517  base36_numdigits_cache[base - 2][power_level] = numdigits;
4518  rb_gc_register_mark_object(power);
4519  }
4520  if (numdigits_ret)
4521  *numdigits_ret = base36_numdigits_cache[base - 2][power_level];
4522  return base36_power_cache[base - 2][power_level];
4523 }
4524 
4525 struct big2str_struct {
4526  int negative;
4527  int base;
4528  BDIGIT_DBL hbase2;
4529  int hbase2_numdigits;
4530  VALUE result;
4531  char *ptr;
4532 };
4533 
4534 static void
4535 big2str_alloc(struct big2str_struct *b2s, size_t len)
4536 {
4537  if (LONG_MAX-1 < len)
4538  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big number");
4539  b2s->result = rb_usascii_str_new(0, (long)(len + 1)); /* plus one for sign */
4540  b2s->ptr = RSTRING_PTR(b2s->result);
4541  if (b2s->negative)
4542  *b2s->ptr++ = '-';
4543 }
4544 
4545 static void
4546 big2str_2bdigits(struct big2str_struct *b2s, BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, size_t taillen)
4547 {
4548  size_t j;
4549  BDIGIT_DBL num;
4550  char buf[SIZEOF_BDIGIT_DBL*CHAR_BIT], *p;
4551  int beginning = !b2s->ptr;
4552  size_t len = 0;
4553 
4554  assert(xn <= 2);
4555  num = bary2bdigitdbl(xds, xn);
4556 
4557  if (beginning) {
4558  if (num == 0)
4559  return;
4560  p = buf;
4561  j = sizeof(buf);
4562  do {
4563  p[--j] = ruby_digitmap[num % b2s->base];
4564  num /= b2s->base;
4565  } while (num);
4566  len = sizeof(buf) - j;
4567  big2str_alloc(b2s, len + taillen);
4568  MEMCPY(b2s->ptr, buf + j, char, len);
4569  }
4570  else {
4571  p = b2s->ptr;
4572  j = b2s->hbase2_numdigits;
4573  do {
4574  p[--j] = ruby_digitmap[num % b2s->base];
4575  num /= b2s->base;
4576  } while (j);
4577  len = b2s->hbase2_numdigits;
4578  }
4579  b2s->ptr += len;
4580 }
4581 
4582 static void
4583 big2str_karatsuba(struct big2str_struct *b2s, BDIGIT *xds, size_t xn, size_t wn,
4584  int power_level, size_t taillen)
4585 {
4586  VALUE b;
4587  size_t half_numdigits, lower_numdigits;
4588  int lower_power_level;
4589  size_t bn;
4590  const BDIGIT *bds;
4591  size_t len;
4592 
4593  /*
4594  * Precondition:
4595  * abs(x) < maxpow**(2**power_level)
4596  * where
4597  * maxpow = maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base, &numdigits)
4598  *
4599  * This function generates sequence of zeros, and then stringized abs(x) into b2s->ptr.
4600  *
4601  * b2s->ptr can be NULL.
4602  * It is allocated when the first character is generated via big2str_alloc.
4603  *
4604  * The prefix zeros should be generated if and only if b2s->ptr is not NULL.
4605  * When the zeros are generated, the zeros and abs(x) consists
4606  * numdigits*(2**power_level) characters at total.
4607  *
4608  * Note:
4609  * power_cache_get_power(base, power_level, &len) may not be cached yet. It should not be called.
4610  * power_cache_get_power(base, power_level-1, &len) should be cached already if 0 <= power_level-1.
4611  */
4612 
4613  if (xn == 0 || bary_zero_p(xds, xn)) {
4614  if (b2s->ptr) {
4615  /* When x is zero, power_cache_get_power(base, power_level) should be cached already. */
4616  power_cache_get_power(b2s->base, power_level, &len);
4617  memset(b2s->ptr, '0', len);
4618  b2s->ptr += len;
4619  }
4620  return;
4621  }
4622 
4623  if (power_level == 0) {
4624  big2str_2bdigits(b2s, xds, xn, taillen);
4625  return;
4626  }
4627 
4628  lower_power_level = power_level-1;
4629  b = power_cache_get_power(b2s->base, lower_power_level, &lower_numdigits);
4630  bn = BIGNUM_LEN(b);
4631  bds = BDIGITS(b);
4632 
4633  half_numdigits = lower_numdigits;
4634 
4635  while (0 < lower_power_level &&
4636  (xn < bn ||
4637  (xn == bn && bary_cmp(xds, xn, bds, bn) < 0))) {
4638  lower_power_level--;
4639  b = power_cache_get_power(b2s->base, lower_power_level, &lower_numdigits);
4640  bn = BIGNUM_LEN(b);
4641  bds = BDIGITS(b);
4642  }
4643 
4644  if (lower_power_level == 0 &&
4645  (xn < bn ||
4646  (xn == bn && bary_cmp(xds, xn, bds, bn) < 0))) {
4647  if (b2s->ptr) {
4648  len = half_numdigits * 2 - lower_numdigits;
4649  memset(b2s->ptr, '0', len);
4650  b2s->ptr += len;
4651  }
4652  big2str_2bdigits(b2s, xds, xn, taillen);
4653  }
4654  else {
4655  BDIGIT *qds, *rds;
4656  size_t qn, rn;
4657  BDIGIT *tds;
4658  int shift;
4659 
4660  if (lower_power_level != power_level-1 && b2s->ptr) {
4661  len = (half_numdigits - lower_numdigits) * 2;
4662  memset(b2s->ptr, '0', len);
4663  b2s->ptr += len;
4664  }
4665 
4666  shift = nlz(bds[bn-1]);
4667 
4668  qn = xn + BIGDIVREM_EXTRA_WORDS;
4669 
4670  if (shift == 0) {
4671  /* bigdivrem_restoring will not modify y.
4672  * So use bds directly. */
4673  tds = (BDIGIT *)bds;
4674  xds[xn] = 0;
4675  }
4676  else {
4677  /* bigdivrem_restoring will modify y.
4678  * So use temporary buffer. */
4679  tds = xds + qn;
4680  assert(qn + bn <= xn + wn);
4681  bary_small_lshift(tds, bds, bn, shift);
4682  xds[xn] = bary_small_lshift(xds, xds, xn, shift);
4683  }
4684 
4685  bigdivrem_restoring(xds, qn, tds, bn);
4686 
4687  rds = xds;
4688  rn = bn;
4689 
4690  qds = xds + bn;
4691  qn = qn - bn;
4692 
4693  if (shift) {
4694  bary_small_rshift(rds, rds, rn, shift, 0);
4695  }
4696 
4697  BARY_TRUNC(qds, qn);
4698  assert(qn <= bn);
4699  big2str_karatsuba(b2s, qds, qn, xn+wn - (rn+qn), lower_power_level, lower_numdigits+taillen);
4700  BARY_TRUNC(rds, rn);
4701  big2str_karatsuba(b2s, rds, rn, xn+wn - rn, lower_power_level, taillen);
4702  }
4703 }
4704 
4705 static VALUE
4706 big2str_base_poweroftwo(VALUE x, int base)
4707 {
4708  int word_numbits = ffs(base) - 1;
4709  size_t numwords;
4710  VALUE result;
4711  char *ptr;
4712  numwords = rb_absint_numwords(x, word_numbits, NULL);
4713  if (BIGNUM_NEGATIVE_P(x)) {
4714  if (LONG_MAX-1 < numwords)
4715  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big number");
4716  result = rb_usascii_str_new(0, 1+numwords);
4717  ptr = RSTRING_PTR(result);
4718  *ptr++ = BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(x) ? '+' : '-';
4719  }
4720  else {
4721  if (LONG_MAX < numwords)
4722  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "too big number");
4723  result = rb_usascii_str_new(0, numwords);
4724  ptr = RSTRING_PTR(result);
4725  }
4726  rb_integer_pack(x, ptr, numwords, 1, CHAR_BIT-word_numbits,
4727  INTEGER_PACK_BIG_ENDIAN);
4728  while (0 < numwords) {
4729  *ptr = ruby_digitmap[*(unsigned char *)ptr];
4730  ptr++;
4731  numwords--;
4732  }
4733  return result;
4734 }
4735 
4736 VALUE
4737 rb_big2str_poweroftwo(VALUE x, int base)
4738 {
4739  return big2str_base_poweroftwo(x, base);
4740 }
4741 
4742 static VALUE
4743 big2str_generic(VALUE x, int base)
4744 {
4745  BDIGIT *xds;
4746  size_t xn;
4747  struct big2str_struct b2s_data;
4748  int power_level;
4749  VALUE power;
4750 
4751  xds = BDIGITS(x);
4752  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
4753  BARY_TRUNC(xds, xn);
4754 
4755  if (xn == 0) {
4756  return rb_usascii_str_new2("0");
4757  }
4758 
4759  if (base < 2 || 36 < base)
4760  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid radix %d", base);
4761 
4762  if (xn >= LONG_MAX/BITSPERDIG) {
4763  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "bignum too big to convert into `string'");
4764  }
4765 
4766  power_level = 0;
4767  power = power_cache_get_power(base, power_level, NULL);
4768  while (power_level < MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES &&
4769  (size_t)BIGNUM_LEN(power) <= (xn+1)/2) {
4770  power_level++;
4771  power = power_cache_get_power(base, power_level, NULL);
4772  }
4773  assert(power_level != MAX_BASE36_POWER_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4774 
4775  if ((size_t)BIGNUM_LEN(power) <= xn) {
4776  /*
4777  * This increment guarantees x < power_cache_get_power(base, power_level)
4778  * without invoking it actually.
4779  * (power_cache_get_power(base, power_level) can be slow and not used
4780  * in big2str_karatsuba.)
4781  *
4782  * Although it is possible that x < power_cache_get_power(base, power_level-1),
4783  * it is no problem because big2str_karatsuba checks it and
4784  * doesn't affect the result when b2s_data.ptr is NULL.
4785  */
4786  power_level++;
4787  }
4788 
4789  b2s_data.negative = BIGNUM_NEGATIVE_P(x);
4790  b2s_data.base = base;
4791  b2s_data.hbase2 = maxpow_in_bdigit_dbl(base, &b2s_data.hbase2_numdigits);
4792 
4793  b2s_data.result = Qnil;
4794  b2s_data.ptr = NULL;
4795 
4796  if (power_level == 0) {
4797  big2str_2bdigits(&b2s_data, xds, xn, 0);
4798  }
4799  else {
4800  VALUE tmpw = 0;
4801  BDIGIT *wds;
4802  size_t wn;
4803  wn = power_level * BIGDIVREM_EXTRA_WORDS + BIGNUM_LEN(power);
4804  wds = ALLOCV_N(BDIGIT, tmpw, xn + wn);
4805  MEMCPY(wds, xds, BDIGIT, xn);
4806  big2str_karatsuba(&b2s_data, wds, xn, wn, power_level, 0);
4807  if (tmpw)
4808  ALLOCV_END(tmpw);
4809  }
4810  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
4811 
4812  *b2s_data.ptr = '\0';
4813  rb_str_resize(b2s_data.result, (long)(b2s_data.ptr - RSTRING_PTR(b2s_data.result)));
4814 
4815  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
4816  return b2s_data.result;
4817 }
4818 
4819 VALUE
4820 rb_big2str_generic(VALUE x, int base)
4821 {
4822  return big2str_generic(x, base);
4823 }

4825 #ifdef USE_GMP
4826 VALUE
4827 big2str_gmp(VALUE x, int base)
4828 {
4829  const size_t nails = (sizeof(BDIGIT)-SIZEOF_BDIGIT)*CHAR_BIT;
4830  mpz_t mx;
4831  size_t size;
4832  VALUE str;
4833  BDIGIT *xds = BDIGITS(x);
4834  size_t xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
4835 
4836  mpz_init(mx);
4837  mpz_import(mx, xn, -1, sizeof(BDIGIT), 0, nails, xds);
4838 
4839  size = mpz_sizeinbase(mx, base);
4840 
4841  if (BIGNUM_NEGATIVE_P(x)) {
4842  mpz_neg(mx, mx);
4843  str = rb_usascii_str_new(0, size+1);
4844  }
4845  else {
4846  str = rb_usascii_str_new(0, size);
4847  }
4848  mpz_get_str(RSTRING_PTR(str), base, mx);
4849  mpz_clear(mx);
4850 
4851  if (RSTRING_PTR(str)[RSTRING_LEN(str)-1] == '\0') {
4852  rb_str_set_len(str, RSTRING_LEN(str)-1);
4853  }
4854 
4855  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
4856  return str;
4857 }

4859 VALUE

4866 static VALUE
4867 rb_big2str1(VALUE x, int base)
4868 {
4869  BDIGIT *xds;
4870  size_t xn;
4871 
4872  if (FIXNUM_P(x)) {
4873  return rb_fix2str(x, base);
4874  }
4875 
4876  bigtrunc(x);
4877  xds = BDIGITS(x);
4878  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
4879  BARY_TRUNC(xds, xn);
4880 
4881  if (xn == 0) {
4882  return rb_usascii_str_new2("0");
4883  }
4884 
4885  if (base < 2 || 36 < base)
4886  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid radix %d", base);
4887 
4888  if (xn >= LONG_MAX/BITSPERDIG) {
4889  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "bignum too big to convert into `string'");
4890  }
4891 
4892  if (POW2_P(base)) {
4893  /* base == 2 || base == 4 || base == 8 || base == 16 || base == 32 */
4894  return big2str_base_poweroftwo(x, base);
4895  }
4896 
4897 #ifdef USE_GMP
4898  if (GMP_BIG2STR_DIGITS < xn) {
4899  return big2str_gmp(x, base);
4900  }
4901 #endif
4902 
4903  return big2str_generic(x, base);
4904 }
4905 
4906 VALUE
4907 rb_big2str(VALUE x, int base)
4908 {
4909  return rb_big2str1(x, base);
4910 }
4911 
4912 /*
4913  * call-seq:
4914  * big.to_s(base=10) -> string
4915  *
4916  * Returns a string containing the representation of <i>big</i> radix
4917  * <i>base</i> (2 through 36).
4918  *
4919  * 12345654321.to_s #=> "12345654321"
4920  * 12345654321.to_s(2) #=> "1011011111110110111011110000110001"
4921  * 12345654321.to_s(8) #=> "133766736061"
4922  * 12345654321.to_s(16) #=> "2dfdbbc31"
4923  * 78546939656932.to_s(36) #=> "rubyrules"
4924  */
4925 
4926 static VALUE
4927 rb_big_to_s(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE x)
4928 {
4929  int base;
4930 
4931  if (argc == 0) base = 10;
4932  else {
4933  VALUE b;
4934 
4935  rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "01", &b);
4936  base = NUM2INT(b);
4937  }
4938  return rb_big2str(x, base);
4939 }
4940 
4941 static unsigned long
4942 big2ulong(VALUE x, const char *type)
4943 {
4944  size_t len = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
4945  unsigned long num;
4946  BDIGIT *ds;
4947 
4948  if (len == 0)
4949  return 0;
4950  if (BIGSIZE(x) > sizeof(long)) {
4951  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "bignum too big to convert into `%s'", type);
4952  }
4953  ds = BDIGITS(x);
4954 #if SIZEOF_LONG <= SIZEOF_BDIGIT
4955  num = (unsigned long)ds[0];
4956 #else
4957  num = 0;
4958  while (len--) {
4959  num <<= BITSPERDIG;
4960  num += (unsigned long)ds[len]; /* overflow is already checked */
4961  }
4962 #endif
4963  return num;
4964 }
4965 
4966 unsigned long
4967 rb_big2ulong(VALUE x)
4968 {
4969  unsigned long num = big2ulong(x, "unsigned long");
4970 
4971  if (BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(x)) {
4972  return num;
4973  }
4974  else {
4975  if (num <= LONG_MAX)
4976  return -(long)num;
4977  if (num == 1+(unsigned long)(-(LONG_MIN+1)))
4978  return LONG_MIN;
4979  }
4980  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "bignum out of range of unsigned long");
4981 }
4982 
4983 long
4984 rb_big2long(VALUE x)
4985 {
4986  unsigned long num = big2ulong(x, "long");
4987 
4988  if (BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(x)) {
4989  if (num <= LONG_MAX)
4990  return num;
4991  }
4992  else {
4993  if (num <= LONG_MAX)
4994  return -(long)num;
4995  if (num == 1+(unsigned long)(-(LONG_MIN+1)))
4996  return LONG_MIN;
4997  }
4998  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "bignum too big to convert into `long'");
4999 }

5009

5011  return 0;

5063 static VALUE
5064 dbl2big(double d)
5065 {
5066  long i = 0;
5067  BDIGIT c;
5068  BDIGIT *digits;
5069  VALUE z;
5070  double u = (d < 0)?-d:d;
5071 
5072  if (isinf(d)) {
5073  rb_raise(rb_eFloatDomainError, d < 0 ? "-Infinity" : "Infinity");
5074  }
5075  if (isnan(d)) {
5076  rb_raise(rb_eFloatDomainError, "NaN");
5077  }
5078 
5079  while (1.0 <= u) {
5080  u /= (double)(BIGRAD);
5081  i++;
5082  }
5083  z = bignew(i, d>=0);
5084  digits = BDIGITS(z);
5085  while (i--) {
5086  u *= BIGRAD;
5087  c = (BDIGIT)u;
5088  u -= c;
5089  digits[i] = c;
5090  }
5091 
5092  return z;
5093 }
5094 
5095 VALUE
5096 rb_dbl2big(double d)
5097 {
5098  return bignorm(dbl2big(d));
5099 }
5100 
5101 static double
5102 big2dbl(VALUE x)
5103 {
5104  double d = 0.0;
5105  long i = (bigtrunc(x), BIGNUM_LEN(x)), lo = 0, bits;
5106  BDIGIT *ds = BDIGITS(x), dl;
5107 
5108  if (i) {
5109  bits = i * BITSPERDIG - nlz(ds[i-1]);
5110  if (bits > DBL_MANT_DIG+DBL_MAX_EXP) {
5111  d = HUGE_VAL;
5112  }
5113  else {
5114  if (bits > DBL_MANT_DIG+1)
5115  lo = (bits -= DBL_MANT_DIG+1) / BITSPERDIG;
5116  else
5117  bits = 0;
5118  while (--i > lo) {
5119  d = ds[i] + BIGRAD*d;
5120  }
5121  dl = ds[i];
5122  if (bits && (dl & ((BDIGIT)1 << (bits %= BITSPERDIG)))) {
5123  int carry = (dl & ~(BDIGMAX << bits)) != 0;
5124  if (!carry) {
5125  while (i-- > 0) {
5126  carry = ds[i] != 0;
5127  if (carry) break;
5128  }
5129  }
5130  if (carry) {
5131  dl &= BDIGMAX << bits;
5132  dl = BIGLO(dl + ((BDIGIT)1 << bits));
5133  if (!dl) d += 1;
5134  }
5135  }
5136  d = dl + BIGRAD*d;
5137  if (lo) {
5138  if (lo > INT_MAX / BITSPERDIG)
5139  d = HUGE_VAL;
5140  else if (lo < INT_MIN / BITSPERDIG)
5141  d = 0.0;
5142  else
5143  d = ldexp(d, (int)(lo * BITSPERDIG));
5144  }
5145  }
5146  }
5147  if (!BIGNUM_SIGN(x)) d = -d;
5148  return d;
5149 }
5150 
5151 double
5152 rb_big2dbl(VALUE x)
5153 {
5154  double d = big2dbl(x);
5155 
5156  if (isinf(d)) {
5157  rb_warning("Bignum out of Float range");
5158  if (d < 0.0)
5159  d = -HUGE_VAL;
5160  else
5161  d = HUGE_VAL;
5162  }
5163  return d;
5164 }

5166 /*
5167  * call-seq:
5168  * big.to_f -> float
5169  *
5170  * Converts <i>big</i> to a <code>Float</code>. If <i>big</i> doesn't
5171  * fit in a <code>Float</code>, the result is infinity.
5172  *
5173  */
5174 
5175 static VALUE
5176 rb_big_to_f(VALUE x)
5177 {
5178  return DBL2NUM(rb_big2dbl(x));
5179 }
5180 
5181 VALUE
5182 rb_integer_float_cmp(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5183 {
5184  double yd = RFLOAT_VALUE(y);
5185  double yi, yf;
5186  VALUE rel;
5187 
5188  if (isnan(yd))
5189  return Qnil;
5190  if (isinf(yd)) {
5191  if (yd > 0.0) return INT2FIX(-1);
5192  else return INT2FIX(1);
5193  }
5194  yf = modf(yd, &yi);
5195  if (FIXNUM_P(x)) {
5196 #if SIZEOF_LONG * CHAR_BIT < DBL_MANT_DIG /* assume FLT_RADIX == 2 */
5197  double xd = (double)FIX2LONG(x);
5198  if (xd < yd)
5199  return INT2FIX(-1);
5200  if (xd > yd)
5201  return INT2FIX(1);
5202  return INT2FIX(0);
5203 #else
5204  long xn, yn;
5205  if (yi < FIXNUM_MIN)
5206  return INT2FIX(1);
5207  if (FIXNUM_MAX+1 <= yi)
5208  return INT2FIX(-1);
5209  xn = FIX2LONG(x);
5210  yn = (long)yi;
5211  if (xn < yn)
5212  return INT2FIX(-1);
5213  if (xn > yn)
5214  return INT2FIX(1);
5215  if (yf < 0.0)
5216  return INT2FIX(1);
5217  if (0.0 < yf)
5218  return INT2FIX(-1);
5219  return INT2FIX(0);
5220 #endif
5221  }
5222  y = rb_dbl2big(yi);
5223  rel = rb_big_cmp(x, y);
5224  if (yf == 0.0 || rel != INT2FIX(0))
5225  return rel;
5226  if (yf < 0.0)
5227  return INT2FIX(1);
5228  return INT2FIX(-1);
5229 }
5230 
5231 VALUE
5232 rb_integer_float_eq(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5233 {
5234  double yd = RFLOAT_VALUE(y);
5235  double yi, yf;
5236 
5237  if (isnan(yd) || isinf(yd))
5238  return Qfalse;
5239  yf = modf(yd, &yi);
5240  if (yf != 0)
5241  return Qfalse;
5242  if (FIXNUM_P(x)) {
5243 #if SIZEOF_LONG * CHAR_BIT < DBL_MANT_DIG /* assume FLT_RADIX == 2 */
5244  double xd = (double)FIX2LONG(x);
5245  if (xd != yd)
5246  return Qfalse;
5247  return Qtrue;
5248 #else
5249  long xn, yn;
5250  if (yi < LONG_MIN || LONG_MAX < yi)
5251  return Qfalse;
5252  xn = FIX2LONG(x);
5253  yn = (long)yi;
5254  if (xn != yn)
5255  return Qfalse;
5256  return Qtrue;
5257 #endif
5258  }
5259  y = rb_dbl2big(yi);
5260  return rb_big_eq(x, y);
5261 }
5262 
5263 /*
5264  * call-seq:
5265  * big <=> numeric -> -1, 0, +1 or nil
5266  *
5267  * Comparison---Returns -1, 0, or +1 depending on whether +big+ is
5268  * less than, equal to, or greater than +numeric+. This is the
5269  * basis for the tests in Comparable.
5270  *
5271  * +nil+ is returned if the two values are incomparable.
5272  *
5273  */
5274 
5275 VALUE
5276 rb_big_cmp(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5277 {
5278  int cmp;
5279 
5280  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
5281  x = bignorm(x);
5282  if (FIXNUM_P(x)) {
5283  if (FIX2LONG(x) > FIX2LONG(y)) return INT2FIX(1);
5284  if (FIX2LONG(x) < FIX2LONG(y)) return INT2FIX(-1);
5285  return INT2FIX(0);
5286  }
5287  else {
5288  if (BIGNUM_NEGATIVE_P(x)) return INT2FIX(-1);
5289  return INT2FIX(1);
5290  }
5291  }
5292  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
5293  }
5294  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
5295  return rb_integer_float_cmp(x, y);
5296  }
5297  else {
5298  return rb_num_coerce_cmp(x, y, rb_intern("<=>"));
5299  }
5300 
5301  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(x) > BIGNUM_SIGN(y)) return INT2FIX(1);
5302  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(x) < BIGNUM_SIGN(y)) return INT2FIX(-1);
5303 
5304  cmp = bary_cmp(BDIGITS(x), BIGNUM_LEN(x), BDIGITS(y), BIGNUM_LEN(y));
5305  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(x))
5306  return INT2FIX(cmp);
5307  else
5308  return INT2FIX(-cmp);
5309 }
5310 
5311 enum big_op_t {
5312  big_op_gt,
5313  big_op_ge,
5314  big_op_lt,
5315  big_op_le
5316 };
5317 
5318 static VALUE
5319 big_op(VALUE x, VALUE y, enum big_op_t op)
5320 {
5321  VALUE rel;
5322  int n;
5323 
5324  if (FIXNUM_P(y) || RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
5325  rel = rb_big_cmp(x, y);
5326  }
5327  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
5328  rel = rb_integer_float_cmp(x, y);
5329  }
5330  else {
5331  ID id = 0;
5332  switch (op) {
5333  case big_op_gt: id = '>'; break;
5334  case big_op_ge: id = rb_intern(">="); break;
5335  case big_op_lt: id = '<'; break;
5336  case big_op_le: id = rb_intern("<="); break;
5337  }
5338  return rb_num_coerce_relop(x, y, id);
5339  }
5340 
5341  if (NIL_P(rel)) return Qfalse;
5342  n = FIX2INT(rel);
5343 
5344  switch (op) {
5345  case big_op_gt: return n > 0 ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
5346  case big_op_ge: return n >= 0 ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
5347  case big_op_lt: return n < 0 ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
5348  case big_op_le: return n <= 0 ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
5349  }
5350  return Qundef;
5351 }
5352 
5353 /*
5354  * call-seq:
5355  * big > real -> true or false
5356  *
5357  * Returns <code>true</code> if the value of <code>big</code> is
5358  * greater than that of <code>real</code>.
5359  */
5360 
5361 static VALUE
5362 big_gt(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5363 {
5364  return big_op(x, y, big_op_gt);
5365 }
5366 
5367 /*
5368  * call-seq:
5369  * big >= real -> true or false
5370  *
5371  * Returns <code>true</code> if the value of <code>big</code> is
5372  * greater than or equal to that of <code>real</code>.
5373  */
5374 
5375 static VALUE
5376 big_ge(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5377 {
5378  return big_op(x, y, big_op_ge);
5379 }
5380 
5381 /*
5382  * call-seq:
5383  * big < real -> true or false
5384  *
5385  * Returns <code>true</code> if the value of <code>big</code> is
5386  * less than that of <code>real</code>.
5387  */

5390 big_lt(VALUE x, VALUE y)

5393 }
5394 
5395 /*
5396  * call-seq:
5397  * big <= real -> true or false
5398  *
5399  * Returns <code>true</code> if the value of <code>big</code> is
5400  * less than or equal to that of <code>real</code>.
5401  */
5402

5404 big_le(VALUE x, VALUE y)

5406  return big_op(x, y, big_op_le);

5408 
5409 /*
5410  * call-seq:
5411  * big == obj -> true or false
5412  *
5413  * Returns <code>true</code> only if <i>obj</i> has the same value
5414  * as <i>big</i>. Contrast this with <code>Bignum#eql?</code>, which
5415  * requires <i>obj</i> to be a <code>Bignum</code>.
5416  *
5417  * 68719476736 == 68719476736.0 #=> true
5418  */
5419 
5420 VALUE
5421 rb_big_eq(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5422 {
5423  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
5424  if (bignorm(x) == y) return Qtrue;
5425  y = rb_int2big(FIX2LONG(y));
5426  }
5427  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
5428  }
5429  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
5430  return rb_integer_float_eq(x, y);
5431  }
5432  else {
5433  return rb_equal(y, x);
5434  }
5435  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(x) != BIGNUM_SIGN(y)) return Qfalse;
5436  if (BIGNUM_LEN(x) != BIGNUM_LEN(y)) return Qfalse;
5437  if (MEMCMP(BDIGITS(x),BDIGITS(y),BDIGIT,BIGNUM_LEN(y)) != 0) return Qfalse;
5438  return Qtrue;
5439 }
5440 
5441 /*
5442  * call-seq:
5443  * big.eql?(obj) -> true or false
5444  *
5445  * Returns <code>true</code> only if <i>obj</i> is a
5446  * <code>Bignum</code> with the same value as <i>big</i>. Contrast this
5447  * with <code>Bignum#==</code>, which performs type conversions.
5448  *
5449  * 68719476736.eql?(68719476736.0) #=> false
5450  */
5451 
5452 VALUE
5453 rb_big_eql(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5454 {
5455  if (!RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) return Qfalse;
5456  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(x) != BIGNUM_SIGN(y)) return Qfalse;
5457  if (BIGNUM_LEN(x) != BIGNUM_LEN(y)) return Qfalse;
5458  if (MEMCMP(BDIGITS(x),BDIGITS(y),BDIGIT,BIGNUM_LEN(y)) != 0) return Qfalse;
5459  return Qtrue;
5460 }
5461 
5462 /*
5463  * call-seq:
5464  * -big -> integer
5465  *
5466  * Unary minus (returns an integer whose value is 0-big)
5467  */
5468 
5469 VALUE
5470 rb_big_uminus(VALUE x)
5471 {
5472  VALUE z = rb_big_clone(x);
5473 
5474  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(z, !BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5475 
5476  return bignorm(z);
5477 }
5478 
5479 /*
5480  * call-seq:
5481  * ~big -> integer
5482  *
5483  * Inverts the bits in big. As Bignums are conceptually infinite
5484  * length, the result acts as if it had an infinite number of one
5485  * bits to the left. In hex representations, this is displayed
5486  * as two periods to the left of the digits.
5487  *
5488  * sprintf("%X", ~0x1122334455) #=> "..FEEDDCCBBAA"
5489  */
5490 
5491 static VALUE
5492 rb_big_neg(VALUE x)
5493 {
5494  VALUE z = rb_big_clone(x);
5495  BDIGIT *ds = BDIGITS(z);
5496  long n = BIGNUM_LEN(z);
5497 
5498  if (!n) return INT2FIX(-1);
5499 
5500  if (BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(z)) {
5501  if (bary_add_one(ds, n)) {
5502  big_extend_carry(z);
5503  }
5504  BIGNUM_SET_NEGATIVE_SIGN(z);
5505  }
5506  else {
5507  bary_neg(ds, n);
5508  if (bary_add_one(ds, n))
5509  return INT2FIX(-1);
5510  bary_neg(ds, n);
5511  BIGNUM_SET_POSITIVE_SIGN(z);
5512  }
5513 
5514  return bignorm(z);
5515 }
5516 
5517 static VALUE
5518 bigsub(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5519 {
5520  VALUE z;
5521  BDIGIT *xds, *yds, *zds;
5522  long xn, yn, zn;
5523 
5524  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
5525  yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y);
5526  zn = xn < yn ? yn : xn;
5527 
5528  z = bignew(zn, 1);
5529 
5530  xds = BDIGITS(x);
5531  yds = BDIGITS(y);
5532  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5533 
5534  if (bary_sub(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn)) {
5535  bary_2comp(zds, zn);
5536  BIGNUM_SET_NEGATIVE_SIGN(z);
5537  }
5538 
5539  return z;
5540 }

5542 static VALUE bigadd_int(VALUE x, long y);
5543 
5544 static VALUE
5545 bigsub_int(VALUE x, long y0)
5546 {
5547  VALUE z;
5548  BDIGIT *xds, *zds;
5549  long xn, zn;
5550  BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED num;
5551  long i, y;
5552 
5553  y = y0;
5554  xds = BDIGITS(x);
5555  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
5556 
5557  if (xn == 0)
5558  return LONG2NUM(-y0);
5559 
5560  zn = xn;
5561 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
5562  if (zn < bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG))
5563  zn = bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG);
5564 #endif
5565  z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5566  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5567 
5568 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
5569  assert(xn == zn);
5570  num = (BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)xds[0] - y;
5571  if (xn == 1 && num < 0) {
5572  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(z, !BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5573  zds[0] = (BDIGIT)-num;
5574  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
5575  return bignorm(z);
5576  }
5577  zds[0] = BIGLO(num);
5578  num = BIGDN(num);
5579  i = 1;
5580  if (i < xn)
5581  goto y_is_zero_x;
5582  goto finish;
5583 #else
5584  num = 0;
5585  for (i=0; i < xn; i++) {
5586  if (y == 0) goto y_is_zero_x;
5587  num += (BDIGIT_DBL_SIGNED)xds[i] - BIGLO(y);
5588  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5589  num = BIGDN(num);
5590  y = BIGDN(y);
5591  }
5592  for (; i < zn; i++) {
5593  if (y == 0) goto y_is_zero_z;
5594  num -= BIGLO(y);
5595  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5596  num = BIGDN(num);
5597  y = BIGDN(y);
5598  }
5599  goto finish;
5600 #endif
5601 
5602  for (; i < xn; i++) {
5603  y_is_zero_x:
5604  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero_x;
5605  num += xds[i];
5606  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5607  num = BIGDN(num);
5608  }
5609 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
5610  for (; i < zn; i++) {
5611  y_is_zero_z:
5612  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero_z;
5613  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5614  num = BIGDN(num);
5615  }
5616 #endif
5617  goto finish;
5618 
5619  for (; i < xn; i++) {
5620  num_is_zero_x:
5621  zds[i] = xds[i];
5622  }
5623 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
5624  for (; i < zn; i++) {
5625  num_is_zero_z:
5626  zds[i] = 0;
5627  }
5628 #endif
5629  goto finish;
5630 
5631  finish:
5632  assert(num == 0 || num == -1);
5633  if (num < 0) {
5634  get2comp(z);
5635  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(z, !BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5636  }
5637  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
5638  return bignorm(z);
5639 }
5640 
5641 static VALUE
5642 bigadd_int(VALUE x, long y)
5643 {
5644  VALUE z;
5645  BDIGIT *xds, *zds;
5646  long xn, zn;
5647  BDIGIT_DBL num;
5648  long i;
5649 
5650  xds = BDIGITS(x);
5651  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
5652 
5653  if (xn == 0)
5654  return LONG2NUM(y);
5655 
5656  zn = xn;
5657 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
5658  if (zn < bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG))
5659  zn = bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG);
5660 #endif
5661  zn++;
5662 
5663  z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5664  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5665 
5666 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
5667  num = (BDIGIT_DBL)xds[0] + y;
5668  zds[0] = BIGLO(num);
5669  num = BIGDN(num);
5670  i = 1;
5671  if (i < xn)
5672  goto y_is_zero_x;
5673  goto y_is_zero_z;
5674 #else
5675  num = 0;
5676  for (i=0; i < xn; i++) {
5677  if (y == 0) goto y_is_zero_x;
5678  num += (BDIGIT_DBL)xds[i] + BIGLO(y);
5679  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5680  num = BIGDN(num);
5681  y = BIGDN(y);
5682  }
5683  for (; i < zn; i++) {
5684  if (y == 0) goto y_is_zero_z;
5685  num += BIGLO(y);
5686  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5687  num = BIGDN(num);
5688  y = BIGDN(y);
5689  }
5690  goto finish;
5691 
5692 #endif
5693 
5694  for (;i < xn; i++) {
5695  y_is_zero_x:
5696  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero_x;
5697  num += (BDIGIT_DBL)xds[i];
5698  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5699  num = BIGDN(num);
5700  }
5701  for (; i < zn; i++) {
5702  y_is_zero_z:
5703  if (num == 0) goto num_is_zero_z;
5704  zds[i] = BIGLO(num);
5705  num = BIGDN(num);
5706  }
5707  goto finish;
5708 
5709  for (;i < xn; i++) {
5710  num_is_zero_x:
5711  zds[i] = xds[i];
5712  }
5713  for (; i < zn; i++) {
5714  num_is_zero_z:
5715  zds[i] = 0;
5716  }
5717  goto finish;
5718 
5719  finish:
5720  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
5721  return bignorm(z);
5722 }
5723 
5724 static VALUE
5725 bigadd(VALUE x, VALUE y, int sign)
5726 {
5727  VALUE z;
5728  size_t len;
5729 
5730  sign = (sign == BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
5731  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(x) != sign) {
5732  if (sign) return bigsub(y, x);
5733  return bigsub(x, y);
5734  }
5735 
5736  if (BIGNUM_LEN(x) > BIGNUM_LEN(y)) {
5737  len = BIGNUM_LEN(x) + 1;
5738  }
5739  else {
5740  len = BIGNUM_LEN(y) + 1;
5741  }
5742  z = bignew(len, sign);
5743 
5744  bary_add(BDIGITS(z), BIGNUM_LEN(z),
5745  BDIGITS(x), BIGNUM_LEN(x),
5746  BDIGITS(y), BIGNUM_LEN(y));
5747 
5748  return z;
5749 }
5750 
5751 /*
5752  * call-seq:
5753  * big + other -> Numeric
5754  *
5755  * Adds big and other, returning the result.
5756  */
5757 
5758 VALUE
5759 rb_big_plus(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5760 {
5761  long n;
5762 
5763  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
5764  n = FIX2LONG(y);
5765  if ((n > 0) != BIGNUM_SIGN(x)) {
5766  if (n < 0) {
5767  n = -n;
5768  }
5769  return bigsub_int(x, n);
5770  }
5771  if (n < 0) {
5772  n = -n;
5773  }
5774  return bigadd_int(x, n);
5775  }
5776  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
5777  return bignorm(bigadd(x, y, 1));
5778  }
5779  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
5780  return DBL2NUM(rb_big2dbl(x) + RFLOAT_VALUE(y));
5781  }
5782  else {
5783  return rb_num_coerce_bin(x, y, '+');
5784  }
5785 }
5786 
5787 /*
5788  * call-seq:
5789  * big - other -> Numeric
5790  *
5791  * Subtracts other from big, returning the result.
5792  */
5793 
5794 VALUE
5795 rb_big_minus(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5796 {
5797  long n;
5798 
5799  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
5800  n = FIX2LONG(y);
5801  if ((n > 0) != BIGNUM_SIGN(x)) {
5802  if (n < 0) {
5803  n = -n;
5804  }
5805  return bigadd_int(x, n);
5806  }
5807  if (n < 0) {
5808  n = -n;
5809  }
5810  return bigsub_int(x, n);
5811  }
5812  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
5813  return bignorm(bigadd(x, y, 0));
5814  }
5815  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
5816  return DBL2NUM(rb_big2dbl(x) - RFLOAT_VALUE(y));
5817  }
5818  else {
5819  return rb_num_coerce_bin(x, y, '-');
5820  }
5821 }
5822 
5823 static VALUE
5824 bigsq(VALUE x)
5825 {
5826  long xn, zn;
5827  VALUE z;
5828  BDIGIT *xds, *zds;
5829 
5830  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
5831  zn = 2 * xn;
5832 
5833  z = bignew(zn, 1);
5834 
5835  xds = BDIGITS(x);
5836  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5837 
5838 #ifdef USE_GMP
5839  if (xn < GMP_MUL_DIGITS)
5840  bary_sq_fast(zds, zn, xds, xn);
5841  else
5842  bary_mul(zds, zn, xds, xn, xds, xn);
5843 #else
5844  if (xn < KARATSUBA_MUL_DIGITS)
5845  bary_sq_fast(zds, zn, xds, xn);
5846  else
5847  bary_mul(zds, zn, xds, xn, xds, xn);
5848 #endif
5849 
5850  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
5851  return z;
5852 }
5853 
5854 static VALUE
5855 bigmul0(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5856 {
5857  long xn, yn, zn;
5858  VALUE z;
5859  BDIGIT *xds, *yds, *zds;
5860 
5861  if (x == y)
5862  return bigsq(x);
5863 
5864  xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
5865  yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y);
5866  zn = xn + yn;
5867 
5868  z = bignew(zn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
5869 
5870  xds = BDIGITS(x);
5871  yds = BDIGITS(y);
5872  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5873 
5874  bary_mul(zds, zn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
5875 
5876  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
5877  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
5878  return z;
5879 }

5881 /*
5882  * call-seq:
5883  * big * other -> Numeric
5884  *
5885  * Multiplies big and other, returning the result.
5886  */
5887 
5888 VALUE
5889 rb_big_mul(VALUE x, VALUE y)
5890 {
5891  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
5892  y = rb_int2big(FIX2LONG(y));
5893  }
5894  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
5895  }
5896  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
5897  return DBL2NUM(rb_big2dbl(x) * RFLOAT_VALUE(y));
5898  }
5899  else {
5900  return rb_num_coerce_bin(x, y, '*');
5901  }
5902 
5903  return bignorm(bigmul0(x, y));
5904 }
5905 
5906 static VALUE
5907 bigdivrem(VALUE x, VALUE y, volatile VALUE *divp, volatile VALUE *modp)
5908 {
5909  long xn = BIGNUM_LEN(x), yn = BIGNUM_LEN(y);
5910  VALUE z;
5911  BDIGIT *xds, *yds, *zds;
5912  BDIGIT dd;
5913 
5914  VALUE q = Qnil, r = Qnil;
5915  BDIGIT *qds, *rds;
5916  long qn, rn;
5917 
5918  yds = BDIGITS(y);
5919  BARY_TRUNC(yds, yn);
5920  if (yn == 0)
5921  rb_num_zerodiv();
5922 
5923  xds = BDIGITS(x);
5924  BARY_TRUNC(xds, xn);
5925 
5926  if (xn < yn || (xn == yn && xds[xn - 1] < yds[yn - 1])) {
5927  if (divp) *divp = rb_int2big(0);
5928  if (modp) *modp = x;
5929  return Qnil;
5930  }
5931  if (yn == 1) {
5932  dd = yds[0];
5933  z = bignew(xn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
5934  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5935  dd = bigdivrem_single(zds, xds, xn, dd);
5936  if (modp) {
5937  *modp = rb_uint2big((VALUE)dd);
5938  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(*modp, BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5939  }
5940  if (divp) *divp = z;
5941  return Qnil;
5942  }
5943  if (xn == 2 && yn == 2) {
5944  BDIGIT_DBL x0 = bary2bdigitdbl(xds, 2);
5945  BDIGIT_DBL y0 = bary2bdigitdbl(yds, 2);
5946  BDIGIT_DBL q0 = x0 / y0;
5947  BDIGIT_DBL r0 = x0 % y0;
5948  if (divp) {
5949  z = bignew(bdigit_roomof(sizeof(BDIGIT_DBL)), BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
5950  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5951  zds[0] = BIGLO(q0);
5952  zds[1] = BIGLO(BIGDN(q0));
5953  *divp = z;
5954  }
5955  if (modp) {
5956  z = bignew(bdigit_roomof(sizeof(BDIGIT_DBL)), BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5957  zds = BDIGITS(z);
5958  zds[0] = BIGLO(r0);
5959  zds[1] = BIGLO(BIGDN(r0));
5960  *modp = z;
5961  }
5962  return Qnil;
5963  }
5964 
5965  if (divp) {
5966  qn = xn + BIGDIVREM_EXTRA_WORDS;
5967  q = bignew(qn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x)==BIGNUM_SIGN(y));
5968  qds = BDIGITS(q);
5969  }
5970  else {
5971  qn = 0;
5972  qds = NULL;
5973  }
5974 
5975  if (modp) {
5976  rn = yn;
5977  r = bignew(rn, BIGNUM_SIGN(x));
5978  rds = BDIGITS(r);
5979  }
5980  else {
5981  rn = 0;
5982  rds = NULL;
5983  }
5984 
5985  bary_divmod_branch(qds, qn, rds, rn, xds, xn, yds, yn);
5986 
5987  if (divp) {
5988  bigtrunc(q);
5989  *divp = q;
5990  }
5991  if (modp) {
5992  bigtrunc(r);
5993  *modp = r;
5994  }
5995 
5996  return Qnil;
5997 }
5998 
5999 static void
6000 bigdivmod(VALUE x, VALUE y, volatile VALUE *divp, volatile VALUE *modp)
6001 {
6002  VALUE mod;
6003 
6004  bigdivrem(x, y, divp, &mod);
6005  if (BIGNUM_SIGN(x) != BIGNUM_SIGN(y) && !BIGZEROP(mod)) {
6006  if (divp) *divp = bigadd(*divp, rb_int2big(1), 0);
6007  if (modp) *modp = bigadd(mod, y, 1);
6008  }
6009  else if (modp) {
6010  *modp = mod;
6011  }
6012 }

6015 static VALUE
6016 rb_big_divide(VALUE x, VALUE y, ID op)
6017 {
6018  VALUE z;
6019 
6020  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6021  y = rb_int2big(FIX2LONG(y));
6022  }
6023  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6024  }
6025  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
6026  if (op == '/') {
6027  return DBL2NUM(rb_big2dbl(x) / RFLOAT_VALUE(y));
6028  }
6029  else {
6030  double dy = RFLOAT_VALUE(y);
6031  if (dy == 0.0) rb_num_zerodiv();
6032  return rb_dbl2big(rb_big2dbl(x) / dy);
6033  }
6034  }
6035  else {
6036  return rb_num_coerce_bin(x, y, op);
6037  }
6038  bigdivmod(x, y, &z, 0);
6039 
6040  return bignorm(z);
6041 }

6044  * call-seq:
6045  * big / other -> Numeric

6049  * result.
6050  */

6090  }

6121 /*
6122  * call-seq:
6123  * big.divmod(numeric) -> array
6124  *
6125  * See <code>Numeric#divmod</code>.
6126  *
6127  */
6128 VALUE
6129 rb_big_divmod(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6130 {

6132

6134  y = rb_int2big(FIX2LONG(y));
6135  }
6136  else if (!RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6137  return rb_num_coerce_bin(x, y, rb_intern("divmod"));
6138  }
6139  bigdivmod(x, y, &div, &mod);
6140

6144 static VALUE
6145 big_shift(VALUE x, long n)
6146 {
6147  if (n < 0)
6148  return big_lshift(x, 1+(unsigned long)(-(n+1)));
6149  else if (n > 0)
6150  return big_rshift(x, (unsigned long)n);
6151  return x;
6152 }
6153 
6154 static VALUE
6155 big_fdiv(VALUE x, VALUE y, long ey)
6156 {
6157 #define DBL_BIGDIG ((DBL_MANT_DIG + BITSPERDIG) / BITSPERDIG)
6158  VALUE z;
6159  long l, ex;
6160 
6161  bigtrunc(x);
6162  l = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
6163  ex = l * BITSPERDIG - nlz(BDIGITS(x)[l-1]);
6164  ex -= 2 * DBL_BIGDIG * BITSPERDIG;
6165  if (ex) x = big_shift(x, ex);
6166 
6167  bigdivrem(x, y, &z, 0);
6168  l = ex - ey;
6169 #if SIZEOF_LONG > SIZEOF_INT
6170  {
6171  /* Visual C++ can't be here */
6172  if (l > INT_MAX) return DBL2NUM(INFINITY);
6173  if (l < INT_MIN) return DBL2NUM(0.0);
6174  }
6175 #endif
6176  return DBL2NUM(ldexp(big2dbl(z), (int)l));
6177 }
6178 
6179 static VALUE
6180 big_fdiv_int(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6181 {
6182  long l, ey;
6183  bigtrunc(y);
6184  l = BIGNUM_LEN(y);
6185  ey = l * BITSPERDIG - nlz(BDIGITS(y)[l-1]);
6186  ey -= DBL_BIGDIG * BITSPERDIG;
6187  if (ey) y = big_shift(y, ey);
6188  return big_fdiv(x, y, ey);
6189 }
6190 
6191 static VALUE
6192 big_fdiv_float(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6193 {
6194  int i;
6195  y = dbl2big(ldexp(frexp(RFLOAT_VALUE(y), &i), DBL_MANT_DIG));
6196  return big_fdiv(x, y, i - DBL_MANT_DIG);
6197 }
6198 
6199 /*
6200  * call-seq:
6201  * big.fdiv(numeric) -> float
6202  *
6203  * Returns the floating point result of dividing <i>big</i> by
6204  * <i>numeric</i>.
6205  *
6206  * -1234567890987654321.fdiv(13731) #=> -89910996357705.5
6207  * -1234567890987654321.fdiv(13731.24) #=> -89909424858035.7
6208  *
6209  */
6210 
6211 
6212 VALUE
6213 rb_big_fdiv(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6214 {
6215  double dx, dy;
6216 
6217  dx = big2dbl(x);
6218  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6219  dy = (double)FIX2LONG(y);
6220  if (isinf(dx))
6221  return big_fdiv_int(x, rb_int2big(FIX2LONG(y)));
6222  }
6223  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6224  dy = rb_big2dbl(y);
6225  if (isinf(dx) || isinf(dy))
6226  return big_fdiv_int(x, y);
6227  }
6228  else if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
6229  dy = RFLOAT_VALUE(y);
6230  if (isnan(dy))
6231  return y;
6232  if (isinf(dx))
6233  return big_fdiv_float(x, y);
6234  }
6235  else {
6236  return rb_num_coerce_bin(x, y, rb_intern("fdiv"));
6237  }
6238  return DBL2NUM(dx / dy);
6239 }
6240 
6241 /*
6242  * call-seq:
6243  * big ** exponent -> numeric
6244  *
6245  * Raises _big_ to the _exponent_ power (which may be an integer, float,
6246  * or anything that will coerce to a number). The result may be
6247  * a Fixnum, Bignum, or Float
6248  *
6249  * 123456789 ** 2 #=> 15241578750190521
6250  * 123456789 ** 1.2 #=> 5126464716.09932
6251  * 123456789 ** -2 #=> 6.5610001194102e-17
6252  */
6253 
6254 VALUE
6255 rb_big_pow(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6256 {
6257  double d;
6258  SIGNED_VALUE yy;
6259 
6260  again:
6261  if (y == INT2FIX(0)) return INT2FIX(1);
6262  if (RB_FLOAT_TYPE_P(y)) {
6263  d = RFLOAT_VALUE(y);
6264  if ((!BIGNUM_SIGN(x) && !BIGZEROP(x)) && d != round(d))
6265  return rb_funcall(rb_complex_raw1(x), rb_intern("**"), 1, y);
6266  }
6267  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6268  y = bignorm(y);
6269  if (FIXNUM_P(y))
6270  goto again;
6271  rb_warn("in a**b, b may be too big");
6272  d = rb_big2dbl(y);
6273  }
6274  else if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6275  yy = FIX2LONG(y);
6276 
6277  if (yy < 0)
6278  return rb_funcall(rb_rational_raw1(x), rb_intern("**"), 1, y);
6279  else {
6280  VALUE z = 0;
6281  SIGNED_VALUE mask;
6282  const size_t xbits = rb_absint_numwords(x, 1, NULL);
6283  const size_t BIGLEN_LIMIT = 32*1024*1024;
6284 
6285  if (xbits == (size_t)-1 ||
6286  (xbits > BIGLEN_LIMIT) ||
6287  (xbits * yy > BIGLEN_LIMIT)) {
6288  rb_warn("in a**b, b may be too big");
6289  d = (double)yy;
6290  }
6291  else {
6292  for (mask = FIXNUM_MAX + 1; mask; mask >>= 1) {
6293  if (z) z = bigsq(z);
6294  if (yy & mask) {
6295  z = z ? bigtrunc(bigmul0(z, x)) : x;
6296  }
6297  }
6298  return bignorm(z);
6299  }
6300  }
6301  }
6302  else {
6303  return rb_num_coerce_bin(x, y, rb_intern("**"));
6304  }
6305  return DBL2NUM(pow(rb_big2dbl(x), d));
6306 }
6307 
6308 static VALUE
6309 bigand_int(VALUE x, long xn, BDIGIT hibitsx, long y)
6310 {
6311  VALUE z;
6312  BDIGIT *xds, *zds;
6313  long zn;
6314  long i;
6315  BDIGIT hibitsy;
6316 
6317  if (y == 0) return INT2FIX(0);
6318  if (xn == 0) return hibitsx ? LONG2NUM(y) : 0;
6319  hibitsy = 0 <= y ? 0 : BDIGMAX;
6320  xds = BDIGITS(x);
6321 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
6322  if (!hibitsy) {
6323  y &= xds[0];
6324  return LONG2NUM(y);
6325  }
6326 #endif
6327 
6328  zn = xn;
6329 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
6330  if (hibitsx && zn < bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG))
6331  zn = bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG);
6332 #endif
6333 
6334  z = bignew(zn, 0);
6335  zds = BDIGITS(z);
6336 
6337 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
6338  i = 1;
6339  zds[0] = xds[0] & BIGLO(y);
6340 #else
6341  for (i=0; i < xn; i++) {
6342  if (y == 0 || y == -1) break;
6343  zds[i] = xds[i] & BIGLO(y);
6344  y = BIGDN(y);
6345  }
6346  for (; i < zn; i++) {
6347  if (y == 0 || y == -1) break;
6348  zds[i] = hibitsx & BIGLO(y);
6349  y = BIGDN(y);
6350  }
6351 #endif
6352  for (;i < xn; i++) {
6353  zds[i] = xds[i] & hibitsy;
6354  }
6355  for (;i < zn; i++) {
6356  zds[i] = hibitsx & hibitsy;
6357  }
6358  twocomp2abs_bang(z, hibitsx && hibitsy);
6359  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
6360  return bignorm(z);
6361 }
6362 
6363 /*
6364  * call-seq:
6365  * big & numeric -> integer
6366  *
6367  * Performs bitwise +and+ between _big_ and _numeric_.
6368  */
6369 
6370 VALUE
6371 rb_big_and(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6372 {
6373  VALUE z;
6374  BDIGIT *ds1, *ds2, *zds;
6375  long i, xn, yn, n1, n2;
6376  BDIGIT hibitsx, hibitsy;
6377  BDIGIT hibits1, hibits2;
6378  VALUE tmpv;
6379  BDIGIT tmph;
6380  long tmpn;
6381 
6382  if (!FIXNUM_P(y) && !RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6383  return rb_num_coerce_bit(x, y, '&');
6384  }
6385 
6386  hibitsx = abs2twocomp(&x, &xn);
6387  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6388  return bigand_int(x, xn, hibitsx, FIX2LONG(y));
6389  }
6390  hibitsy = abs2twocomp(&y, &yn);
6391  if (xn > yn) {
6392  tmpv = x; x = y; y = tmpv;
6393  tmpn = xn; xn = yn; yn = tmpn;
6394  tmph = hibitsx; hibitsx = hibitsy; hibitsy = tmph;
6395  }
6396  n1 = xn;
6397  n2 = yn;
6398  ds1 = BDIGITS(x);
6399  ds2 = BDIGITS(y);
6400  hibits1 = hibitsx;
6401  hibits2 = hibitsy;
6402 
6403  if (!hibits1)
6404  n2 = n1;
6405 
6406  z = bignew(n2, 0);
6407  zds = BDIGITS(z);
6408 
6409  for (i=0; i<n1; i++) {
6410  zds[i] = ds1[i] & ds2[i];
6411  }
6412  for (; i<n2; i++) {
6413  zds[i] = hibits1 & ds2[i];
6414  }
6415  twocomp2abs_bang(z, hibits1 && hibits2);
6416  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
6417  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
6418  return bignorm(z);
6419 }
6420 
6421 static VALUE
6422 bigor_int(VALUE x, long xn, BDIGIT hibitsx, long y)
6423 {
6424  VALUE z;
6425  BDIGIT *xds, *zds;
6426  long zn;
6427  long i;
6428  BDIGIT hibitsy;
6429 
6430  if (y == -1) return INT2FIX(-1);
6431  if (xn == 0) return hibitsx ? INT2FIX(-1) : LONG2FIX(y);
6432  hibitsy = 0 <= y ? 0 : BDIGMAX;
6433  xds = BDIGITS(x);
6434 
6435  zn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
6436 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
6437  if (zn < bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG))
6438  zn = bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG);
6439 #endif
6440  z = bignew(zn, 0);
6441  zds = BDIGITS(z);
6442 
6443 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
6444  i = 1;
6445  zds[0] = xds[0] | BIGLO(y);
6446  if (i < zn)
6447  goto y_is_fixed_point;
6448  goto finish;
6449 #else
6450  for (i=0; i < xn; i++) {
6451  if (y == 0 || y == -1) goto y_is_fixed_point;
6452  zds[i] = xds[i] | BIGLO(y);
6453  y = BIGDN(y);
6454  }
6455  if (hibitsx)
6456  goto fill_hibits;
6457  for (; i < zn; i++) {
6458  if (y == 0 || y == -1) goto y_is_fixed_point;
6459  zds[i] = BIGLO(y);
6460  y = BIGDN(y);
6461  }
6462  goto finish;
6463 #endif
6464 
6465  y_is_fixed_point:
6466  if (hibitsy)
6467  goto fill_hibits;
6468  for (; i < xn; i++) {
6469  zds[i] = xds[i];
6470  }
6471  if (hibitsx)
6472  goto fill_hibits;
6473  for (; i < zn; i++) {
6474  zds[i] = 0;
6475  }
6476  goto finish;
6477 
6478  fill_hibits:
6479  for (; i < zn; i++) {
6480  zds[i] = BDIGMAX;
6481  }
6482 
6483  finish:
6484  twocomp2abs_bang(z, hibitsx || hibitsy);
6485  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
6486  return bignorm(z);
6487 }

6489 /*
6490  * call-seq:
6491  * big | numeric -> integer
6492  *
6493  * Performs bitwise +or+ between _big_ and _numeric_.
6494  */
6495 
6496 VALUE
6497 rb_big_or(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6498 {
6499  VALUE z;
6500  BDIGIT *ds1, *ds2, *zds;
6501  long i, xn, yn, n1, n2;
6502  BDIGIT hibitsx, hibitsy;
6503  BDIGIT hibits1, hibits2;
6504  VALUE tmpv;
6505  BDIGIT tmph;
6506  long tmpn;
6507 
6508  if (!FIXNUM_P(y) && !RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6509  return rb_num_coerce_bit(x, y, '|');
6510  }
6511 
6512  hibitsx = abs2twocomp(&x, &xn);
6513  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6514  return bigor_int(x, xn, hibitsx, FIX2LONG(y));
6515  }
6516  hibitsy = abs2twocomp(&y, &yn);
6517  if (xn > yn) {
6518  tmpv = x; x = y; y = tmpv;
6519  tmpn = xn; xn = yn; yn = tmpn;
6520  tmph = hibitsx; hibitsx = hibitsy; hibitsy = tmph;
6521  }
6522  n1 = xn;
6523  n2 = yn;
6524  ds1 = BDIGITS(x);
6525  ds2 = BDIGITS(y);
6526  hibits1 = hibitsx;
6527  hibits2 = hibitsy;
6528 
6529  if (hibits1)
6530  n2 = n1;
6531 
6532  z = bignew(n2, 0);
6533  zds = BDIGITS(z);
6534 
6535  for (i=0; i<n1; i++) {
6536  zds[i] = ds1[i] | ds2[i];
6537  }
6538  for (; i<n2; i++) {
6539  zds[i] = hibits1 | ds2[i];
6540  }
6541  twocomp2abs_bang(z, hibits1 || hibits2);
6542  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
6543  RB_GC_GUARD(y);
6544  return bignorm(z);
6545 }

6547 static VALUE
6548 bigxor_int(VALUE x, long xn, BDIGIT hibitsx, long y)
6549 {
6550  VALUE z;
6551  BDIGIT *xds, *zds;
6552  long zn;
6553  long i;
6554  BDIGIT hibitsy;
6555 
6556  hibitsy = 0 <= y ? 0 : BDIGMAX;
6557  xds = BDIGITS(x);
6558  zn = BIGNUM_LEN(x);
6559 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT < SIZEOF_LONG
6560  if (zn < bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG))
6561  zn = bdigit_roomof(SIZEOF_LONG);
6562 #endif
6563  z = bignew(zn, 0);
6564  zds = BDIGITS(z);
6565 
6566 #if SIZEOF_BDIGIT >= SIZEOF_LONG
6567  i = 1;
6568  zds[0] = xds[0] ^ BIGLO(y);
6569 #else
6570  for (i = 0; i < xn; i++) {
6571  zds[i] = xds[i] ^ BIGLO(y);
6572  y = BIGDN(y);
6573  }
6574  for (; i < zn; i++) {
6575  zds[i] = hibitsx ^ BIGLO(y);
6576  y = BIGDN(y);
6577  }
6578 #endif
6579  for (; i < xn; i++) {
6580  zds[i] = xds[i] ^ hibitsy;
6581  }
6582  for (; i < zn; i++) {
6583  zds[i] = hibitsx ^ hibitsy;
6584  }
6585  twocomp2abs_bang(z, (hibitsx ^ hibitsy) != 0);
6586  RB_GC_GUARD(x);
6587  return bignorm(z);
6588 }

6613  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6614  return bigxor_int(x, xn, hibitsx, FIX2LONG(y));
6615  }
6616  hibitsy = abs2twocomp(&y, &yn);
6617  if (xn > yn) {

6619  tmpn = xn; xn = yn; yn = tmpn;
