6644 /*
6645  * call-seq:
6646  * big << numeric -> integer
6647  *
6648  * Shifts big left _numeric_ positions (right if _numeric_ is negative).
6649  */
6650 
6651 VALUE
6652 rb_big_lshift(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6653 {
6654  int lshift_p;
6655  size_t shift_numdigits;
6656  int shift_numbits;
6657 
6658  for (;;) {
6659  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6660  long l = FIX2LONG(y);
6661  unsigned long shift;
6662  if (0 <= l) {
6663  lshift_p = 1;
6664  shift = l;
6665  }
6666  else {
6667  lshift_p = 0;
6668  shift = 1+(unsigned long)(-(l+1));
6669  }
6670  shift_numbits = (int)(shift & (BITSPERDIG-1));
6671  shift_numdigits = shift >> bit_length(BITSPERDIG-1);
6672  return bignorm(big_shift3(x, lshift_p, shift_numdigits, shift_numbits));
6673  }
6674  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6675  return bignorm(big_shift2(x, 1, y));
6676  }
6677  y = rb_to_int(y);
6678  }
6679 }

6683  * call-seq:
6684  * big >> numeric -> integer
6685  *
6686  * Shifts big right _numeric_ positions (left if _numeric_ is negative).
6687  */
6688 
6689 VALUE
6690 rb_big_rshift(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6691 {

6693  size_t shift_numdigits;
6694  int shift_numbits;
6695

6698  long l = FIX2LONG(y);
6699  unsigned long shift;
6700  if (0 <= l) {
6701  lshift_p = 0;
6702  shift = l;
6703  }
6704  else {
6705  lshift_p = 1;
6706  shift = 1+(unsigned long)(-(l+1));
6707  }
6708  shift_numbits = (int)(shift & (BITSPERDIG-1));
6709  shift_numdigits = shift >> bit_length(BITSPERDIG-1);
6710  return bignorm(big_shift3(x, lshift_p, shift_numdigits, shift_numbits));
6711  }
6712  else if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6713  return bignorm(big_shift2(x, 0, y));
6714  }

6718 
6719 /*
6720  * call-seq:
6721  * big[n] -> 0, 1
6722  *
6723  * Bit Reference---Returns the <em>n</em>th bit in the (assumed) binary
6724  * representation of <i>big</i>, where <i>big</i>[0] is the least
6725  * significant bit.
6726  *
6727  * a = 9**15
6728  * 50.downto(0) do |n|
6729  * print a[n]
6730  * end
6731  *
6732  * <em>produces:</em>
6733  *
6734  * 000101110110100000111000011110010100111100010111001
6735  *
6736  */
6737 
6738 static VALUE
6739 rb_big_aref(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6740 {
6741  BDIGIT *xds;
6742  size_t shift;
6743  size_t i, s1, s2;
6744  long l;
6745  BDIGIT bit;
6746 
6747  if (RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6748  if (!BIGNUM_SIGN(y))
6749  return INT2FIX(0);
6750  bigtrunc(y);
6751  if (BIGSIZE(y) > sizeof(size_t)) {
6752  out_of_range:
6753  return BIGNUM_SIGN(x) ? INT2FIX(0) : INT2FIX(1);
6754  }
6755 #if SIZEOF_SIZE_T <= SIZEOF_LONG
6756  shift = big2ulong(y, "long");
6757 #else
6758  shift = big2ull(y, "long long");
6759 #endif
6760  }
6761  else {
6762  l = NUM2LONG(y);
6763  if (l < 0) return INT2FIX(0);
6764  shift = (size_t)l;
6765  }
6766  s1 = shift/BITSPERDIG;
6767  s2 = shift%BITSPERDIG;
6768  bit = (BDIGIT)1 << s2;
6769 
6770  if (s1 >= BIGNUM_LEN(x)) goto out_of_range;
6771 
6772  xds = BDIGITS(x);
6773  if (BIGNUM_POSITIVE_P(x))
6774  return (xds[s1] & bit) ? INT2FIX(1) : INT2FIX(0);
6775  if (xds[s1] & (bit-1))
6776  return (xds[s1] & bit) ? INT2FIX(0) : INT2FIX(1);
6777  for (i = 0; i < s1; i++)
6778  if (xds[i])
6779  return (xds[s1] & bit) ? INT2FIX(0) : INT2FIX(1);
6780  return (xds[s1] & bit) ? INT2FIX(1) : INT2FIX(0);
6781 }
6782 
6783 /*
6784  * call-seq:
6785  * big.hash -> fixnum
6786  *
6787  * Compute a hash based on the value of _big_.
6788  *
6789  * See also Object#hash.
6790  */
6791 
6792 static VALUE
6793 rb_big_hash(VALUE x)
6794 {
6795  st_index_t hash;
6796 
6797  hash = rb_memhash(BDIGITS(x), sizeof(BDIGIT)*BIGNUM_LEN(x)) ^ BIGNUM_SIGN(x);
6798  return INT2FIX(hash);
6799 }
6800 
6801 /*
6802  * call-seq:
6803  * big.coerce(numeric) -> array
6804  *
6805  * Returns an array with both a +numeric+ and a +big+ represented as Bignum
6806  * objects.
6807  *
6808  * This is achieved by converting +numeric+ to a Bignum.
6809  *
6810  * A TypeError is raised if the +numeric+ is not a Fixnum or Bignum type.
6811  *
6812  * (0x3FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF+1).coerce(42) #=> [42, 4611686018427387904]
6813  */
6814 
6815 static VALUE
6816 rb_big_coerce(VALUE x, VALUE y)
6817 {
6818  if (FIXNUM_P(y)) {
6819  y = rb_int2big(FIX2LONG(y));
6820  }
6821  else if (!RB_BIGNUM_TYPE_P(y)) {
6822  rb_raise(rb_eTypeError, "can't coerce %s to Bignum",
6823  rb_obj_classname(y));
6824  }
6825  return rb_assoc_new(y, x);
6826 }
6827 
6828 /*
6829  * call-seq:
6830  * big.abs -> aBignum
6831  * big.magnitude -> aBignum
6832  *
6833  * Returns the absolute value of <i>big</i>.
6834  *
6835  * -1234567890987654321.abs #=> 1234567890987654321
6836  */
6837 
6838 static VALUE
6839 rb_big_abs(VALUE x)
6840 {
6841  if (!BIGNUM_SIGN(x)) {
6842  x = rb_big_clone(x);
6843  BIGNUM_SET_SIGN(x, 1);
6844  }
6845  return x;
6846 }
6847 
6848 /*
6849  * call-seq:
6850  * big.size -> integer
6851  *
6852  * Returns the number of bytes in the machine representation of
6853  * <i>big</i>.
6854  *
6855  * (256**10 - 1).size #=> 12
6856  * (256**20 - 1).size #=> 20
6857  * (256**40 - 1).size #=> 40
6858  */
6859 
6860 static VALUE
6861 rb_big_size(VALUE big)
6862 {
6863  return SIZET2NUM(BIGSIZE(big));
6864 }
6865 
6866 /*
6867  * call-seq:
6868  * int.bit_length -> integer
6869  *
6870  * Returns the number of bits of the value of <i>int</i>.
6871  *
6872  * "the number of bits" means that
6873  * the bit position of the highest bit which is different to the sign bit.
6874  * (The bit position of the bit 2**n is n+1.)
6875  * If there is no such bit (zero or minus one), zero is returned.
6876  *
6877  * I.e. This method returns ceil(log2(int < 0 ? -int : int+1)).
6878  *
6879  * (-2**10000-1).bit_length #=> 10001
6880  * (-2**10000).bit_length #=> 10000
6881  * (-2**10000+1).bit_length #=> 10000
6882  *
6883  * (-2**1000-1).bit_length #=> 1001
6884  * (-2**1000).bit_length #=> 1000
6885  * (-2**1000+1).bit_length #=> 1000
6886  *
6887  * (2**1000-1).bit_length #=> 1000
6888  * (2**1000).bit_length #=> 1001
6889  * (2**1000+1).bit_length #=> 1001
6890  *
6891  * (2**10000-1).bit_length #=> 10000
6892  * (2**10000).bit_length #=> 10001
6893  * (2**10000+1).bit_length #=> 10001
6894  *
6895  * This method can be used to detect overflow in Array#pack as follows.
6896  *
6897  * if n.bit_length < 32
6898  * [n].pack("l") # no overflow
6899  * else
6900  * raise "overflow"
6901  * end
6902  */
6903 
6904 static VALUE
6905 rb_big_bit_length(VALUE big)
6906 {
6907  int nlz_bits;
6908  size_t numbytes;
6909 
6910  static const BDIGIT char_bit[1] = { CHAR_BIT };
6911  BDIGIT numbytes_bary[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(size_t))];
6912  BDIGIT nlz_bary[1];
6913  BDIGIT result_bary[bdigit_roomof(sizeof(size_t)+1)];
6914 
6915  numbytes = rb_absint_size(big, &nlz_bits);
6916 
6917  if (numbytes == 0)
6918  return LONG2FIX(0);
6919 
6920  if (BIGNUM_NEGATIVE_P(big) && rb_absint_singlebit_p(big)) {
6921  if (nlz_bits != CHAR_BIT-1) {
6922  nlz_bits++;
6923  }
6924  else {
6925  nlz_bits = 0;
6926  numbytes--;
6927  }
6928  }
6929 
6930  if (numbytes <= SIZE_MAX / CHAR_BIT) {
6931  return SIZET2NUM(numbytes * CHAR_BIT - nlz_bits);
6932  }
6933 
6934  nlz_bary[0] = nlz_bits;
6935 
6936  bary_unpack(BARY_ARGS(numbytes_bary), &numbytes, 1, sizeof(numbytes), 0,
6937  INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER);
6938  BARY_SHORT_MUL(result_bary, numbytes_bary, char_bit);
6939  BARY_SUB(result_bary, result_bary, nlz_bary);
6940 
6941  return rb_integer_unpack(result_bary, numberof(result_bary), sizeof(BDIGIT), 0,
6942  INTEGER_PACK_LSWORD_FIRST|INTEGER_PACK_NATIVE_BYTE_ORDER);
6943 }
6944 
6945 /*
6946  * call-seq:
6947  * big.odd? -> true or false
6948  *
6949  * Returns <code>true</code> if <i>big</i> is an odd number.
6950  */
6951 
6952 static VALUE
6953 rb_big_odd_p(VALUE num)
6954 {
6955  if (BIGNUM_LEN(num) != 0 && BDIGITS(num)[0] & 1) {
6956  return Qtrue;
6957  }
6958  return Qfalse;
6959 }
6960 
6961 /*
6962  * call-seq:
6963  * big.even? -> true or false
6964  *
6965  * Returns <code>true</code> if <i>big</i> is an even number.
6966  */
6967 
6968 static VALUE
6969 rb_big_even_p(VALUE num)
6970 {
6971  if (BIGNUM_LEN(num) != 0 && BDIGITS(num)[0] & 1) {
6972  return Qfalse;
6973  }
6974  return Qtrue;
6975 }
6976 
6977 /*
6978  * Bignum objects hold integers outside the range of
6979  * Fixnum. Bignum objects are created
6980  * automatically when integer calculations would otherwise overflow a
6981  * Fixnum. When a calculation involving
6982  * Bignum objects returns a result that will fit in a
6983  * Fixnum, the result is automatically converted.
6984  *
6985  * For the purposes of the bitwise operations and <code>[]</code>, a
6986  * Bignum is treated as if it were an infinite-length
6987  * bitstring with 2's complement representation.
6988  *
6989  * While Fixnum values are immediate, Bignum
6990  * objects are not---assignment and parameter passing work with
6991  * references to objects, not the objects themselves.
6992  *
6993  */
6994 
6995 void
6996 Init_Bignum(void)
6997 {
6998  rb_cBignum = rb_define_class("Bignum", rb_cInteger);
6999 
7000  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "to_s", rb_big_to_s, -1);
7001  rb_define_alias(rb_cBignum, "inspect", "to_s");

7013  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "fdiv", rb_big_fdiv, 1);
7014  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "**", rb_big_pow, 1);
7015  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "&", rb_big_and, 1);
7016  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "|", rb_big_or, 1);

7020  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, ">>", rb_big_rshift, 1);

7022 
7023  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "<=>", rb_big_cmp, 1);
7024  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "==", rb_big_eq, 1);
7025  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, ">", big_gt, 1);

7027  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "<", big_lt, 1);
7028  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "<=", big_le, 1);
7029  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "===", rb_big_eq, 1);
7030  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "eql?", rb_big_eql, 1);
7031  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "hash", rb_big_hash, 0);
7032  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "to_f", rb_big_to_f, 0);
7033  rb_define_method(rb_cBignum, "abs", rb_big_abs, 0);

7039 
7040 #ifdef USE_GMP

7042  rb_define_const(rb_cBignum, "GMP_VERSION", rb_sprintf("GMP %s", gmp_version));
7043 #endif
7044 
7045  power_cache_init();
7046 }
